title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water, margarine and cornstarch.
Cook until clear. Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Let cool.
Add to strawberries. Pour into baked pie shell and top with whipped topping.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Form into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.
While warm, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: ground beef in sour cream-tomato sauce
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, egg, Worcestershire sauce, grated onion and salt; shape into four patties.
Brown well on both sides in butter and skillet.
Remove from pan.
Add flour to butter in pan; blend well.
Gradually add tomatoes and sour cream.
Return meat patties to sauce.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes.

title: cherry mash candy
directions: Mix milk, sugar, frosting mix, vanilla, cherries and cherry juice. Roll into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Freeze.
Melt chocolate chips and grated wax in double boiler over hot water. Add peanuts to chocolate mixture.
Dip frozen balls in chocolate mixture and put on wax paper.
Makes a large batch.

title: microwave chunky apple butter
directions: Combine in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch dish.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Cook at 100° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; uncover and mash if desired.
Cook, uncovered, at 100° for 10 minutes longer.
Pack in sterile jars, or let stand until cool. Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator for up to 2 months.
(To make without sugar, reduce cooking time.)

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown and drain
ground beef in Dutch oven.
Saute in 1 teaspoon oil the onion and pepper.
Add seasonings.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours; remove bay leaves.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: kentucky jam cake
directions: Put all ingredients except pecans in large mixing bowl; blend with
mixer,
then
beat
minutes on medium speed of mixer, scraping bowl often. Fold in pecans.
Pour into greased and floured pans and bake 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with caramel frosting.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream
cheese
and
oleo
in
food
processor.
Add ice water, flour,
salt and red pepper.
Roll out of cookie press with star disc on ungreased, but lightly floured cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch lengths.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream shortening and butter in mixing bowl.
Add vanilla. Gradually beat in sugar.
Add milk; beat until light and fluffy.

title: natural sweet treat
directions: Mix honey and peanut butter in a bowl.
Stir in nonfat dry milk, a little at a time, until thoroughly blended.
Shape into narrow rolls. Wrap in wax paper and chill until firm.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in flour.
Add salt, coconut and nuts.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in preheated oven at 300°.
Store cooled cookies in an airtight container about 5 days before serving. Then enjoy!

title: zucchini vegetable
directions: Slice zucchini.
Chop onion and tomato.
Saute zucchini in small amount of oleo until limp and keep stirring.
Push zucchini aside and add onion and tomato.
Add lemon juice.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and basil or dill weed.
Salt and pepper to taste. Stir over medium high heat until tomato and/or zucchini get soft. Add tomato sauce.
Sprinkle cheese on.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes ore until thickens.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil until browned.
Drain on paper towels.

title: sausage balls
directions: Shred cheese.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Roll into small balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Bake until brown, about 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed in milk for 1 hour.

title: chocolate oatmeal brownie
directions: Beat butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Stir in oatmeal and 1/2 cup chocolate chips.
Spread in ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining chocolate chips.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix with electric mixer sugar and cream cheese.
Add strawberries, bananas, crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix and freeze 24 hours before serving.

title: tuna boats
directions: Mix up your favorite tuna sandwich mix.
Add hard-cooked eggs if desired.
Toast one side of bread under broiler; place some tuna mixture on other side.
Put slice of Velveeta on top.
Return to broiler and heat until cheese melts.
Or put on hamburger bun and heat until cheese melts (can use one bun to make 2 sandwiches or one closed sandwich).
Try canned chicken instead of tuna also.

title: walnut crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts; mix well.
Chill for 3 hours or longer.
Form dough into long rolls, 1/2 inch across.
Cut in 3-inch lengths.
Shape into crescents.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 15 minutes. Do not brown.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: instant boiled custard
directions: Mix sugar, pudding and milk.
Stir as you add until mix and sugar dissolves.
Pour in container; cover and chill.
Add more milk if it's too thick.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Dip tortillas in chicken broth.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with tortillas.
Saute chopped onion and pepper in butter.
Mix 2 cans soup and tomatoes over heat.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over tortillas.
Cover with another layer of tortillas.
Cover with rest of mixture and put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbling.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Make a paste of the cocoa and food coloring. Add to batter.
Blend.
Add flour, salt and soda alternating with the buttermilk and vinegar. Blend completely.
Pour into two floured 9-inch round cake pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion until brown; add tomato sauce and catsup. Pour into shallow baking dish and top with cheese.
Pinch biscuits into small pieces and place on top.
Bake uncovered until brown.

title: becky's pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve 1 cup sugar in 1 cup water and bring to boil.
Set aside.
Dissolve 3 tablespoons plain gelatin in another cup of water.
Add to hot sugar and water.
When cool, add 2 large cans unsweetened, crushed pineapple with juice.
Fill serving bowl with 1/2 and chill until set.
Thin 8 ounce package of cream cheese with milk until of spreading consistency.
Mix 1/2 cup chopped nuts into cream cheese and spread over chilled mixture.
Add remaining mixture and chill until firm.

title: mom's corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
If you like thin corn bread, use a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
If you like your corn bread thick, use a 9-inch square greased and floured pan. Beat eggs and sour milk together; add sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add to milk mixture.
Stir baking soda into hot water and stir into mixture.
If this mixture seems too thick, add a little sour cream or buttermilk.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: stuffed cukes
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seeds. Combine cream cheese and deviled ham.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon into cucumber.
Cover and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Cut each in half and then 2 quarters.

title: charcoal-broiled shrimp
directions: Combine oil, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and garlic salt; marinate shrimp in sauce at least 1 hour.
Grill on a wire rack over coals 5 minutes per side or until shrimp turn pink. (Do not overcook.)
Serve with cocktail sauce for dunking.

title: watergate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoon on greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chili cheese roll-up
directions: Combine cream cheese, green chilies and onion salt in a bowl. Spread a thin layer on each tortilla.
Roll and let set in fridge 1 hour.
Slice into pinwheels.
Serve as appetizer.

title: easy vegetable casserole
directions: Put drained vegetables in bottom of a deep casserole dish.
Set aside.
In a bowl, mix together cream of chicken soup, mayonnaise and onion.
Pour on top of vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese on top of that, then the crackers on top of cheese.
Pour butter over the top of it all and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add onion.
Cook until onion is tender. Add rice,
mushrooms
and
soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Note:
I also add plain yogurt and oat bran.

title: wendy's hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into patties.
Fry or grill.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease
and flour two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Beat eggs,
then
add pumpkin, oil and sugar.
Mix well. Add dry
ingredients
just
until moistened.
Add nuts. Bake about 1 hour or until pick comes out clean.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix salsa and refried beans; spread in bottom of pan.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Layer on top of salsa and bean mixture.
In layers, add lettuce, cheese, tomatoes, chilies and black olives.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets, or bake in microwave (not too mushy).
Cool; peel.
Grate them into baking dish.
Heat other ingredients together until cheese melts.
Pour over potatoes. Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: lime sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers into about 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices and soak in lime water mixture for 24 hours.
Rinse in clear water twice.
Let stand in clear water for 2 hours.
Bring vinegar, sugar and spices to a boil.
Then add 1 teaspoon of salt and cucumbers.
Simmer 3 hours.
Pack in jars and seal.
Makes a crisp, spicy pickle.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken in salt and pepper water.
Debone and dice.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Bring to boiling point. Beat the eggs gradually.
Add syrup mixture.
Add pecans, salt and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix in order given.
Add 1 c. grated cheese.
Bake at 350°F for 1 or 1 1/2 hours in greased casserole dish.
May use other meats.

title: quick and easy salad
directions: Stir all together and chill.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind up onions and peppers, then add rest of ingredients. Bring to boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Boil jars and lids.
Put relish in hot jars and seal.

title: nutty balls(cookies)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
When cold, re-roll in powdered sugar.

title: annie wingate's chicken sesame
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt oleo in baking dish.
Mix egg and milk together.
Dip pieces of chicken in milk and egg mixture. Roll in dry ingredients.
Lay chicken skin side down in baking dish.
Sprinkle pecans over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Turn and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: cheeseburger rice
directions: Brown ground beef in large nonstick skillet; drain. Add water, ketchup and mustard. Bring to a boil. Stir in rice. Sprinkle with cheese and cover. Cook on low heat for 5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: barbecued venison
directions: Cut venison into small pieces and trim off fat.
Cover venison with water and cook for 4 hours covered.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 2 hours.
Serve on buns or French bread.

title: cheryl's cheesecake
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla with mixer until smooth.
Pour equally into 2 pie crusts.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes, just until the center of the pie is firm.
Cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese and Cheddar cheese at room temperature, then add onion; mix.
Roll into a ball, then roll onto diced dried beef.

title: galliano
directions: Boil sugar and water together to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Add vodka, anise and yellow food coloring.
Pour into bottles with airtight caps.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: truffles
directions: Gradually add sugar to cream cheese, mixing well as you add. Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix well.
Chill several hours. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in chopped almonds, cocoa or additional powdered sugar.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: swedish brownies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt in small bowl.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla to melted margarine.
Add flour mixture.
Blend well with mixing spoon.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes. Let cool before cutting.

title: red bean salad
directions: Mix all together.
Great on a hot summer day with your favorite sandwich.

title: large applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Mix well, then add applesauce.
Sift dry ingredients together and add slowly to mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.
Candied fruits, raisins and nuts may be added for fruit cake.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine Crisco and boiling water; stir over low heat until Crisco is melted.
Add flour and salt all at once; beat until ingredients are completely smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously after each.
Drop from tablespoon onto lightly greased baking sheet, 2 inches between each puff.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake 20 minutes longer.
Puffs should be golden brown and crisp.
When cold, cut off tops with a sharp knife.
Fill with flavored whipped cream, ice cream or a filling made from a pudding mix.
Replace tops and serve.

title: old-fashioned white cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together with water until they are well creamed.
Use approximately 3 tablespoons water.
Add salt, nutmeg, vanilla and cream.
Stir well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle a little nutmeg over the top of the pie and dot with butter.
Bake in 325° oven for about an hour.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Combine milk and water, butter and salt in saucepan.
Bring to lukewarm.
Add yeast and egg.
Stir in flour to form soft dough.
Beat vigorously. Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Place in pan and let rise to top of pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until medium brown. Take from oven and butter tops.
Place rolls onto a clean towel and let cool.

title: flanc
directions: Beat all ingredients until foamy.
Pour in 1 1/2 quart dish. Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: onion tart(zwiebelkuchen)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease an 11-inch quiche pan; set aside.
Using a pastry blender or fork, work butter into flour. Stir in 1 egg, half and half and salt to make a dough.
Let stand in a cool place for a few minutes.
Thinly slice onions.
Fry bacon in a small skillet over medium heat until golden brown.
Add onion rings and saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain off excess fat.
In medium bowl, beat together whipping cream, eggs, salt and pepper.
On a slightly floured surface, roll out pastry.
Line pan with pastry, pricking surface with a fork.
Spread bacon and onions over pastry. Pour in cream mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake 20 minutes, remove foil and bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until set.
Cut into squares or wedges and serve warm.
Ingredients may be doubled if desired.
Bake on a large baking sheet or jelly roll pan.
Puff pastry or pizza dough can be substituted for pastry.
Serve with chilled white wine.

title: yellow cake mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes, or until done.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top of cake when removed from oven.

title: banana punch
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend mixture well and freeze in plastic containers.
When ready to use, begin thawing and add ginger ale, 7-Up or Sprite in punch bowl with frozen fruit mixture.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Prepare vegetables and add to broth.
Boil together until tender, about 20 minutes.
One serving is about 35 calories.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all well.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: cajun chicken strips
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in plastic bag.
Add chicken, 1/2 at a time and shake to coat.
Melt butter in skillet.
Fry chicken strips 8 to 10 minutes.

title: new england fish chowder
directions: In a 6 to 8 quart kettle, melt 1/4 cup butter over medium heat.
Saute onions until tender, but not brown; add potatoes, salt, pepper and water.
Top with fish.
Simmer covered 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in scalded evaporated milk and remaining butter; heat through.
Season with additional salt and pepper if desired.
Yields about 4 1/2 quarts.

title: julia's t cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs and extract.
Sift together the baking powder and flour and add to mixture.
Knead well.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Make a syrup of the vinegar and sugar and add to a spice bag made of cloves and ginger root, if desired.
Add cinnamon sticks to the syrup.
Add peaches to this boiling syrup.
Cook until the fruit can be easily pierced with a straw.
Let stand in a covered kettle overnight.
Next day, pack into sterilized jars.
Fill jar to within 1/2 inch of the top with fruit and syrup.
Put on cap, screw band tight and process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes.

title: italian sauce
directions: Combine tomatoes and tomato sauce in saucepan.
Heat over medium-high. Combine cornstarch and cooking wine. Add to sauce. Add remaining ingredients. Stir occasionally until thickened.
Use this sauce as a pizza sauce, spaghetti sauce or on any other Italian dish.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix melted butter, onions, mustard and Worcestershire sauce together and chill. Open rolls and spread mixture on rolls; add ham and cheese. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve warm or cold.

title: slightly easier chicken kiev
directions: Early in day, melt butter; add thyme and pour in bowl.
Freeze. About 1 hour before serving, place a chicken breast between layers of clear plastic wrap; pound flat with meat mallet and repeat with remaining 3 chicken breasts.
Salt and lightly pepper both sides of chicken breast.
Break up frozen butter and place 1/4 in middle along the length of each chicken breast.
Roll up jelly roll style and secure with toothpick.
Roll to coat in flour, then egg and milk mixture, then bread crumbs.
Place back in freezer for 20 minutes.

title: oriental spinach salad
directions: Soak bean sprouts and Chinese vegetables in cold water for several hours until crisp.
Drain thoroughly.
Wash, dry and chill spinach.

In a bowl, combine oil, soy sauce, lemon juice, onion, sesame seed, salt and pepper; let stand for 1 hour. Arrange spinach in salad bowl; top with sprouts and Chinese vegetables, then water chestnuts.
Pour dressing over and toss thoroughly.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix beans, Velveeta cheese, 2 tablespoons of green onions and seasonings in a saucepan.
Stir over low heat until Velveeta is melted.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients; bring to a rolling boil for exactly 1 minute.
Cool; beat and pour into a 9-inch square pan.
Substitute brown sugar and omit cocoa for caramel icing.

title: scallops sauteed with herbs and vegetables
directions: Stir-fry the julienned vegetables in a frypan in 2 tablespoons butter for 1 minute; add wine and simmer for 3 minutes.
Keep warm. Pat scallops dry.
Melt 1/4 cup butter in a frypan over medium heat; add scallops.
Cook and stir until scallops are almost done, about 3 minutes; add herbs, seasonings and vegetables.
Blend flour and soft butter.
Push scallops and vegetables to the side of pan; whisk in butter and flour.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened. Spoon into puff pastry shells and sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: giant shells
directions: Cook shells as directed.
Brown beef, onion and garlic until beef is crumbly.
Drain fat; cool.
Stir in cheese, crumbs, parsley and eggs.
Stuff shells.
Spoon 1/4 spaghetti sauce in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place shells on top.
Pour rest of meat and sauce over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: heavenly hawaiian cream
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve 1/4 cup syrup. Cut cherries into fourths. Combine pineapple, marshmallows, cherries and reserved syrup. Let stand 1 hour. Fold in whipped cream. Spoon into dessert dishes and chill. Melt butter in skillet. Toast almonds. When ready to serve, sprinkle coconut and almonds over dessert.

title: hungarian stuffed peppers
directions: Slow cooking is the secret.

title: white cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar for 15 minutes; add milk alternately with flour.
Mix baking powder with flour and sift 3 times.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: tuna ring mold
directions: In large size bowl, soften gelatin in cold water; heat soup to boiling in saucepan.
Pour into bowl, mixing with gelatin, until gelatin is dissolved.
Beat until smooth.
Blend in cottage cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 5 cup ring mold or fish mold.
Chill until firm.
To serve, garnish with greens.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough for 1 hour; slice into 1/8-inch slices. Line foil lined 14-inch pizza pan with slices, overlapping edges slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool; place on plate.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
spread over crust.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese layer.
Glaze with marmalade and water.
Chill.

title: cheese parfait
directions: Place cheese in a bowl of electric mixer; add sugar and mix well for 2 minutes.
Add Tia Maria and mix for 1 minute.
Add whipped cream and chopped strawberries; mix well using a spatula! Spoon into parfait glasses and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Decorate with fresh strawberries.

title: chicken casserole - velveeta
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place a layer into casserole dish. Add a layer of cooked, drained noodles.
Pour half of the soup and milk mixture (mixed together) over chicken and noodles.
Place a layer of cheese on top.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, having cheese on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done and brown on top.

title: quick and easy broccoli soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water at high heat.
When dissolved, add broccoli, hash browns and onions.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium and add soup and cheese.
Stir occasionally.
When cheese is melted, soup is ready.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter bottom of deep Pyrex dish.
Butter both sides of bread; place on bottom of dish.
Mix together other ingredients, except cheese; pour on top of bread.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Let stand 3 to 5 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: fried kielbasa
directions: In large saucepan saute onions in butter.
Meanwhile cut potatoes in chunks.
Toss everything else in and cook at medium heat for about 30 minutes.

title: fish florentine with lemon mayonnaise
directions: Clean fresh spinach, removing stems and wilted leaves, then chop finely (or thaw frozen chopped spinach).
In a large saucepan, cook spinach in water to cover until tender, 5 minutes at most.
Remove from heat and drain spinach very thoroughly. Spread in bottom of buttered, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Spread fish fillets over spinach.
Combine mayonnaise with lemon juice and salt, stirring to fully mix.
Pour over fish fillets and spinach, coating evenly, then sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes until fish is done, but not dry.
Serve hot with fresh lemon quarters.
Serves 4.

title: filled angel food cake
directions: In medium bowl mix frosting of whipping cream and sugar.
In another medium bowl mix filling of crushed pineapple, strawberries and marshmallows.
Hollow out the inside of the angel food cake, keeping about 1/2-inch sides.
Fold half of the frosting in the filling.
Keep other half to ice the cake with.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: pina colada fruit dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine dry pudding mix and dry milk powder. Add yogurt, water and pineapple with juice.
Mix well using a wire whisk.
Blend in Cool Whip lite, coconut extract and rum extract. Add banana.
Mix gently to combine.
Evenly spoon mixture into 6 dessert dishes.
Top each with 1 teaspoon flaked coconut. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken until done. Cook spaghetti in leftover chicken stock; save 2 cups of stock for sauce. Chop onion and green pepper and cook in mushroom liquid.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain.
Mix tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, pepper and garlic with meat.
Mix egg, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley, oregano and basil in bowl.
Layer cooked noodles in baking pan, then meat mixture, next cottage cheese mixture, then Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: italian fritters
directions: Combine ingredients and set aside for 1 hour.
Drop by the tablespoon into hot oil (2-inches).
Do not crowd pan.
Remove when done.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together margarine and brown sugar.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs to margarine mixture and beat until light.
Add pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients; add rolled oats and vanilla and stir thoroughly.
Finally, add fruit and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets and bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned and top springs back when touched lightly.
Cool on wire racks.
Yield: approximately 6 dozen.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook until a soft ball forms. Mix last four ingredients and add to cooked mixture.
Stir until spreading consistency.

title: strawberry pie
directions: *If using frozen, drain and pat well.

title: raisin pie
directions: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil. Add raisins and cook uncovered for 3 to 5 minutes or until plump and tender.
Remove from heat.

title: quick and easy snacks
directions: Mix all together and put in an airtight container.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes.
Mix all ingredients together well and spoon into an ovenproof serving dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Serve with crackers.

title: crumb cake
directions: Crumble first 3 ingredients together.
Save 1 cup of crumbs for top of cake.
To remainder of crumbs, add spices, sour milk, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Put in pan (9 x 12 x 3-inch) and sprinkle reserved crumbs on top of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and shortening in a large bowl.
Heat applesauce in a saucepan.
Add soda; cook until foams. Add to sugar and shortening, stirring until sugar melts.

title: cherry-o-cheese pie
directions: Beat until fluffy.
Add milk.
Stir until thoroughly mixed. Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours (don't freeze), then pour cherries on top.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir in shortening. Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons water.
Add to buttermilk.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Will keep in refrigerator for a week.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add vodka, if desired.

title: unbaked chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo in saucepan. Boil one minute. Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Drop from teaspoon on waxed paper; let stand until hardened.

title: armadillo stew(if all else fails, try this recipe!)
directions: Leave the meat set out of doors overnight.
Microwave for 11 hours.
Put in a large pot of boiling water, then add other ingredients in any order.
Let this boil until Tuesday night. Serve this mess to the two armadillos.
If they survive, you can bring it to the next meeting.

title: punch
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Bring to a boil.
When this begins to boil, set off stove and add citric acid.
Stir well.
In a gallon jug, add orange juice.
Add mixture to jug and finish filling with water.
Stir and add ginger ale.

title: icebox bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling
water over 1 cup of bran; set aside to cool. Cream the shortening, sugar and beaten eggs.
Add cooled mixture, buttermilk, flour soda and salt.
Stir in 2 cups bran.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Will keep for a month or more.
Use as needed and bake at 375°.

title: drain opener
directions: Put the baking soda into the drain.
Follow with the vinegar (it will boil).
Wait for 5 minutes, then pour the boiling water into the drain.
Run the water for a minute or two.

title: tastee roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place into an oiled loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.
Let cool and slice.

title: brownies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs, then add rest.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Ovens may vary, so don't overbake.)

title: classic mud pie
directions: Chocolate Cookie Crust:
Combine over hot (not boiling) water, 1/2 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips and butter; stir until chocolate chips are melted and smooth.
Add wafer crumbs; stir until well blended.
Press into 9-inch pie pan.
Chill until firm (35 to 45 minutes).

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spoon into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Chill completely before serving.

title: stuffed spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Have large roasting pan with wire rack on bottom so ribs are not touching bottom of pan.
Crush rosemary; sprinkle both sides of ribs with salt and crushed rosemary.
Place one rack of ribs in pan with bones curving up.
Fill with stuffing.
Place second rack of ribs over stuffing with bones curving down.
Racks of ribs usually are wider at one end.
Fit ribs together as evenly as possible.
Place pan in oven at 400° until ribs are lightly browned.
Reduce oven temperature to 325° and bake until ribs are tender.
If ribs brown too much, lightly cover with aluminum foil.
Rosemary and salt will stay on ribs better if you rinse ribs in cold water first.

title: apricot cheese delight
directions: Chill jello combination, then add fruit and marshmallows. Pour into 2 (8 x 8-inch) or 1 (9 x 13-inch) cold water rinsed molds.
Chill.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Scoop out seeds from pumpkin; wash and clean.
Remove string as best as you can.
Let soak in salted water overnight (1 1/2 teaspoons salt per 2/3 cup water).
Drain well.
Then place seeds on shallow baking pan and place in oven at 300° for approximately 20 minutes or until golden.
Eat with or without removing the shells.

title: deep dish cheddar chicken
directions: Saute onion in 1/4 cup margarine. Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add chicken, cheese and peas; mix well.
Pour into dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Crust may also be added to top if you like.

title: chili
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil for 10 minutes.
Add beef. Brown and drain off grease. Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: salsa cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger/sausage and drain.
Combine hamburger, cheese cubes and salsa in crock-pot; heat until cheese is melted and all ingredients are heated through.
Serve with chips.

title: cry baby cookies(they cry for more!!)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, then molasses.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Bake at 350°
for 12 to 15 minutes. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Boil whole chicken or chicken breast until tender.
Dice chicken and set aside.
Combine chicken stock and pepper in large pan.
Bring to boil.
Make a roux with butter and flour.
When roux is smooth and thick, add broth.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer slowly for about 15 minutes.
Pour in bowls and top with crumbled tortilla chips.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and cinnamon; set aside.
Mix sugar, eggs, oil and orange juice until well blended.
Stir in flour mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in apples, nuts and coconut.
Pour into well floured and greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Put on cake plate.
Puncture top of cake with a fork. Pour hot Buttermilk Sauce over cake (recipe follows).
Let stand 1 hour.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Combine flour, sugar, egg and pineapple juice.
Put on heat to cook and stir until really thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and cheese.
Stir until melted, mixing really good.
Then add pineapple chunks and stir really good, mixing up.
Cover top with small marshmallows.
Put under broiler and brown lightly.
It's really good!

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Slice bananas and beat well into mashed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes. Remove and finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: pineapple whips
directions: Prepare a graham cracker crust in 8 x 8-inch pan and cool. Beat confectioners sugar, margarine and egg, adding a few drops of vanilla and food coloring.
Spread mixture over graham cracker crust in pan.
Whip the cream; fold in pineapple and spread on top of mixture in pan.
Refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: treasure filled brownie drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs and water.
Fold in apple pie filling.

title: cream cheese cutout cookies
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese with electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Beat well.
Stir together flour and baking powder.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, beating well.
Divide dough into thirds (about 2 cups each).
Cover and chill overnight.
Or place in plastic freezer bags and freeze up to 3 months.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Spray a 14-inch pizza pan with a nonfat cooking spray (or 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan).
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon corn meal into prepared pan.
Combine remaining 1/2 cup corn meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and liquid Butter Buds.
Stir with a fork until mixture forms a ball.
Press dough into prepared pan.
Shape edge to form rim.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: anne's spaghetti sauce
directions: Using large skillet or Dutch oven, brown meat and drain off fat
using
strainer.
Return
to
heat;
add
onion, bell pepper and
mushrooms
(with
liquid
from
can).
Cook until onions
are translucent, stirring often.
Add spaghetti sauce, catsup, salt and pepper.
If sauce is too thick, water may be added
until desired
consistency
is reached.
Simmer for at least 30
minutes to
blend flavors, longer if needed.
Serve over cooked thin spaghetti or vermicelli.

title: mom's red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with an electric mixer.
Spray 3 (9-inch) round cake pans with nonstick coating.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.
Cool layers in pans 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut crust off loaf of bread.
Cut each slice of bread into five fingers.
Electric knife makes this easier and neater.
Put fingers and crusts on cookie sheets in 200° oven for one hour. Crush crust into crumbs.
Dip bread fingers into mixture of oil and peanut butter.
Roll in crushed crumbs.
Place on wax paper to dry.
Store in a tight container.
They will stay crisp for a long time.
Makes 90 to 100 sticks.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and both sugars until fluffy.
Add egg and mix well.
Add oil and mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and oats; mix well.
Add nuts, cornflakes, coconut and vanilla; mix well.	Batter will be very stiff.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on cookie sheet for a few minutes before removing. When completely cooled, store in tightly closed container.	They will stay moist and keep beautifully for a week or more.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread coconut on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread pecans over coconut.
Mix cake according to box directions; pour on top of coconut and nuts.
Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Drop from spoon in dollops onto cake mix.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° until tester comes out clean between dollops.

title: salmon salad
directions: Drain
and flake salmon.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Keep refrigerated.
Good served with crackers.

title: microwave hollandaise
directions: In a glass 2-cup measure, melt butter in microwave. Add all remaining ingredients and cook uncovered for 1 minute, stirring every 15 seconds.
Cook another minute, if not thick enough.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients 1 to 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, depending on pan size.
Makes 4 mini, 3 small, 2 large or 1 Bundt. Test with toothpick for doneness.
Top will crack.

title: granola
directions: Bake until brown and crunchy at 350°.

title: chicken broccoli chowder
directions: Combine carrots, water, chicken broth, broccoli, onion and salt in a 4-quart saucepan or Dutch oven.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer about 10 minutes.
Bring to full rolling boil.
Gradually add oat flour, stirring constantly.
Stir in milk.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in cheese.
Cover; let stand 3 to 5 minutes before serving.
Makes about 4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Pour over snacks and toss to mix.
Heat in 250 degree oven for 1 hour.
Store in air-tight containers.

title: sugar twist bread
directions: Pour the scalded milk over the sugar, salt and shortening. Let stand until lukewarm.
Beat in flour, softened yeast, eggs, oats, currants or raisins.
Add flour.
Turn out and knead until smooth and satiny, 10 minutes.
Round dough into a ball; place in greased bowl.
Let rise until doubled in bulk, 1 hour.
Divide into 2 parts.
Roll in balls.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Roll each half into an 8 x 15-inch rectangle.

title: fruit turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix baking mix, sugar, margarine and milk until a soft dough forms.
Form dough into balls with hands. Lightly flour cutting board.
Knead dough 8 to 10 times.
Divide dough in half.
Flatten dough with palm of hand.
Roll into a rectangle, 12 x 8-inch.
Cut into six 4-inch squares.
Place squares on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place 1 tablespoon pie filling in corner of each square.
Fold opposite corner over.
Press edges with floured fork to seal.
Prick tops.
Repeat with remaining half of dough.
Bake until brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat remaining filling.
Spoon over warm turnovers or sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Turnovers may also be made by rolling each half of the dough in a circle.
Use a small dessert bowl as an outline for the turnovers.

title: corn relish
directions: Friendship is a priceless gift

title: mustard chicken
directions: Melt butter in covered pan.
Cover chicken breasts with the mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put chicken breasts and red potatoes, cut in half, into melted butter.
Cover for 1/2 hour and simmer, checking until well coked and browned.
Serve and enjoy!

title: aunt dean's chocolate pie
directions: In iron skillet, mix cocoa, sugar and flour.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks, then add butter.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring to keep from sticking.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with beaten egg whites and sugar.
Brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough over stoneware and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cream together cream cheese, sugar, orange juice and spread over cooled cookie dough.
Place fruit decoratively over cream cheese mixture.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Peel the potatoes and cut into quarter chunks. Boil until tender. Drain and pour one layer into a serving dish.
Place strips of cheese while hot, then sprinkle on bacon bits.
Repeat layers as necessary.

title: toffee bar crunch pie
directions: Spread dessert topping on bottom of crust.
Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and chopped toffee bars. Spoon into crust.

title: karl malone's hot crab salad jazz c b
directions: Toss together lettuce, eggs, cucumbers, green onions and raisins and set aside.
Melt butter and lemon juice and let simmer on low.
Heat in medium saucepan 24 ounces of Ranch dressing and cheese.
Heat until cheese has melted.
Heat crab flakes in microwave for 5 minutes.
Mix butter and lemon, Ranch dressing and melted cheese together; add crab flakes to lettuce mixture.
Just before serving, top with heated dressing and eat while warm.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and margarine in microwave for 2 minutes.
Mix them with the cereal in a bowl.
After the cereal is coated, dump it in a bag with the sugar.
Enjoy!

title: american goulash
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until done. Drain. Add soup and sauce. Add cooked noodles. Pour into 9 x 12 pan. Top with several strips of cheese. Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy tomato soup
directions: Heat tomato soup, soda and seasonings in one pan.
Heat milk in second pan.
Do not boil either liquid.
When each is hot, pour milk into juice and serve.
Do not reverse procedure because the soup will curdle.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray a Bundt pan with Pam.
Cut rolls into fourths; roll in sugar mixture.
Arrange anyway in pan; you can also add a spoonful of sugar mixture between every third or fourth row.
After pan is full, melt butter, pour over top layer of rolls.
Sprinkle more sugar mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water.
Cook beef and onions until brown.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce.
Cook until thickened.
Drain noodles.
Combine cream cheese and evaporated milk in warm saucepan until smooth.
Mix noodles and garlic salt.
Stir noodles and milk mixture together.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan: noodles, meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hubby pound cake
directions: Beat all the ingredients together for about 10 minutes at medium speed.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased loaf pan or 40 minutes in 13 x 9 inch pan.

title: blackberry crisp
directions: Combine blackberries and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Stir and place in greased 8-inch square pan.
Dot with butter.

title: 6 weeks muffins
directions: Mix cereal, flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add beaten eggs, Crisco and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 16 minutes.
Batter will be thick.
It keeps at least 6 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: hot dog n' potato bake
directions: Slice thin potatoes in a deep dish casserole dish (grease dish).
Place sliced onion on top (thin sliced).
Add oil, salt, pepper and garlic together.
Pour over potatoes and onions. Sprinkle with parsley and more garlic, if desired.
Roll bacon on hot dogs; place on top of casserole.
Add pepper.
Cover.
Bake until potatoes are done, 30 to 45 minutes.
Add cheese, if you desire, on top.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate chips for 2 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Add Eagle Brand milk stirring rapidly before mixture cools.
Add nuts (if desired) and refrigerate until firm.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine Bisquick, sausage and grated cheese until ball is formed (easier if sausage and cheese are at room temperature). Form into balls. Place on cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: low calorie peach fluff
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve softened gelatin in hot water.
Add salt, sugar, peaches and lemon juice.
Allow to jell slightly, then beat until mixture becomes fluffy and holds its shape.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Mold or pile lightly in sherbet glasses.
Makes 6 servings.
Only 50 calories each serving.
Can be sweetened with artificial sweetener.

title: sugar-free ice milk
directions: Mix pudding, Sweet 'N Low and Equal.
Add eggs and vanilla to mixture and combine.
Stir in the remaining milk.
Put in ice cream freezer and freeze.
Makes 22 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Beat egg whites until they are thick and fluffy.
Mix all of the other ingredients and then fold in the beaten whites.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: santa fe chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Season as desired.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done. Sprinkle Mozzarella on chicken (when done).
Top with salsa.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Measure and sift together the first 5 ingredients; set aside. Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and molasses. Stir in dry ingredients; blend well.
Form teaspoon size dough balls by rolling lightly between palms of hands.
Roll dough in granulated sugar to cover surface.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until tops are slightly rounded, crackly and lightly browned.

title: iced strawberry delight
directions: Beat strawberries, egg whites, lemon and sugar for 10 minutes on high speed.
Add cream; spread over crumbs in pan and top with rest of crumbs.
Freeze and keep frozen.

title: granny wedding cookies
directions: Mix ingredients with hands.
Shape into balls about the size of acorns.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Let cool about 5 minutes.
Roll in powderd sugar while still warm.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown ground beef and pan sausage.
Drain fat.
Add pepper, garlic powder and onion.
Cook until onion is soft.
Add soup, tomatoes and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
This may be frozen and then heated in the microwave.

title: confetti artichokes
directions: Place lemon juice in a large bowl and fill 3/4 with water. Clean artichokes.
Trim stems and bottom.
Cut about 1 1/2-inches off top.
Place in lemon water.
Reserve.
Partially cover each pot and cook over medium low heat for 1 hour (artichokes should be tender and pull apart easily).
Carefully place artichokes on a shallow platter.
Spoon liquids on top.
Sprinkle with parsley. Enjoy warm or cool.

title: poor man's pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until it starts to brown on top. Makes 2 pies.

title: wild rice pork chops
directions: Mix contents of box, soup and water in 2-quart casserole.
Add Chinese vegetables.
Arrange pork chops on top.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350° (do not cover). Serve with Chinese noodles and soy sauce.
(This is great for working women, these chops with a vegetable and salad is a good meal).
Yields 6 servings.
Time to prepare:
1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pasta vodka(entree)
directions: Bring butter, pepper and vodka to a boil and simmer 5 minutes. Add puree and milk or cream.
Add pasta.
Blend in cheese.
Bon Appetito!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar for 10 minutes.
In another bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt three times.
In a small pan, heat milk and butter to just below boiling.
Add sifted flour and milk mixture to beaten sugar and eggs.
Pour into a greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: crispy mallow nest(great for easter treats)
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter in 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir occasionally until marshmallows are melted and smooth.
Add chow mein noodles, mixing until noodles are thoroughly coated.
Drop noodle mixture by rounded tablespoonful onto greased cookie sheet, shaping with greased fingers to form a nest.
Place 3 peanut chocolate candies into center of each nest.
Let stand until firm.
Dust bottom of nest with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: Cook pasta; set aside.
Cook together chicken, potatoes and water.
When cooked about 10 minutes, add soup base more or less to suit taste.
Cook another 10 to 15 minutes.
Add pasta, cook together about 5 minutes.

title: raspberry apple sensation
directions: Place applesauce in pot and heat just to boiling.
Add gelatin.
Mix.
Remove from heat and stir in frozen raspberries. Place in 4-cup mold, or individual sherbet glasses.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: baked ham with strawberry sauce
directions: Score ham fat in several places and brown in skillet on both sides.
Place ham in baking dish.
Combine mustard, brown sugar and vinegar and sprinkle over ham.
Simmer strawberries and spices together in saucepan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over ham and bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add remaining ingredients.
Mold. Serves 7.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour and soda.
Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture alternately with 1/2 cup of the lemonade.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 7 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and brush lightly with remaining lemonade and sprinkle with sugar.

title: heavenly chocolate cheesecake
directions: Cream together cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla, until smooth.
Melt chocolate chips, cool and fold into cream cheese mixture.
Fold whipped topping into cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into pie crust and refrigerate until set, approximately 3 hours.

title: refrigerator mashed potatoes
directions: Cook peeled and diced potatoes in salted water until tender. Drain and mash until smooth. Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and butter. Beat until light and fluffy. Cool. Cover and place in refrigerator. May be used anytime within 2 weeks. To use, place desired amount in a greased casserole, dot with butter and bake at 350° about 30 minutes. Freezes well. 12 servings.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Mix all but the tortillas together.
Soften corn tortillas in hot oil.
Line a 13 x 11-inch pan with 6 corn tortillas.
Pour half of the mixture over tortillas.
Put remaining 6 tortillas and repeat.
Top with grated cheese and heat about 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: glazed pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper and dredge pork chops in flour.
Brown on both sides.
Remove and drain off drippings, reserving 1 tablespoon in skillet.
Return chops to skillet and top with apples and zucchini. Top with brown sugar and syrup.
Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Stir flour, sugar and salt together.
Cut in Crisco until crumbly.
Beat water, vinegar and egg in a small bowl.
Add to flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Divide dough into 4 or 5 patties.
Wrap each one in plastic wrap and wax paper. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
When ready to roll, flour both sides of patty and rolling pin.
Dough will always be flaky even if handled more than usual.
May be left in refrigerator for 3 days or can be frozen.
Must be thawed before use.
Makes 5 (9-inch) pie shells.

title: beef salami
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 2 rolls; wrap in foil and tie ends.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Do not remove foil. Place in pan, covered with water.
Boil 60 minutes.
Put on rack and punch holes in the foil to drain.
Rewrap and refrigerate. Serve when cooled.

title: b. l. t.  squares
directions: Separate each biscuit into 2 thinner halves.
Place biscuit halves in a well-greased casserole baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over biscuits evenly.
Bake at 375 degrees for 25 minutes.
Serve and enjoy!

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with chopped cabbage.
Mix hamburger with raw rice, egg, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle hamburger mixture over cabbage.
Place more chopped cabbage on top.
In saucepan heat Hunt's Italian sauce, garlic powder, brown sugar and lemon juice. Stir over low heat.
Pour over cabbage.
Poke holes to allow sauce through cabbage.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: grandma coffey's pumpkin squares
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until center is set.
Cool completely and cut into squares.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Beat the whipping cream until stiff, stands in peaks, and add the sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into graham cracker or vanilla wafer crusts.
Makes two 9-inch pies or 1 deep dish. Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: shrimp patties
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Make patties (not thin). Dredge in flour and deep fry.

title: oven barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions and margarine in pan.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion, green peppers, mushroom; drain off fat.
Add pizza sauce, pepper and salt to beef, then put in macaroni.
In casserole dish alternate layers of cheeses, pepperoni and meat mixture; ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. If dry add a little V-8 or tomato juice.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.
Form into ball and sprinkle with pecans.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended. Pour into crust.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed in ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: native american flat bread
directions: In a bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Melt butter and add it to the dry ingredients along with the milk.
Gradually knead into a ball and place in a greased bowl. Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Next, pinch into golf ball sized pieces and deep fry at 450°, turning once.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in pan. Heat until butter melts. Mix last 3 ingredients together. Mix well. Pour into a greased baking pan. Spoon hot fruit over top. Place in a 350° oven until done. Crust will come to top and get brown, about 30 minutes.

title: tuna touchdown
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
Add other ingredients and heat through.

title: creamy mushroom bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter shallow baking dish.
Arrange mushrooms in dish stemmed side down.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in small saucepan over low heat.
Increase heat to medium-high, blend in flour and cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour in half and half and bring to a boil.
Mix in stock and pepper and return to boil.
Pour sauce evenly over mushrooms.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and continue baking until cheese melts, 5 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Pour vegetables into 13 x 2 x 9-inch pan.
Mix soup, sour cream, onion,
cheese and water in separate bowl.
Pour over vegetables.
Melt butter.
Mix with crackers and stuffing mix. Sprinkle over dish.
Cook for 25 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: caramels
directions: Grease an oblong cake pan with butter.
Combine the sugar, Karo, vanilla, butter and 1 can of evaporated milk in a large, deep pan.
Bring to a boil and then add the second can of evaporated milk.
Continue to cook to hard ball stage, stirring constantly.
Pour into pan and let cool.
After cooled, cut into squares and wrap in waxed paper.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook meat until dry.
Drain.
Add onions, peppers, garlic, salt and chili powder.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients. Put cheese on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with half of the pastry; trim the edges of crust.
Combine sugar and salt.
Add blackberries, tossing to coat.
Pour berry mixture into pastry-lined pie plate.
Cut slits in top crust; place on top of filling.
Seal and flute edges.
To prevent overbrowning, cover edge of pie with foil.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes longer or until golden.
Cool on rack.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: oriental punch
directions: Combine sugar and 2 cups of water in saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add spices; cool.
Stir in juices to strained mixture. Add peppermint and enough food coloring to tint pale green.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Pour over crushed ice.
Garnish with mint leaves.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle rice evenly over bottom of pan.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice.

title: kid's carrots
directions: Combine carrots, raisins, butter, spices and salt in saucepan. Cook on medium heat for 10 minutes (until tender).
Stir in brown sugar until dissolved.

title: mini cheese cakes
directions: Beat all ingredients (except wafers and pie filling) together. Place vanilla wafer on bottom of cupcake paper.
Fill with filling.
Bake at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.
Cool and top with cherry pie filling or other filling.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and season; stir in soup, sauce and chilies. Simmer about 5 minutes.
Place tortillas on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan; pour hamburger mixture over tortillas.
Sprinkle onion and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly around edges.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add broccoli.
Stir until thawed.
Add Cheez Whiz, onion, soup and rice.
Pour into large baking dish and cover with croutons.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry-banana nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into a medium bowl.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg.
Add cranberries and orange rind.
Mix well.
Stir in milk and then banana.
Stir in dry ingredients and pecans just until blended. Pour into prepared pan. Bake until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 5 minutes.
Invert on wire rack and cool completely. Wrap in foil or wax paper.
Let stand overnight before slicing. The bread slices and tastes best if made one day ahead.

title: dried beef roll-ups
directions: Arrange dried beef in a single flat piece.
Spread cream cheese on top and roll like a jelly roll.
Fasten the roll with toothpicks.
Place in foil and refrigerate overnight.
Cut the roll into mini rolls (individual servings).
Arrange on party serving tray.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Cook juice, eggs, flour and sugar until thick.
Cool.
Cut pineapple into tidbit size.
Add marshmallows.
Drain fruit cocktail and add to pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour sauce over fruit mixture.
Stir.
Whip the cream until stiff and fold into fruit mixture.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and salt; stir.
Beat eggs with a fork, then add, stirring well.
Add oil.
Add flour; mix well.
Cover; let rise until double in size.
Turn out onto floured board; knead, then cut out rolls, putting 8 to a pan. This makes 2 to 2 1/2 pans.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough evenly over pizza pan and bake as directed.
When baking is completed, remove from oven and spread with cream cheese.
Arrange fruit on top.
Sprinkle with nuts. Drizzle glaze over the top and place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Some have meat but cannot eat;

title: chocolate cake
directions: Grease 2 (8-inch) round cake pans.
Flour lightly.
Combine chocolate, butter and water; microwave until melted.
Let cool. Sift flour, soda and salt into large bowl.
Beat eggs with sour cream until blended in medium sized bowl.
Beat in sugar and vanilla; stir in cooled chocolate mixture.
Beat into flour mixture 1/2 at a time just until smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Pour evenly into prepared pans and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched with fingertips. Cool on wire racks.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs. mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to butter mixture and mix thoroughly.
Stir in rolled oats.
Add nuts or raisins if desired. Drop by tsp. onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coconut jam tarts
directions: Line muffin tins with pie pastry.
Prick openings.
Bake at 425°
until light brown.
Fill centers with flavored jam.
Cover with a mixture of sugar, vanilla, Cool Whip and coconut.

title: cheese and chicken noodle bake
directions: Prepare noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Cook celery, onions and carrots until tender.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts. Combine noodles, cheese mixture, mushrooms, peppers, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 3-quart baking dish; top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: aunt hannah's sliced sweet potato pie
directions: Sprinkle flour, sugar and nutmeg on bottom of deep-dish crust.
Slice sweet potatoes, thin layer.
Sprinkle each layer with sugar, margarine, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Top with thin pie crust.
Make slits on top.
Pour water over potatoes until water comes out of slits.
Moisten crust with water.
Sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand in oven for 1 hour.

title: "people" puppy chow
directions: Pour powdered sugar into the doubled grocery bags; set aside. Empty the box of cereal into a large bowl; set aside.
In a saucepan, melt margarine, chips and peanut butter, stirring constantly.
When thoroughly melted, pout the mixture over the cereal and mix well to coat each pieces.
Immediately pour the cereal into the grocery bag and fold down twice.
Shake and turn the bag several times until cereal is coated with sugar.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: godfather meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs, tomato sauce, bread crumbs, garlic, salt and pepper with ground beef and mix well.
On waxed paper, flatten meat into rectangle.
Arrange ham on top of meat, leaving a 1-inch margin around edges.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over ham.
Carefully roll up meat, using paper to lift.
Seal edges and ends well. Place roll, seam side down, in dish.
Cook 1 hour and 15 minutes, then put cheese on top and cook 15 more minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Slice.
This is very good served with tossed lettuce and tomato salad and baked potatoes.

title: cherry trifle
directions: Cut up or break sponge cake into inch square pieces.
Set aside 1 cup Cool Whip to frost top.
Mix the remainder with enough Amaretto to taste, but not enough to thin the Cool Whip too much. Mix the cake with Cool Whip to coat the cake pieces.

title: cheese knishes
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, salt, flour and yeast
in warm water and sour cream.
Work into ball; let stand 2 hours and roll out.

title: apple pie in a jar
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Heat until bubbly.
Add lemon juice.
Pack apples in quart jars.
Pour hot syrup over apples and seal.
Water bath for 25 minutes, or pressure 10 minutes on 10 pounds pressure.

title: creamy chicken salad(microwave)
directions: Place 1 boneless chicken breast on a microwave-proof plate. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Cover with wax paper and cook on High for 3 to 5 minutes, turning over once.
Cool in freezer for 10 minutes.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix together.
Mixture will be rather chunky.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Brownies should be chewy.

title: oatmeal rolls(breakfast)
directions: In a saucepan, bring 2 cups water to boil. Add oatmeal and butter and simmer 1 minute. Add brown sugar and white sugar. Cool slightly. Heat remaining water to 120° to 130°. Add yeast. Add salt, oatmeal mixture, yeast and half of flour in a large bowl. Mix well. Add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough. Turn onto a floured board and knead 6 to 8 minutes or until smooth and elastic. Add additional flour if needed. Place dough in a greased bowl. Cover and let rise until doubled. Punch dough down; divide in half and shape each half into 12 balls. Place 1-inch apart in 2 greased 9 x 13 pans. Cover and let rise. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: yellow mexican rice(serves 4 to 6 people)
directions: *You can purchase these items at the international grocery store located in the West Side Plaza at 1400 West Main Street in Carbondale.

title: meringue turtledoves
directions: Line a large cookie sheet with wax paper foil.
In a small mixer bowl beat egg whites, vanilla, and cream of tartar till soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form. Put egg white mixture in a decorating bag fitted with a 1/2 inch round tip, filling bag half full.
Beginning at head end, squeeze bag gently, moving tip in a clockwise direction to form a question mark with egg white mixture.
For lower body, continue squeezing as you move tip about 2 1/2 inches to the right, back left, then right again, releasing pressure as you pull up tip.
repeat with remaining mixture.
Place miniature chocolate pieces on head for eye and beak.

title: bacon fat oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Make into small balls and flatten with a fork dipped in cold water.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes or until done.

title: steak elegante
directions: Cut steak in 6 pieces. Place in a greased 10-inch Dutch oven. Sprinkle
with
soup
mix.	Add mushrooms.	Blend soup, liquid from
mushrooms
and
grape
juice.
Pour
over steak. Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at medium heat (350° to 375°).

title: crock-pot roast beef
directions: Place beef in crock-pot.
Cover with other ingredients.
Cook on low 10 to 11 hours.
Thicken liquid with cornstarch to make gravy.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown burger in skillet; mix potatoes using directions on box. Cook veggies.
Layer ingredients in casserole dish, starting with 1/2 the potatoes, then burger.
Drain juice from veggies.
Add butter until melted.
Combine over burger.
Top with last of potatoes.
Delicious with shredded Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted and bubbles.

title: california marinade sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Use cubed beef round loin tip roast. Refrigerate 24 to 36 hours so meat will be tenderized.
Fill skewers alternating with green pepper strips, onions, mushrooms or any tidbits one chooses.
Broil over hot coals, brushing often with sauce.
Turn skewers often on grill.
Cooks rather quickly.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, eggs, crisco, oil and oranges. Drain the juice, using 1 tablespoon and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Use 9-inch cake pan (3 layers).

title: light low calorie cake
directions: Mix ingredients together until thoroughly moistened.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake as directed on the box.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix all ingredients together and blend well.
Spoon into ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve piping hot with crackers or party rye.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites very stiff.
Add sugar and continue beating until mixture stands in high peaks. Add nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased foil lined cookie sheet. Set in oven which has been heated to 350°.
Turn off oven and leave cookies in oven for 4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Under no circumstances open the oven door.
Makes 40 cookies. These are good served with coffee after a dinner party.

title: unbaked peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring sugars and Karo to boil and boil till sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and Special K. Drop by tsp. on waxed paper.

title: cranberry cooler
directions: Place ice cubes in
a large pitcher.
Add a few strawberries, then pour in cranberry juice cocktail.
Carefully pour lemon-lime beverage down the side of the pitcher.
Makes 6 1/2 cups.

title: hot crab sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients together very slowly until cheese is melted.
Serve over toasted English muffins or kaiser rolls with fresh fruit (seasonal).
This is a wonderful luncheon recipe. Serves 6 to 8.

title: green and gold potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and onions.
Layer in 2-quart microwaveable casserole.
Dot butter on top.
Then pour over the hot water mixed with the chicken bouillon.
Cover.
Microwave at High 17 to 20 minutes until potatoes are tender, stirring after 10 minutes.
Uncover casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley. Microwave at High 1/2 to 1 minute, uncovered, or until cheese melts.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: In large, thick 2-quart saucepan, brown meat until almost done.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Cook until slightly tender (don't overcook).
Add pork and beans, sugar and ketchup, stirring well after each.
Place on low heat for around 10 minutes.

title: bates avenue chicken
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour, covered, then 15 minutes more, uncovered.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Very good reheated.

title: flank broil
directions: Pierce steak with sharp fork all over.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Marinate steak in shallow pan overnight.
Broil in oven or on grill until done.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple together, till pudding is blended well, add marshmallows and
nuts. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: maple walnut pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, flour, maple syrup and butter. Beat in eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour mixture into prepared unbaked pie shell.
Place walnuts evenly on top, covering entire surface.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Mix sour cream (yogurt) with dry Italian dressing mix.
Spread sour cream on chicken breast and roll in cracker crumbs.
Place in buttered shallow baking dish (at least 9 1/2 x 13-inch).
Bake in 350° oven approximately 45 minutes.

title: aunt nancy's vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter and whip in flour to make a smooth paste. Stir in water. Saute ground chuck; drain and add meat to soup base. Add onions and celery. Add mixed vegetables, tomatoes, Accent, beef bouillon cubes, pepper, tomato soup, celery seed, oregano, cumin and salt. Simmer over medium heat for 45 minutes or more. Also works well in Crock Pot and/or freezes well.

title: lemon bread
directions: Add dry ingredients to liquid.
Beat 4 minutes (do not underbeat).
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in greased and floured pans (2 very large loaf pans or 3 to 4 small pans).

title: fruit smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and process until ice is finely chopped.
You can use any other fruits and juices you like!

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth and stir until sauce is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in half and half, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Toss chicken, mushrooms, olives and fettucini into sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw and squeeze all liquid from spinach.
Prepare Stove top according to directions.
Beat eggs.
Add all ingredients together and mix well.
Chill for 2 hours.
Roll by hand into bite size balls.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300° or until light brown.
Serve with a sweet and sour sauce.

title: lemon light drop cookies
directions: In a large bowl, cream the sugar, shortening and lemon peel until light and fluffy. Add eggs; beat well. Add yogurt and lemon extract; mix well. Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Blend well. Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle sugar or chopped nuts over tops and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned around edges. Remove from cookie sheets immediately and cool.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine the dry ingredients and mix into creamed mixture, next the mashed bananas.
Fold in nuts last.
Pour in greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
I use 4 pans, size 7 1/2 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/4-inch.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease two cookie pans.
Cream together oleo and sugars.
Beat in egg.
Add vanilla and water.
Fold in flour, then add chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased pans.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: baked chicken with wine
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Place cheese slices over each chicken breast.
Mix wine and soup.
Pour over chicken-cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing over chicken.
Drizzle butter over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: Combine and mix well the flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, baking powder and milk.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Pour batter mix in spreading it evenly.
Heat cherries or other fruit in 1 cup water and 1 cup sugar to boiling.
Pour cherries or other fruit mixture, while boiling hot, into baking dish over the batter. Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Slice and place 15 half Twinkies (cake side down) on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 cups milk with instant pudding and whip. Pour over Twinkies.
Place rest of sliced Twinkies on top of pudding, cake side up.
Pour Cool Whip over Twinkies and sprinkle with crumbled Heath bar.
Refrigerate to chill and serve.
Makes 15 servings.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and oil to a boil; then cool for syrup. Pour over vegetables.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: easy corned beef hash with cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage until tender (do not overcook).
Season to taste. In skillet, put onion and potatoes.
Add oil or oleo.
Simmer until onion and potatoes are done.
Open corned beef and slice over potatoes and onion.
Cover and simmer until meat falls apart. Stir occasionally.
Serve with the cabbage.

title: beef barley soup
directions: In soup pot, put the oil and get hot. Add the ground chuck; brown and drain. Stir in the flour, then add the water, beef bouillon, barley, tomatoes, onion, carrots, celery and salt and pepper. Cook about 1 hour until veggies are done.

title: refritos (refried beans)
directions: Bring to soak the beans at least 3 hours before you need them. Cover the pintos with water and let soak 1 1/2 hours or more. Cover with more water and cook, partially covered, until well done, usually 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Make sure you check their water level periodically while they cook.
When they are soft, drain off excess water and mash them well with a wooden pestle or a potato masher.

title: herb shaker(a flavorful salt substitute)
directions: Blend in blender on high speed 1 minute or until evenly ground.
Store in airtight	container.
Use
as an all-purpose or table top seasoning.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg yolks and milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat 2 egg whites until they form peaks.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar gradually and beat until glossy.
Spread on top of pie.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Soak the rump roast meat in mixture for 48 to 72 hours.
Brown both sides of rump roast in a little fat; take out and brown butter and flour.
Fill your roasting pan with about 2 cups of the vinegar juice and stew the meat in it slowly for about an hour or so. Before serving, thicken gravy with a teaspoon of flour and 1/4 cup cream.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: french bread chips
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°.
Using an electric knife, slice bread into very thin (1/8-inch thick) slices about 1-inch wide and 2 1/2 inches long.
Place slices in a large mixing bowl.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour butter mixture over slices; toss well to combine.
Spread on lightly greased baking sheets.
Stirring occasionally, bake 40 minutes or until golden brown and crisp.
Yields about 9 cups of chips.

title: wild goose
directions: You
put
everything
in
your slow cooker and cook all day. Cook
on 3 or 4.
When you're goose gets tender, you put your thickener in, made of flour and water.

title: crab imperial
directions: Make a white sauce of the first 6 ingredients.
Blanch, peel and mince finely green pepper.
Add Worcestershire sauce; stir in crabmeat.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with corn flake crumbs and butter.
Bake in 450° oven until brown.
Serves 4.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes or microwave for 5 to 7 minutes.
Use plain tortilla chips and dip into hot dip.

title: barbecue sauce(quantities to serve 100 people)
directions: Blend all ingredients well in blender or pan.
Yield: enough for 40 to 50 chicken halves.

title: chocolate nut meringues
directions: Beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar until foamy. Add sugar gradually; beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in vanilla, chocolate bits and nuts.
Put 1/2 teaspoon in mini paper cups, or drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 275° oven for 40 minutes.
Leave in oven to cool.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Mix together butter and sugar; add water and vanilla.
Add flour and chopped pecans to mixture and blend together. Roll into log shapes about the size of a little finger.
Bake at 275° until light tan (about 30 to 35 minutes).
Roll in powdered sugar. Cool. Makes about 60 cookies.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put all ingredients together except jello.
Put on stove and let come to a boil (about 2 minutes).
