Stir and take off stove and beat in jello.
Let cool until lukewarm.
Pour over strawberries, which have been cut in halves and sliced, then pour into pie shell.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Top with whipped cream.
(Can also use fresh peaches.)

title: rice mushroom bake
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter until tender.
In a bowl beat eggs and cream cheese until smooth, then stir in milk.
In a baking pan, combine mixtures and the rice.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes and then serve.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all dry ingredients well.
Add eggs, sugar and melted margarine.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli rice cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice in water until tender (2 cups of water per cup of rice).
Saute onion in oil.
Add cheese, milk, salt and soup; stir in onion and heat and stir until cheese is melted at low heat. Pour rice in greased casserole dish and add margarine.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain broccoli; stir into rice. Pour cheese mixture over broccoli and rice.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 8 to 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Put last 2 ingredients in spice bag.
Peel peaches.
Bring rest of ingredients to a boil.
Drop peaches in mixture and let boil gently for 15 minutes.
When tender, put in jars and seal.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients by gently folding together.
Chill and serve.
Tastes best when served fresh, but for jalapeno lovers, gets right after it's about 4 days old.
Eat with chips.

title: family fish loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients. Shape into loaf and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cover with a low-fat tartar sauce for the last 5 minutes. Serve with vegetables from your garden.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
(Makes 2 large pies.)
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until done.
(Cooks like a pecan pie.)

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to package instructions for pie filling but use only 2 cups of milk (instead of 4) and make certain that you beat it only 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line the bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with whole graham crackers (do not crush).
Spread with half of vanilla pudding and top with another layer of graham crackers.
Place remaining pudding on top and then another layer of graham crackers.
Gently spread the frosting on top.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Cut into squares and serve. Makes 12 or more servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain well. Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until bread crumbs brown.
Serves 8.

title: date nut pinwheels
directions: Combine dates, sugar and water. Cook until thick (10 minutes). Add nuts and cool. Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and remaining ingredients. Chill. Roll into 2 or 3 rolls. Spread with filling.
Chill.
Cut 1/4-inch thick.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat 425° oven.
Grease 12 muffin cups.
Combine 2 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Set aside.
Sift next 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in 1/3 cup brown sugar. Combine sweet potatoes, buttermilk, egg and oil.
Stir into dry mixture until just combined.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Scald milk and pour over oats.
Add sugars, salt, shortening and molasses.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in water with 1/2 teaspoon sugar and add to first ingredients.
Add enough flour to make a smooth, elastic dough.
Let rise once.
Put in greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° to 400° approximately 15 minutes until done, large loaves take a little longer.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Mix graham cracker crumbs and sugar; melt butter and pour into crumb mixture.
Press on bottom of spring-form pan (or use Keebler crust).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a large baking dish with butter and put chicken into it.
Mix soups and sour cream together; pour over chicken.
Put stuffing mix on top of soup.
Mix 1 stick butter and chicken broth; drizzle over top of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mom's gingerbread
directions: Mix buttermilk, molasses, egg, Wesson oil and sugar.
Add to flour, ginger, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda.
Mix together well and bake in a 9 x 10-inch iron skillet sprayed with Pam for 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.

title: spicy chicken noodles
directions: Boil
macaroni until soft.
In a large saucepan, simmer chicken,
soups,
tomato
sauce,
Ro-Tel and 1/2 box Velveeta. Add macaroni
and
put in a 9 x 13-inch casserole baking dish. Top with
other
half
of
Velveeta and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: raisin spice cookies
directions: Cream together honey, oil and egg or egg substitute. Add rice flour, potato flour, baking powder, baking soda and apple pie spice. Mix well. Stir in raisins. Drop onto lightly oiled baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato chowder
directions: Fry pork and brown vegetables in the fat.
Add boiling water to cover.
Cook until tender.
Add white sauce.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add other ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve over corn chips and garnish with grated cheese and chopped green onions.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken with celery, carrots and quartered onion. (This can be done the day before.) Debone the chicken and dice. Cook the spaghetti as directed on the package. Combine 1 1/2 cups broth and the diced chicken, diced onion, diced pepper, mushrooms, pimento, 2 cans mushroom soup and 1/2 the grated cheese. Mix well and put into large greased baking dish; sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake for 45 minutes at 350°. This will feed several.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, layer:

title: tasty little buggers
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain.
Melt Velveeta in microwave or as directed on package.
Add browned meat mixture to melted Velveeta.
Add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and hot pepper sauce.
Spread on party rye bread.
Can be frozen on a cookie sheet.
When hardened, place in plastic bags and use as needed.
Broil, if frozen, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: ginger beer
directions: In large stockpot, combine grated ginger with the boiling water and sugar. Stir well to mix, then cover and let stand at room temperature for about 2 days. Strain the ginger beer through clean muslin and store it in a glass drink bottle in the refrigerator until it is ready to drink. Serve with ice and stir in small amount of lime juice if you wish. Makes about 3 quarts.

title: mexican rice
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add rice, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Add mushrooms and sausage.
Place mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and cover mixture with 1 1/2 cups boiling beef stock or enough to cover rice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add to pineapple.
Next, add beaten egg. Pour into baking dish and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Meanwhile, cube the 5 slices of bread.
Melt the butter and pour over the bread cubes.
Put the bread cubes on the pineapple mixture, put back in the oven and bake for 1/2 hour at 400°.

title: quick and easy salmon patties
directions: Mix well and roll in meal.
Fry in deep fryer until done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix everything, except cheese, together.
Pour in casserole. Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes in preheated 325° oven.

title: green beans and asparagus
directions: Mix vegetables together with Cheddar cheese and soup.
Pour ingredients into an oblong dish. Top with enough cracker crumbs to cover the food in the casserole. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mashed potato bake
directions: Cook, drain and mash potatoes.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add potatoes and all other ingredients and mix together thoroughly.
If too thick, add a little milk and beat.
Put into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot top with butter.
Cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
You can prepare beforehand and keep in refrigerator until ready to bake.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Saute
chopped	onions	and
bell peppers in margarine. Beat eggs
with a fork.	Add these ingredients to ground meat. Add oatmeal, Worcestershire sauce, onion salt, celery salt and pepper; mix
well.

title: refrigerator rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and pineapple. Let stand 30 minutes.
Place in saucepan on stove.
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 12 minutes. Take from heat and stir in jello. Cool and place jam in jars. Store in refrigerator.

title: garbanzo guacamole dip
directions: In food processor bowl with metal blade or blender container, combine beans, lemon juice and garlic; process 10 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients except tomato.
Process 30 to 45 seconds or until well blended.
Cover.
Refrigerate to blend flavors. Garnish with chopped tomato.
Serve with tortilla chips or vegetable relishes.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: jaegerschnitzel (hunter's chop)
directions: Sprinkle flour on meat generously and brown on both sides in small amount of oil.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Simmer, covered, for 30 to 45 minutes.
Some water may be added to give sauce the desired consistency.
Jaegerschnitzel may be served with mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: punch
directions: Add all ingredients in a big bowl and mix together.
Chill and serve.

title: italian squash
directions: Place the olive oil and margarine in a frying pan on low heat. Add the squash, tomato and onion with the seasonings and spices. Cook in the covered frying pan on low heat for about 20 minutes or until soft.
Serve immediately.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and wet ingredients together. Fold over.
Good with steamed greens.

title: pine nut
directions: Sugar rim of 8 ounce coffee glass.
Add Amaretto and Kahlua. Fill with coffee.
Add whipped cream as garnish.

title: welch cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes approximately 8 dozen.

title: spaghetti and cabbage with cheese sauce
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender; drain.
Make sauce from margarine, flour, salt and milk.
Remove from heat; add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Alternate layers of cabbage and spaghetti in casserole dish.
Pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove cover last 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Drain liquid from can of yams.
Pour yams into large bowl. Add milk; add vanilla flavor.
Beat 2 eggs in separate dish.
Add sugar to large bowl.
Melt butter; pour into large bowl; add eggs to large bowl.
Mix all together.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: choco-nilla cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in greased oblong cake pan for 45 minutes.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Arrange apples in unbaked pie shell.
Mix the 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Mix flour with the 1/3 cup of sugar; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
If pie browns too quickly, cover edge with foil.
Cool and serve.

title: steak with garlic-wasabi sauce
directions: For Sauce:
Combine broths, 1/2 cup chopped onion, tomato, apple, carrot, celery, soy sauce, 3 chopped garlic cloves and tomato paste in pan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Strain into medium pan.
Boil until reduced to 1/2 cup.
Stir in wasabi mixture.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix 3 minutes. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Cool layers and split.

title: nook's potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion and carrots in water with seasonings until tender.
Mix flour with milk and add to the mixture and also the cheese.
Stir so cheese doesn't stick.
Do not boil after adding the milk.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Bring 3-quart saucepan of water to a boil.
Meanwhile, in a good processor, with the slicing blade, slice the unpeeled potatoes.
Add the potatoes and unpeeled garlic cloves to the boiling water and cook until the potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.

title: great grandmother lawrence's pumpkin pie filling
directions: Mix together and pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Lower oven to 325° and cook an additional 30 minutes.

title: mother's steam pudding
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and spices.
Add to creamed butter and molasses.
Add flour mixture and milk gradually and mix well.
Line a pan (Bundt will do) with cheesecloth.
Then add pudding mixture and put the pan into another larger pan which has water in it.
Bake at 350° for about 4 hours to steam the pudding.

title: salmon puffs
directions: Mix all together and fry by spoonfuls in hot fat for a few minutes or until it is a a little brown.

title: brascioule
directions: Brown round steak in shortening.
Liberally sprinkle one side of steak with remaining ingredients.
Roll steak up with seasoning side in and tie with string.
Put in a covered dish and refrigerate overnight.
Prepare sauce for cooking the next day.

title: baked ham loaf
directions: Combine ground ham, brown sugar, eggs and bread crumbs.
Mix to a slightly wet consistency.
Add more sugar or egg, if needed. Bake in a loaf pan, coated with butter or margarine.
Bake 45 minutes or until firm and slightly brown.
Slice and serve with Chef Mate or La Choy sweet and sour sauce.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook whole beets.
When done, peel and slice.
Set aside. Cook sugar, vinegar and salt over low heat until sugar dissolves. Pour syrup over beets and let stand overnight.
Place in containers and freeze.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Wrap breasts in beef and bacon.
Season with pepper.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over breasts. Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 3 hours.

title: cheese dip for raw vegetables
directions: Melt cheese and milk in a saucepan until smooth.
Add the other remaining ingredients. Stir thoroughly.
Remove from heat and chill.
Serve dip with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: white cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Combine dry ingredients; add together with water.
Fold in egg whites and bake at 350° until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix syrup for pineapple and oranges with pudding and Tang. Pour over fruit and nuts.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: granny's jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add jam to egg yolks and mix together.
Add butter and sugar mixture.
Then mix all dry ingredients together.
With sour milk, fold in beaten egg whites and vanilla.
Blend all together.
Place in 3 round lined, floured cake pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake in preheated oven for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash the sweet potatoes.
Add butter, sugar, milk, salt and lemon rind. Scoop up 1/4 cup of mixture.
Put a marshmallow in the center.
Cover with more potatoes and shape into balls. Roll in crushed corn flakes or coconut.
Place in buttered baking dish and cover with aluminum foil.
Freeze. When ready to serve, bake until marshmallows begin to ooze, about 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put chicken breasts in bottom of baking dish.
Pour melted butter over the chicken breasts.
Crumble 3 or 4 crackers over chicken breasts.
Heat cream of mushroom soup and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding with lemon sauce
directions: Mix milk and bread crumbs together.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients and add to the milk and bread mixture.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and
put into a pan of water in the oven.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: cream cheese braids
directions: Scald sour cream.
Stir in next 3 ingredients. Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast in water and stir.
Add to sour cream mixture.
Add eggs and flour.
Mix well. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
Divide dough into 4 pieces.
Roll each piece into rectangle (8 x 12-inch).
Mix cream cheese, sugar, salt, vanilla, lemon and 1 egg until smooth.
Spread each rectangle with filling.
Roll up like jelly roll.
Place on greased sheet.
Cut each roll, making cut alternating side to side.
Allow to rise double in bulk, 2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Spread with glaze.

title: best pound cake
directions: Beat
egg
whites
at room temperature, adding 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1 cup sugar.
Set aside.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, garlic and celery in large saucepan until onion is clear; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles and top with Parmesan cheese.

title: apple-cinnamon bake
directions: Dip biscuits in butter, then in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Arrange in round pan with cinnamon sugar side up.
Place 1 apple slice between each biscuit and between each biscuit and side of pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spicy slithering snakes(kid's favorites)
directions: Separate rolls and stretch slightly.
Place peach slice on wide end and roll up to resemble a snake.
Pull dough to make snake longer, if desired.
Place on baking sheet.
Press two raisin "eyes" into dough and sprinkle lightly with cinnamon. Bake according to package directions until dark golden brown.
Makes 8 snakes.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add flour, eggs and cinnamon, mixing well.
Add apples.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Whip eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla, milk, margarine and coconut.
Pour in pie shell and bake until golden brown, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet and spicy salsa
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least an hour before serving.

title: chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Melt chips on top of double boiler over hot, not boiling water.
Stir in milk.
Cook until smooth.
Beat egg yolks with sugar and salt.
Add hot chocolate mixture gradually to egg yolks.
Return to double boiler and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add softened gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Cool until almost set.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill until firm.
To serve, top with sweetened whipped cream.

title: cheesy spinach pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles. Spread rectangles with cheese to 1/4 inch of edges, top with ham and spinach.
Starting at shortest side roll up each rectangle, press edges to seal.
Cut each roll into 6 slices.

title: cheeseburger lasagna pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook lasagna macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
Meanwhile, saute ground beef and onion until meat is browned.
Drain excess fat.
Add 3/4 of the can of lasagna sauce from package and grated cheese from package. Mix well.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch baking dish with Pam no stick cooking spray.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Beat eggs.
Add buttermilk and oil.
Mix dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Mix, but do not overmix (a few small lumps are okay).
Let stand 15 minutes.
Set baker to a little hotter than medium setting.
Spray baker with Pam first time.
Pour about 1/3 cup batter in center of baker.
Bake until brown. Makes 7 to 8 waffles.

title: crisp asparagus roll-ups
directions: Roll bread slices flat; brush each with melted butter.
Place 1 or 2 asparagus spears on bread; roll up.
Brush again with melted butter and roll in Parmesan cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven until crisp and lightly browned.
Delicious served with a salad, lunch or afternoon tea.
Will serve about 25.

title: meatball nuggets
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze firm.
Wrap in foil or plastic bag and return to freezer.
Before serving, place frozen meatballs on a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Keep warm in chafing dish.
Makes 5 dozen.
Enjoy!

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Grease some cookie sheets.
Combine the butter and 3/4 cup sugar; beat until thoroughly blended.
Add the egg, egg yolk and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir together the flour, baking soda, salt and nutmeg; add to the first mixture, mixing until thoroughly blended.
Roll pieces of the dough between the palms of your hands into 1 inch balls.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup sugar with the cinnamon.
Roll each ball in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni or small spaghetti and cool.
Add cauliflower, cut in chunks.
Add broccoli, cut in pieces.
You can put in onions.
Pour 1 bottle Wish-Bone Italian dressing over and mix. Pepper to taste (optional).
Cover and chill at least an hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain.
Stir in soup, sour cream, 1/2 margarine, poultry seasoning and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix crackers and rest of margarine.
Sprinkle over squash and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and cottage cheese; add other ingredients and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line 9 x 11 pan with vanilla wafers on bottom and sides. Beat pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Alternate pudding and vanilla wafers, ending with wafers on top.
Spread icing on top and refrigerate overnight.

title: five flavored cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add extracts and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to mixture alternately with milk.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until done.

title: green pea soup
directions: Wash peas. Cover with water and soak 2 hours. Drain and rinse. Place in saucepan with chicken broth. Bring to simmering point over low heat. Cover and cook for about 1 1/2 hours until peas are tender.
Saute onions, carrots and celery in butter for 5 minutes. Add to peas. Add sugar, mint, salt and pepper. Cook for 20 minutes. Puree the soup in blender.
Strain into pan. Add cream and heat 2 minutes.
Fry croutons in butter or oil.
Garnish soup.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix beef, Cheddar cheese, onion and jalapeno peppers.
Mix meal, eggs, milk, soda, salt, creamed corn and bacon grease. Grease pan.
Sprinkle with corn meal.
Pour 1/2 of meal mix, then all of meat.
Pour the rest of meal mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cut off corn to put in freezer
directions: Mix well and freeze in freezer boxes.

title: linguine with broccoli and scallops
directions: Blanch broccoli in boiling salted water.
Refresh with cold water and set aside.
Cook linguine in unsalted water.
Drain and toss with 1/4 cup butter.
Set aside.
Heat remaining 1/2 cup butter in skillet and saute garlic.
Add scallops, salt and pepper.
Saute 3 minutes or until scallops are opaque.
Add broccoli and heat one minute.
Add pasta and heat through.
Add cheese and serve.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Make a thick white sauce with the butter, flour and milk.
Add mustard, cayenne pepper, salt and pepper. Stir into the hot white sauce the shredded cheese.
Remove from heat; stir in egg yolks, well beaten.
Beat until stiff 3 egg whites with cream of tartar. Fold in the cheese mixture.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole (7 1/2-inch).
Make a groove 1 inch from the edge with a knife blade.
Set casserole in a pan of water 1 inch deep. Bake until puffed and golden brown, in a moderate oven (350°) about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cornish pasties
directions: Boil chicken until well done in 3-quart pan.
Cool, refrigerate and remove fat from top of broth.
When ready to make potpie, remove skin and fat from chicken pieces and pick meat from bones.
Return meat to broth.
Add several chicken bouillon cubes and bring broth to full boil.
While broth is heating, make potpie.

title: barbecued drumsticks
directions: In quart glass combine water, onion, tomato paste, vinegar, garlic, chili powder, mustard and pepper until well blended. Cover with plastic wrap; microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir and microwave uncovered 5 minutes longer.
Pour half the mixture over bottom of 12 x 8-inch microwave-safe dish.
Place drumsticks in dish and pour remaining sauce over them.
Cover with waxed paper. Microwave at Medium-high 12 minutes per pound.
Turn drumsticks often.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix well and spoon onto a cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: stuffed venison burgers
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Combine milk and meat.
Divide into five patty.
On wax paper, pat each to a 6-inch circle.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each patty.
Draw meat over stuffing and seal.
Place in shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts and debone.
Cook and drain broccoli. Place broccoli in buttered casserole dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, milk and lemon juice together. Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine boiled squash with soup, carrots, sour cream and onion.
Pour 1/2 cup stuffing to mix with melted butter, then stir into baking dish.
Pour 3/4 of stuffing into mixture, then spread around dish evenly.
Pour remaining stuffing on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Mmm Mmm Good!

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve water, yeast and salt in a large mixing bowl.

title: meat loaf
directions: Pour over meat loaf and continue baking for 1 1/2 hours longer, basting occasionally.

title: pumpkin supreme
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs,
1 cup sugar and butter. Mix well.
Press into a 13 x
x
2-inch baking dish and set aside.

title: fritto misto(mixed fish fry)
directions: Wash all the fish and dry on paper towels.
Heat a frying pan. When hot, add oil.
Dip each piece of fish into egg mixture (beat egg with few drops of water and salt and pepper).
Then dip into flour mixture (flour and bread crumbs) and drop into hot oil.
Fry one type of fish at a time if you have a lot.
When fish pieces are golden brown on both sides, lift with spatula and drain on paper towels.
When all the fish is fried and drained, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange on a heated serving platter and garnish with lemon wedges.
Serve with green salad, tossed with olive oil and lemon dressing.

title: chunky chicken gazpacho salad
directions: Mix the V-8 juice and Italian dressing together; set aside. Cut tomatoes into 1-inch pieces, enough to make 3 cups.
Cut cucumber into 1-inch pieces to make 1 3/4 cups.
Cut bell pepper into 1-inch pieces to make 1 1/2 cups.
In a large bowl, combine cut up chicken and vegetables.
Add salad dressing.
Toss well to coat chicken and vegetables.
Arrange lettuce leaves on a large serving platter.
Place salad on top.
Serve.
Serves 4.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine soups, onion and peppers.
Place half the chips in bottom of baking dish.
Add chicken to soups and onion.
Pour half of this mixture over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat with chips and chicken mixture and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Top with more cheese after you remove from oven.
Sometimes you may need to add chicken broth to keep from being dry.

title: white chili
directions: Saute in oil the onion, garlic and cumin until tender.
Into a 2 1/2-quart casserole, combine onion mixture with chicken, beans, corn, chilies and bouillon.
Add 1 1/2 cups water.
Cover.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Stir in hot pepper sauce and top with cheese.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Cut 2 slices of bread across in an X, making 8 small triangles.
Butter lightly.
Butter the remaining bread, then cut into neat cubes.
You should have about 4 cups.
Place a layer of bread cubes in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat with cubes, then again cheese.
You should have enough for 2 or 3 layers.

title: chinese ginger ribs
directions: Put ribs in pot and cover with water; add the bay leaf, cloves and onion.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 40 minutes.
Have sauce ready to dip ribs in while they are hot.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water for hard ball stage.
Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until stiff.
Very slowly add syrup mixture to egg white and 1 teaspoon flavoring and color. Beat until it holds shape.
Put on waxed paper by spoonfuls.

title: slush punch
directions: Boil sugar and water together until clear.
Mix together in large container and freeze.
Stir occasionally.
Serves about 30 people.

title: crusty-topped noodle kugel
directions: Beat together cream cheese and margarine.
Add sugar; mix well.
Blend in eggs.
Stir in next four ingredients.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Remove fat from chicken.
Cut chicken into 3/4-inch pieces. Heat 1-inch oil in deep fryer or 4-quart Dutch oven to 360°.
Beat flour, 1/4 cup cornstarch, 1/2 cup cold water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the egg in a large bowl with hand mixer until smooth.
Stir chicken into batter until well coated.
Add chicken pieces to oil one at a time.
Fry about 20 pieces at a time for about 5 minutes, turning 2 or 3 times, until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels; keep warm.
Add enough water to reserved pineapple syrup to measure 1 cup.
Heat syrup mixture, brown sugar, vinegar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, soy sauce, carrots and garlic to boiling in a Dutch oven; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 6 minutes until carrots are crisp-tender.
Mix 2 tablespoons cornstarch and 2 tablespoons cold water; stir into sauce.
Add chicken, pineapple and bell pepper. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute. Serve with rice.

title: smiley face pancakes
directions: You also need new kids paintbrushes.

title: "old army chili, 1896
directions: Place steaks into a Dutch oven.
Add water, 3 garlic cloves, peppercorns and salt.
Heat until water comes to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until meat is well done (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
When meat is done, remove liquid and cool.
When cool enough to handle, pull into shreds with fingers or the tines of 2 forks.
Return the meat to the cooking water.

title: green beans like mom canned
directions: Render down the bacon in a heavy saucepan.
When the drippings are liquid, add carefully the 2 cans of beans.
Watch out for splatter!!
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Onion can be added at this time.
Cover with a tight lid and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Do not add water.
Use only the liquid from the green bean can to cook.
Keep watch so that the liquids don't boil away. Stir often and reduce heat if the liquid amount gets too low before cooking time has elapsed.

title: golden champagne punch
directions: In covered blender at high speed, blend crushed pineapple with its liquid, one can at a time, 15 to 20 seconds until thick.
In chilled container stir blended pineapple, undiluted lemonade and sugar according to directions on can.
Stir in club soda and champagne.
Add ice and serve at once.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Cook the pasta al dente.
Cut ham into small pieces; brown in frying pan with a small amount of olive oil.
Make sure the heavy whipping cream and eggs are at room temperature.
Beat eggs until smooth in a large mixing bowl.
Mix all the ingredients together. Serve while hot.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburger until brown; drain.
Mix macaroni, pizza sauce and hamburger together.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Spread Mozzarella cheese over mixture.
Place sliced pepperoni on top of cheese. Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: easy fudge
directions: Heat chocolate and milk over low heat, stirring, until chocolate is melted; remove from heat and add vanilla and salt. Stir in nuts; spread in buttered 8 x 4-inch pan.
Chill until firm, then cut into 18 squares.
I usually double recipe and spread in 8-inch square pan.

title: nutty chocolate cookies
directions: In small saucepan, melt 1 cup of the chocolate over low heat; cool.
In small mixing bowl, cream together sugar and butter; add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in melted chocolate. Thoroughly stir together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in nuts and remaining chocolate pieces.
Drop dough from a teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: heath candy
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients in heavy medium size pan.
Bring to boil; cook until sugar melts over medium heat,.
Turn heat up slightly; let boil until mixture turns golden brown.
Do not burn. Boil for about 5 minutes.
Pour into prepared pan (I use cake pan, foiled lined and buttered well).
Use wooden spoon.
Top with melted chocolate bits.
Cool; break up like brittle.

title: sweet potatoes with poached cranberries
directions: Combine sugar, water and cinnamon.
Stick in a deep saucepan. Bring the mixture to a boil.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add cranberries and cook, uncovered, at a low boil, stirring often for about 5 minutes or until the berries have popped open but still retain their shape.
Remove the cinnamon stick and set the poached berries aside to cool slightly.

title: lemon chess squares
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and preheat oven to 350°.
Mix first 3 ingredients and press into bottom of baking pan.
Beat together last 4 ingredients until smooth.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly brown on top.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, white sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup butter and pecans.
Sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Slice cucumber thin.
Slice onion very thin .
Combine all other ingredients and pour over cucumber and onion.
Cover and chill about 15 minutes before serving.
This dressing may be used on cole slaw or other salad veggies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Roll one piece of bacon around each chicken breast and secure with a toothpick.
Line casserole dish with dried beef.
Place chicken rolls in dish.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for 3 hours.

title: corn pudding delight
directions: Combine whole kernel corn, cream-style corn, eggs, sugar, corn bread mix, salt and dry mustard; mix well.
Add onion, milk and melted butter.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole. Bake at 400° over 1 hour, stirring once.

title: zucchini-summer squash appetizer or vegetable dish
directions: Slice the zucchini and summer squash.
Boil until just tender; drain.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Top with sharp Cheddar cheese.
Wrap in aluminum foil and place on outdoor grill until cheese melts.

title: cauliflower and green pea salad
directions: Cook green peas using package directions for 2 minutes or until just tender; drain.
Cool.
Combine mayonnaise, onion, milk, salt and pepper in large bowl; mix well.
Add green peas, cauliflower and celery; toss lightly to mix.
Chill for several hours to overnight.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Place yeast in the water and let stand for 5 minutes.
In large bowl stir together the flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and sugar.
By hand or pastry blender, cut the shortening into mixture. Add the dissolved yeast and the buttermilk; mix together well. Refrigerate in tightly closed bag.
The dough will keep for 5 days.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cooking oil and buttermilk. Sift together self-rising flour, sugar and soda.
Add to liquid and mix well.
Cover with Saran Wrap and store in refrigerator. Will keep up to 3 weeks.
Take out amount needed and knead on floured board.
No need to let rise.
Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes or until brown.

title: parson's punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Garnish with sprig of mint and cherries.
Serves 2.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Combine juice, oleo and enough water to make 3/4 cup, then add beaten egg.
Pour this mixture into dry ingredients, mixing just to dampen.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Bake in greased pans, spread so higher on sides, at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Remove from pan and drain.
Return to pan and cover with water 1 inch above beef.
Mix all ingredients.
Add to meat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: crybaby cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Yield: 100 cookies.

title: beef salami
directions: Mix
ingredients well.	Place in refrigerator, covered. Next day, knead well.
Do this for 3 days.
On 5th day, knead. Form into 4
rolls.
Place on broiler tray and bake 8 hours at 160° temperature.
Salami forms own casing.

title: pasta with spring vegetables
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet over high heat.
Add the garlic, shallots and zucchini.
Reduce heat to medium and stir to coat all ingredients thoroughly with the olive oil.
Saute, stirring from time to time, until the zucchini is cooked, for about 5 minutes.
Add broccoli (if desired), cauliflower, snow peas and fresh herbs.
Add the broth or water; cover the pan and steam the vegetables briefly, until they are heated through.
In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook linguini according to package directions until tender.
Drain pasta and place in a heated bowl.
Add steamed vegetables, Parmesan, salt and pepper. Toss to coat evenly and serve at once.
Makes 4 entree or 6 to 8 appetizer servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in blender.
Refrigerate overnight. Next day, add 3 cups marshmallows, 1 carton Cool Whip and 1/2 cup nuts.

title: six week muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in extra large bowl.
Add Raisin Bran, milk, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Store in covered bowl in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
Grease and flour muffin pans and fill 2/3 full.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Good for office breaks and breakfast.

title: caramel icing
directions: Melt in saucepan the butter.
Remove from heat.
Blend 1 1/2 tablespoons flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute; if mix curdles, do not be alarmed.
Stir in 1/2 cup brown sugar, packed in cup.
Remove from heat.
Stir in confectioners sugar.
Set saucepan in cold water.
Beat until ready to spread.
Add vanilla and pecans.

title: potato skins
directions: Rub potatoes well with drippings (this keeps them soft).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cut lengthwise into quarters.
Scoop out potato, leaving 1/4-inch next to the skin.
Brush with melted oleo.
Sprinkle with Lawry's seasoned salt, cheese and bacon. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Use remainder of potato for potato salad.

title: low-fat saucy turkey loaf
directions: Combine turkey, breadcrumbs, onion, salt, pepper and egg substitute in a large bowl; stir well.
Shape turkey mixture into a loaf.
Place turkey loaf on rack of a broiler pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Combine brown sugar, catsup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce in a small bowl, stirring well.
Pour brown sugar mixture over turkey loaf, and bake an additional 10 minutes or until meat is no longer pink. Fat:
4.4 grams per serving.
Cholesterol:
47 mg.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute celery in butter until tender.
Remove from the heat.
Add the next 8 ingredients.
Put in a greased dish.
Crush 1/2 cup cornflakes.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter.
Put the cornflakes over the mixture.
Put the melted margarine over the cornflakes.
May add sliced almonds (optional).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: In 2 1/2-quart casserole, microcook broccoli, onion and water covered until vegetables are tender, about 11 minutes.
Stir twice to break up broccoli.
Blend in soup, cheese and milk.
Stir in ham, uncooked rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Microcook covered 10 to 11 minutes, stirring twice.
Let stand covered 5 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: apple squares
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, then apples and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares.
(These freeze very well.)

title: peggy's swedish meatballs
directions: Grind together the beef, veal and pork twice.
Soak the bread crumbs in cream for 5 minutes.
Mix meats, crumb mixture, onion, egg, parsley, salt, pepper, ginger and nutmeg.
Beat 5 minutes at medium speed.
Shape into small balls.
Brown in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Prepare Swedish Meatball Gravy.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Place 9 x 13 dish with butter in 350° oven. Mix flour, sugar and milk together with whisk. After butter is melted, pour in flour, sugar and milk mixture then spoon in pie filling. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (until crust is golden brown).

title: crustless crabmeat quiche
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Beat eggs, Bisquick, butter, milk, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate, then sprinkle crabmeat, cheese and bacon on top (press down gently).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in skillet; cook until thick.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl.
Cook over low heat; don't boil. Stir constantly.
Pour into cooked pie shell.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground chuck with onions and peppers.
Drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken with onion flakes, celery seed, salt and pepper for 1 hour.
Pick from bone and place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix undiluted soup with sour cream and pour over chicken. Mix stuffing according to package.
Place stuffing over top of chicken and soup and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wassail bowl punch
directions: Mix juices.
Tie cloves and cinnamon together in a bag.
Add sugar and spice bag.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Cover and simmer one hour.
May be decorated with orange and lemon slices studded with cloves.

title: prune or carrot cake glaze
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together in a large saucepan. Cook until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Pour over cake while cake is still warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package instructions and drain. Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish except bread crumbs.
Put buttered crumbs on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tropical cake
directions: Mix all cake ingredients together, bake in 3 prepared pans (8 or 9-inch) for 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool well.

title: super-duper doughnuts(the spice is nice!)
directions: In a deep-fryer, heat oil to 375°F (190°C).
In a medium bowl, combine Quick Mix, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend well. In a small bowl, mix together vanilla, egg and milk or water.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir until well-blended.
On a lightly floured surface, knead dough about 10 minutes.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with a floured doughnut cutter.
Fry in hot oil about 1 minute on each side, until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
While doughnuts cool slightly, prepare Vanilla Glaze. Dip warm doughnuts in glaze.
Makes about 12 doughnuts.

title: shell macaroni and shrimp salad
directions: Cook shells per package directions.
Cool.
Blend mayonnaise and mustard until smooth.
Combine with remaining ingredients and macaroni.
Toss until nicely coated with dressing.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Garnish with hard-boiled eggs, pimento peppers and paprika, as desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Line bottom of six 5 1/2 x 3 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans with wax paper or grease.

title: fluffy potato rolls
directions: Place potato in a medium saucepan.
Add enough water to cover potato.
Cook over high heat until tender, about 20 minutes. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup potato water.
Mash potato to yield 1 cup. Scald the milk in a small saucepan over med-hi heat.
Remove from the heat.
Let stand to cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved. Mix reserved potato water, shortening, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Add milk mixture, mashed potato and egg whites. Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Store, tightly covered, in refrigerator for 2 hours. Preheat the oven to 350°. Roll dough on a floured surface to 1/2 inch thickness.
Cut with a floured 2 inch cutter.
Arrange 2 inches apart on baking sheets. Let rolls rise in a warm place until double in size, about 30 minutes.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli casserole #1
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup crackers.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with rest of cheese and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, sour cream, salt, pepper, green chilies and cooked sausage.
Add cheese.
Mix well.
Butter trimmed bread slices.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan, buttered side down.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Best if made night before.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pink cherry chiffon(extremely low-fat)
directions: Soften cream cheese (cream cheese that is fat-free will not be as creamy as regular cream cheese).
Beat cream cheese and milk with electric mixer until smooth.
Add pudding mix and continue to beat.
Add more milk if necessary to make smooth.
(This will take several minutes.)
Add lemon juice and continue to beat.
Fold in Cool Whip and pineapple.
By hand add cherry pie filling and pecans or dates.
(Dates are much lower in fat.)
Mix well.
Add a few drops of red food coloring if desired.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and refrigerate several hours.

title: turkey rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, heat soup, milk, turkey, cheese and broccoli.
Stir often, add seasonings.
Spray a baking dish with non-stick oil.
Spoon rice into dish; pour sauce over and gently mix together.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs and pumpkin.
Blend in sugar and spices.
Add milk and mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out smooth.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine vinegar, beet liquid, cornstarch, salt and sugar. Cook over medium heat until clear and thickened, stirring constantly.
Add butter and sliced, cooked beets.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: mounds bars(large recipe)
directions: Using wooden spoon work all ingredients (except almonds, chocolate and paraffin) together.
It will be very stiff.
Flatten in a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, cut into 1-inch squares and dip in chocolate.

title: tuna sandwich supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in hamburger buns.
Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cook Pet milk, margarine and sugar for about 5 minutes.
Add coconut.

title: coconut chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, butter and confectioners sugar.
Blend in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press evenly into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over hot layer.
Bake for 20 minutes longer.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil hen until tender. Debone the hen. Put aside. Mix the ingredients until blended well. Make dough stiff. Roll out on floured surface until thin. Cut and drop in hot broth. Keep broth boiling until all dumplings have been dropped in. Put the deboned hen back in the pot with the dumplings. Turn fire down and put the lid on. Cook until done.

title: sour cream icing
directions: Stir all ingredients together to make icing of drizzling consistency.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs and beat.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven approximately 45 minutes (until middle of pie looks solid).

title: biscuit mix
directions: Make a cup or 2 cups mix at a time.
Just add water.
Makes muffins, pancakes, biscuits, etc.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Blend all, topping with chips.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together in bowl.
Add milk, eggs, corn and oil, mixing well.
Brown meat, onion and peppers and drain.
Add ground meat mixture to cornbread mix.
Then add grated cheese and mix well.
Pour into pan (9 x 13-inch).
Place into 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: boiled custard(at least 160 years old)
directions: Mix cornstarch, salt and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add milk.
Cook in double boiler, stirring often.
Be careful not to overcook.
When mixture coats spoon, remove from heat; cool.
Add flavoring.
Dried orange rind, grated, may be used.

title: crabbies
directions: Split English muffins in half and set aside.
Cream together all ingredients.
Spread over English muffins.
Place muffins on cookie sheet and put into freezer for 2 hours.
Remove from freezer and place on broiler.
Cook until top browns.
Cut into quarters and serve hot.
Great appetizer.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in 1 cup water.
Place in top double boiler and add cut up marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows are almost dissolved.
Then add pineapple after this is removed from heat.
Blend cream cheese and add to mixture.
Store in refrigerator until cool.
When cold, fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pan and let stand until firm.
Dissolve cherry jello in 2 cups water.
Cool, but do not allow to jell.
Pour over other mixture and let set.

title: cranberry raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Stir in sherbet and lemon juice. Chill, if necessary, until mixture mounds. Mash cranberry sauce slightly with fork; fold into jello mixture.
May be poured into a mold.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in oil and eggs.
Mix in chopped apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: sausage and mushroom pizza
directions: Cook sausage meat until brown and crumbly. Add onion and continue cooking for 5 minutes over moderate heat. Add tomato sauce, mushrooms, tomato paste, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer until thick, about 10 minutes.

title: scalloped corn and oysters
directions: Roll enough crackers to make mixture thick.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake until firm.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Smash strawberries with a potato masher if using whole strawberries.
Mix strawberries, lemonade, water and sugar together.
Pour into a plastic container such as an ice cream bucket.
Freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw mixture for approx. 1 hour or until mixture can be scooped out and placed in glasses. Pour lemon-lime soda over all to serve.
Garnish with a fresh strawberry and mint sprig or serve with swizzle sticks.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend all dry ingredients with shortening and oil.
Add beaten egg, vinegar and water.
Mix.
Roll into crust and shape in pie pan.
Will make 3 or 4 crusts.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: banana nut pancakes
directions: Puree bananas in blender.
In medium bowl, combine bananas, egg, milk and oil.
In large bowl, combine pancake mix, nuts and cinnamon.
Stir in banana mixture until moistened.
Lightly grease griddle.

title: pie delight
directions: Melt butter and mix with other ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: apple blossom punch
directions: Combine fruit juices and ginger ale.
Pour over block of ice. Float orange slices on top of punch.

title: chocolate eclair torte
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with graham crackers.
Mix 3 packages of pudding with milk.
Beat.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half of pudding mix over crackers.
Repeat layers of crackers and pudding.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Frost with chocolate frosting. Chill.

title: mustardy fried chicken breasts
directions: Wipe chicken breasts with damp paper toweling.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans on a pizza pan or 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Mix avocado and sour cream.
Spread over top.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate.
Surround with Tostitos or Doritos before serving.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken in water to cover until tender.
Remove meat from bones and cut in small pieces.
To 3 quarts chicken broth, add chicken, hamburger, diced potatoes, diced onions, beans, corn, salt and pepper.
Simmer 2 hours.
Add tomatoes, sugar and tomato paste and more water or broth, if necessary, then simmer 1 hour or longer.
Cream 2 potatoes or use instant mashed potatoes and add enough to stew to thicken.
Add margarine and additional salt and pepper, if needed.
Be sure and stir often, as it will stick after adding mashed potatoes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup of water.
Mix remaining water with powdered milk, sugar and salt.
Pour over the dissolved yeast. Stir in the melted butter.
Beat in 2 eggs.
Stir the dough out onto a floured surface and clean the bowl.
Knead the dough for 6 to 8 minutes, adding flour as necessary, until it is smooth and bouncy.
Grease the bowl and return dough to it.
Cover it with plastic wrap and let it rise in a warm place for about an hour until it doubles in size.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; mix.
Add buttermilk or sour milk and mix.
(To make sour milk, add 1 tablespoon of lemon juice or vinegar to 1 cup measure and fill to 1 cup with milk.) Measure dry ingredients onto wax paper and stir to mix.
Add to wet ingredients and mix.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan. Sprinkle with topping.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until they become clear.
Add egg yolks, butter and lemon juice; cook until thick. Cool.
Pour in baked pie crust. Cover with meringue and brown at 300°.

title: corn chip dip
directions: Heat all ingredients in crock-pot and serve.

title: deli pasta salad
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and cut into small sections.
Prepare rotini according to package directions; drain.
In large bowl, combine rotini and remaining ingredients; toss to mix.
Cover, chill thoroughly.
Toss gently before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar; add coconut, cherries and nuts. Mix with hands.
Place in small dry bowl lined with Saran Wrap. Chill until firm.
Reshape and pat until round.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Garnish with cherries on top.

title: chicken with hidden valley
directions: Place chicken breasts, meaty side up, in a pan.
Pour 3/4 cup of melted margarine over them.
Sprinkle 1 package Hidden Valley Ranch (dry) over them.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Beat egg and mix lightly with the remaining ingredients. Drain a (No. 2 1/2) can fruit cocktail and add to the previous ingredients and then put into a square baking pan.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup brown sugar; bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: old fashioned lemonade
directions: Boil water and sugar in a small saucepan for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice.
Cool this syrup.
Place syrup in a covered jar and refrigerate.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll into balls.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: crab soup
directions: Mix and heat together over medium heat.
Serve.

title: yogurt fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with slices of fresh fruit.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups dip.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except Parmesan cheese well.
Bake at 325° to 350° for twenty minutes.
Add Parmesan cheese and bake ten minutes more.
Let stand five minutes before serving.
Use an 8 x 8 x 2-inch ungreased pan.

title: fudge pie
directions: Over low heat or in double boiler, melt butter and chocolate squares.
Meanwhile, beat eggs until light in separate mixing bowl. Add corn syrup, sugar, salt and vanilla to eggs and continue beating until mixed well.
Add the slightly cooled chocolate mixture, mix thoroughly and pour into a 9-inch pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is crusty and filling is set, still somewhat soft inside.
Do not overcook. Serve plain or with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: corn and zucchini souffle
directions: Saute corn and zucchini in 2 tablespoons butter for 5 minutes. Stir in onion and set aside.
Heat 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook until smooth and bubbly.
Add milk gradually.
Stir and cook over medium heat until mixture thickens. Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks into a bowl, then gradually stir into hot mixture. Add sauteed corn and zucchini mixture.
Stir in shredded cheese.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Blend 1/3 of the egg whites into milk mixture. Carefully fold in the remaining eggs until no white streaks remain.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until puffy and golden brown on top.
Serves 6.

title: butter baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Leave skin on.
Slice into round pieces. Layer potatoes, sliced onion, salt and pepper and little squares of butter in large deep dish pan.
Layer until all ingredients are gone.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch cake pans.
In large bowl cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Slowly combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add water and beat until smooth.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: southern fried chicken with cream gravy
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry with paper towels.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Put 1 cup flour in a paper or plastic bag.
Drop chicken pieces, 2 at a time, into bag.
Shake until each piece is thoroughly coated with flour.
Lay chicken on a sheet of waxed paper.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, Crisco, salt, sugar, flour and milk, and mix until well blended.
Add baking powder and flavoring.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple (reserve 3 tablespoons juice).
Combine sugar and flour and stir in reserved pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple; mix well.
Put mixture in long casserole dish.
Combine butter and cracker crumbs and put on mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until crumbs are brown.

title: cheese stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Use a sharp knife to cut a small pocket in the thickest side of each chicken breast half.
Insert a Mozzarella cheese slice in each pocket.
Beat egg white in small bowl.
In another bowl, mix flour, Parmesan cheese, parsley, paprika and pepper.
Dip chicken in egg white, then flour mixture. Spray pan with nonstick spray.
Bake at 370° for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no spice apple pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and oil. Add eggs, one at a time and beat well. Add sifted flour, baking soda and salt a little at a time. Stir in the apples, coconut and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan. Turn out on cake rack to cool. May be frozen.

title: cheese and olive treats
directions: Mix margarine and cheese; add flour. Mix well. Roll piece in size of walnut. Stick olive in middle. Roll until covered. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: maid of honor
directions: Cream lard and water together.
Add dry ingredients, allow to cool before using.

title: virgin strawberry daiquiri
directions: Combine mixer, juices and sugar in a large container and stir to blend.

title: kraft caramel cookies
directions: Melt
together	in a double boiler the caramels, margarine and milk.
Dip marshmallows into caramel mixture and roll in Rice Krispies.

title: skillet steak and eggs
directions: Brown beef in a frying pan over medium heat until just brown. Add onion and cook until tender; drain fat.
Stir in eggs and scramble.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: bacon-mushroom wraps
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove to paper toweling.
Drain fat, reserving 3 tablespoons.
Cook mushrooms, garlic and onion in drippings until vegetables are soft.
Crumble bacon and add to mushroom mixture.
Add cheese, oregano and thyme.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
On a flat surface, stack 10 sheets of filo on wax paper. Cut stack lengthwise into 5 strips.
Using two strips at a time, brush with butter and put a heaping teaspoonful of the filling at the bottom end of strip.
Fold up filling so bottom end meets left edge of the dough strip.
Continue to fold, forming a triangle. Put on a baking sheet and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden.

title: helen's potato salad
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Boil 4 eggs until done (10 minutes).
Peel and chop.
Add all ingredients together and stir.
Use enough mayonnaise to mix well.

title: nicola's spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute garlic and onion (in cast-iron pan) in a few tablespoons of olive oil.
Add beef.
Simmer until just cooked.
Add tomatoes, plus the juice, the paste or puree, a pinch of salt, rosemary and basil.
Stir often for 10 minutes.
Simmer on low, covered for 1 hour.
To thicken, simmer longer, uncovered.

title: crab dip
directions: Put crab meat and onion into a bowl and set aside.
Mix cheese, milk and Worcestershire in a blender and mix to a thick paste (for a dip).
Add more milk if needed, 1 teaspoon at a time, then scoop into crab meat and onion mixture and mix well.
Put into a serving dish and top with shrimp sauce and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: crabmeat dip("appetizer")
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add to appropriate baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: creme puff dessert
directions: Bring to boil water and margarine.
Remove from heat and add flour.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Spread into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, which has been greased.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes; cool.

title: cherry oat dessert squares
directions: Mix sugar, nuts, oats, margarine and flour until crumbly.
Set 1 1/2 cups aside for later.
Press remainder of crumb mixture into the bottom of a 9-inch square baking dish.
Mix cinnamon and cherry filling and spread over crust.
Sprinkle leftover crumb mixture over top and press lightly.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: macaroni and cheese salad
directions: Make and refrigerate macaroni and cheese; add ingredients to cool macaroni and cheese.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Mix and boil 1 stick butter, shortening, 4 teaspoons cocoa and water, then add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well. Bake in an 11 x 17 pan at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: joke dessert
directions: Mix margarine and crackers and press into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes, cool.
Mix pudding with milk until thick.
Add ice cream a little at a time.
Pour over crumbs. Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with the coconut.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine cocoa with sugar and salt.
Add milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cook to 228° or until a small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat; drop in butter and stir to melt butter.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture thickens.
Spread on layers.
If chocolate gets too hard, add a small amount of milk.

title: noodles napoleoni
directions: Cook meat, garlic, salt, and pepper until hamburger is done. Add tomato sauce cover bring to boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
In another bowl combine cream cheese, sour cream and scallions - set aside.
Combine hamburger sauce with the cooked noodles.
In buttered 2-qt casserole layer as follows:
1/2 of the noodles and hamburger mixture, 1/2 of the scallion mixture (just drop the scallion mixture by teaspoon over noodles mixture).
Cover with cheddar cheese an bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "feather lite" pancakes
directions: Add dry ingredients to liquid; beat smooth.
Bake on hot griddle.
Yields 10 pancakes (6-inches each).

title: two bean and cheese tortilla stacks
directions: Cook black beans, pink beans, salsa and cumin in a medium sized saucepan over medium heat until hot, 5 minutes.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Yield:
60 cookies.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Chop vegetables into uniform sizes.
Then heat margarine in skillet over medium-high heat until bubbly.
Add vegetables and oregano to skillet.
Stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup water. Cook 5 minutes longer.
Stir in rice.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese.
Serve hot.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour; slowly add milk, mixing well.
Fill can with water.
Add to mixture.
Cook over medium heat until it begins to thicken.
Mix small amount of filling with beaten egg yolks until smooth.
Add to filling.
Mix well while continuing cooking.
Stir in cheese, mixing until melted.
Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites. Beat until glossy.
Add sugar slowly, beating well until stiff.
Spread on filling. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Saute onion.
Add tomato sauce, vinegar, chili powder, cloves, salt, and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add beans.
Continue to simmer 15 minutes.
Take off heat.
Leave covered and let stand 20 minutes.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Roll vanilla wafers into very fine crumbs. Combine with pecans and cocoa.
Mix bourbon with corn syrup, then combine with wafer mixture.
Make into pecan size balls, then roll in sugar.
Place in airtight tin. The longer you keep it, the stronger it gets.

title: coney sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and break up.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cook until onions cook down (about 1/2 hour).
You can cut down on tomato sauce to make it less watery or add extra chili powder to make it hotter.

title: east texas preserve cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cream together the butter and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours in 2 iron skillets.
Ice with caramel icing, if desired.

title: chipa guazu
directions: Brown chopped onion in margarine and add milk.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Mix well and place in greased baking dish. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: glenna's sauerbraten
directions: While heating wine vinegar and water to just below boiling, place roast in large glass or earthenware bowl. Add remaining ingredients to roast. Pour vinegar and water mixture over roast and other ingredients. Place meat in refrigerator to marinate for approximately five days (at least three days). Being careful to not pierce the meat, turn the meat in the mixture with a wooden spoon twice a day.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out excess water.
Mix spinach in bowl with eggs, cheeses, pepper and onions.
Spray 1-quart casserole with Pam and pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together; set aside.

title: taco pie
directions: Put all ingredients, except onion, tomatoes and cheese in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Then spread mixture into a pie plate.
Layer with chopped onion, then layer chopped tomatoes and then top with shredded cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together with small amount of water. heat until fully cooked. Great for parties!

title: philly bread
directions: Thoroughly blend softened cream cheese, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Gradually add 2 cups of flour mixed with baking powder.
Combine. Combine 1/4 cup flour with candied fruit and pecans.
Fold into batter.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Pour batter into pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
When totally cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: garlic and tomato risotto
directions: Coat saucepan with cooking spray; warm over medium-high heat. Add onion; saute until soft but not brown.
(Add 1/4 cup extra broth, if needed to prevent browning.)
Add bell pepper, garlic, dried and fresh tomatoes and spinach.
Saute 1 minute.
Pour in 1/2 cup broth.
Bring to a boil; lower heat to medium.
Cook, stirring continuously, until liquid is almost completely absorbed, adding broth 1/2 cup at a time as it is absorbed.
Stop adding liquid when rice is creamy and just tender, about 25 minutes. Remove Risotto from heat and add Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Beat eggs, milk, baking mix and salt with hand beater until foamy. Remove seeds from chilies; rinse chilies with water. Place in dish. Sprinkle tomatoes and onion evenly over chilies. Pour egg mixture over vegetables. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake uncovered until egg mixture is set and cheese is melted, 40 to 45 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: meatball oven stew
directions: Thoroughly mix first 9 ingredients.
Roll into 1 to 2 inch balls.
Roll the balls in flour and brown, using the fat.
Remove the meatballs from browning pan and use the remaining flour, fat in pan and tomato juice to make tomato gravy.
Place the cut vegetables in a heavy roasting pan.
Put the meatballs on top of the vegetables.
Pour the gravy over the meatballs.
Roast in a 325° oven for approximately 2 hours.
Takes about 1 hour to prepare.
Good recipe to put in oven before church so lunch is ready when you return home.

title: marge's play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients in stainless steel pot.
Cook on stove on low until thickened.
Add some food coloring during cooking. Let cool before handling.
Store in plastic container.
Hours of fun!

title: peanut cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Add beaten eggs, then flour, soda, baking powder, oatmeal, cornflakes and vanilla. Work in Spanish peanuts. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: deer steak
directions: In skillet cover bottom of pan with oil.
Put meat in and cover completely with water.
Sprinkle all over with seasoning.
Cut up onion and pepper over meat.
Cover meat with ketchup or barbecue sauce.
May need a little water until tender.

title: food for angels
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; gradually beat in sugar until very stiff.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread with 1 carton Cool Whip.
Top generously with coconut.

title: rice-nut casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into dish and cover with foil.
Bake at 325°, stirring every 20 minutes until margarine melts.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: aunt jessie's salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Blend cream cheese and jello mixtures together.
Add Cool Whip and pineapple.
Chill.

title: mama tee's fruit salad
directions: Mix drained orange segments and pineapple.
Fold in sour cream.
Add marshmallows and pecans.
Refrigerate for 1/2 a day or overnight.
Serve either with main course or dessert course. Serves 8 to 10.

title: giant oatmeal spice cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Combine dry ingredients and set aside. Combine oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add to flour mix.
Stir in nuts and oats.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: apricot congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
While this cools, beat cream cheese, pineapple and baby food.
Mix well with spatula.
Blend in Cool Whip, then jello mixture (when it has cooled). Refrigerate.

title: ratatouille
directions: Wash the zucchini, dry it and slice it in 1/8-inch rounds. Put a little oil in a heavy skillet and begin sauteeing the zucchini a layer at a time, them removing it to a side dish.
Peel and slice the eggplant in the shape of French fried potatoes.
Add more oil to the skillet and saute the eggplant, then place it in the dish with the zucchini.
Add more oil and saute the onions, green peppers and garlic until softened.
Cut the tomatoes in half and squeeze out the juice and seeds.
Chop them and add to the vegetables in the skillet.
Season with salt and pepper and cook uncovered, until the juice from the tomatoes almost evaporates. Stir frequently.
Return the eggplant and zucchini to the skillet with the other vegetables.

Adjust the salt and pepper; sprinkle with herbs and cook, covered, over low heat about 5 minutes. Uncover and cook over slightly higher heat another 15 minutes, lifting the vegetables and turning carefully with a spatula until nearly all the juices have evaporated except for a few tablespoons of richly flavored oil.
Set aside, uncovered, until serving time, then reheat slowly or serve cold.
It is important for each vegetable to retain its own texture and flavor.
Be careful not to overcook.
"Cold" means room temperature.
Refrigerating diminishes the flavors too much.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: *mama's muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Mix until dry ingredients are moist.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
This batter will keep for 6 weeks in a covered mixing bowl, placed in the refrigerator.
Great for breakfast.

title: famous ashby cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together.
Resift all into 9 x 13-inch pan (ungreased).
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir with fork until well mixed.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry juice
directions: For every cup of berries, add 1 cup of water.
Bring to a boil in a stainless steel or enamel pot; cook until berries burst. Strain through jelly bag or several layers of cheesecloth.
Boil juice for 1 minute.
Add sugar to taste, if desired.
If sugar is used, boil 5 minutes longer.
Freeze or can.

title: argentine ham and cheese pie
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups milk.
Roll out half of dough 1/4 inch thick.
Fit into bottom of 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan. Cover with a layer of sliced ham, then a layer of sliced cheese. Mix eggs, mustard, Parmesan cheese and 2 cups milk.
Pour over ham and cheese.
Roll out remaining dough and place on top.
Make a few slits in the top crust.
Brush top with milk.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes, then cut into squares and serve.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: sopa (mexican rice)
directions: Get bacon grease hot.
Add rice and brown; add onion and let brown.
Add tomato sauce and mix.
Add chicken broth and can of water.
Sprinkle garlic, cumin and oregano to taste.
Stir and cover.
Do not stir anymore.
Cook until moisture disappears.

title: easy chilli soup
directions: Saute onion and peppers in 1 tablespoon cooking oil, then add hamburger and brown lightly, stirring frequently.
Put in 4-quart pan.
Combine the two cans of soup with two cans of water; mix well and add to meat.
Add kidney beans and salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer one hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lizzies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and add liquids and sifted ingredients alternately.
Use part of flour to dredge chopped fruits and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheets and bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 16 dozen.
Excellent cookies at Christmastime.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Add water.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Jell-O.
Place berries in cool shell.
Pour glaze over.
Refrigerate.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and make sauce.
Mix sugar and flour with juice from pineapple.
Boil until thick.
Let cool and mix with fruit.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring water, sugar and cornstarch to a boil, then add Jell-O and let cool.

Spread softened cream cheese in crust carefully without breaking (be sure to cover all the graham cracker crust). Arrange strawberries in crust then pour Jell-O mixture over top. Refrigerate for a couple hours.

title: marinated carrots(these are delicious.....)
directions: Cook carrots, onion and salt until tender. In medium saucepan, mix remaining ingredients. Boil and pour over drained carrots. Serve cold.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Mix limeade, milk, Cool Whip and green food color.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut
cookie dough in 1/2-inch slices.
Place on lightly greased
14-inch pizza pan (sides touching).
Bake as directed on dough
package.
Remove from oven and press flat with palm of hand.
Set aside to cool.

title: everyday cookies
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar, margarine, vegetable oil, egg and vanilla.
Add salt, soda, cream of tartar and flour.
Add quick oats, Rice Krispies, coconut and chopped nuts.
Roll into small balls.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Yields 12 dozen.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and egg yolks.
Roll in 1-inch balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg whites.
Roll in nuts. Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Remove and make thumb print.
Continue baking for 8 minutes more.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms and garlic in margarine with onion.
Prepare sauce blending into vegetable mixture.
Add 2 tablespoons Dry Sack sherry, 2 tablespoons minced fresh parsley and 1 teaspoon lemon juice to prepared sauce.
Serve hot with chicken, beef or vegetables.

title: date nut cake
