directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let soak and cool.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Combine both mixtures.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: raspberry cream cake
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Chill.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Put ingredients in layers as listed in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Don't mix.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: nordic potato soup with ham
directions: Cooking Time: 8 1/2 to 9 hours.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add lemon juice.
Allow to stand in refrigerator until chilled, but not firm.
Add the celery, pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Pour into one large or individual molds and chill.

title: alan's creamed chicken breast
directions: In large bowl, mix together first 5 items.
Place chicken in a large roasting pan and cover with mixture.
Bake at 350° until chicken is cooked, approximately 30 minutes or more.
Serve over rice, pasta or boiled potatoes.

title: lemon chicken and fried rice
directions: Salt, pepper and lemon pepper chicken strips. In a frying pan brown chicken strips in olive oil until brown. Add cans of rice and 2 1/2 cans of water, simmer until rice has absorbed water. Squeeze 1 or 2 lemons over mixture and stir. Serve with egg rolls or rolls and salad for a complete meal.

title: rice dressing
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
Put in slow cooker or oven pan. Add 2 quarts of hot water, mushrooms and rice.
Cook on high until moisture is absorbed.
Season with beef or poultry seasoning to taste.
Continue cooking until light and fluffy.
Serve hot with any meat dish or by itself.

title: baked chicken
directions: Cut chicken into quarters.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Broil both sides.
Add soup and sherry to taste.
Bake 40 minutes in 325° oven.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Add egg yolks and beat, then add buttermilk, soda, flour, spices and stewed prunes. Lastly add the 3 egg whites, stiffly beaten. Bake in 2 layers in a 350° oven. Put together with Prune Filling. Bake 25 minutes or until done.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Rinse artichokes in cold water; drain, then mash.
Stir in remaining ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Spread in 9-inch pie dish; bake in 350° oven, 30 minutes or until hot throughout. Serve with Melba toast or wafers.

title: baked mashed potato balls
directions: Have mashed potatoes ready.
Beat in egg yolks and chopped parsley.
Cool these ingredients slightly.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold them lightly into the potato mixture.
Shape the mixture into balls.
Bake the potatoes in lightly greased muffin tins or drop them on a greased sheet.
Bake them until crisp. Turn them to brown evenly.

title: turtle brownies
directions: On top of stove over low heat, combine caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
While caramels are melting, combine cake mix, butter and remaining 1/3 cup of evaporated milk; mix well.
Add pecans.
Pour half of mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate pieces on top. Pour melted caramels over chocolate pieces.
Spoon remaining cake mixture over caramels.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: menudo(mexican tripe stew)
directions: Cut beef tripe into small pieces.
Simmer, without any liquid, for 1/2 hour.
Watch that it doesn't burn.
Add water and simmer for 2 hours.
Add more water, if needed.
Add chicken broth, hominy and rest of the ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours more. May be served with jalapenos and/or a slice of lime.

title: brussels sprouts and rice
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium heat, heat undiluted soup, milk, 1 cup water, butter or margarine, salt and caraway seed to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sprouts; cover and continue to cook 15 minutes or until rice and sprouts are tender.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball; remove from heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter; mix until blended.
Add flavoring.
Pour into buttered pan (10 x 10-inches); cool.
Cut into squares.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 400° about 20 minutes or until brown.
I bake mine in 2 pie pans.

title: soft and chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Note:
Add 1 1/2 cups chocolate chips if nuts are omitted.

title: dressing for lettuce or endive
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces and fry to crisp. Drain and cool. Mix sugar and egg and beat together. Add water, flour, salt and vinegar. Blend with rotary blender and add mixture to bacon. Cook and stir over low heat until thickened. Add small onion to dressing before placing on the greens.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: *Use any fruit flavor.
Cut apple and peach pieces smaller.

title: banana cake
directions: Mash bananas and add water.
Cream butter or oleo and sugar together.
Add egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
If using self-rising flour omit baking powder.
Sift 3 or 4 times.
Add banana mixture to sugar mixture alternately with flour.
Add chopped nuts and beat until smooth. Fold in well-beaten egg whites.
Bake in two layers and put together with powdered sugar or 7-minute frosting.

title: hamburger-veggie soup
directions: In Dutch oven pan, fry hamburger in two tablespoons butter and all seasonings, garlic, bouillon cube and onion.
Don't drain.
In same pan, add 8 cups water, potatoes and carrots.
Put lid on and boil until veggies are tender.
Add corn and beans; cook until warm.
Serve.
The fennel seed add a sweetness to the flavor of the soup.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese together.
Add orange juice or lemon juice.
Excellent for dipping strawberries, apples, etc.

title: pickled beets
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and cook for about 5 minutes. Stir in beets.
Continue to cook for about 5 more minutes.

title: pumpkin tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together grahams, 1/3 sugar and margarine and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 2 eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Pour this over crust.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 45 minutes (important).
When 20 minutes have passed of this 45 minutes start next part.
Mix pumpkin, egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, milk, salt and cinnamon.
Cook this until mixture is hot throughout.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Beat egg whites; add 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Remove 1 cup of this mixture and set aside.
Pour the rest of mix over baked crust.
Fold 1 large container Cool Whip as next layer, then take the 1 cup of mixture and add to a small container of Cool Whip and fold over Cool Whip layer.
Chill at least 2 to 3 hours.
Better overnight.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes and chop.
Combine all ingredients.
Put in glass pie dish and heat for 30 minutes at 300°.
Serve warm.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, egg, vanilla and salt. Fold in blueberries. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine pickles and onions in gallon jar.
Add brine mix and dissolve.
Don't cook!!

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna in boiling, salted water according to package directions.
Drain.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, Ricotta, spinach, salt, lemon rind and lemon juice.
(Optional: Pinch of cinnamon.)
Mix well.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Bring soup to boil (no water).
Add cream cheese; stir until dissolved.
Add gelatin and mayonnaise, stirring until blended well.
Add shrimp, onions and celery; stir.
Grease mold with mayonnaise and pour mixture in.
Let set 2 to 3 hours.
Unmold by dipping in hot water.
Serve with crackers or rye bread.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and butter.
Add sugars and cream until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour and dry ingredients and add to mixture, alternately with milk.
Add flavorings.
Blend thoroughly.
Stir in pecans.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mock pralines
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter gradually with margarine.
Add sugar and bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, cover with foil.
Place graham crackers (one square cut in half) in pan. Cover completely with pecans.
Pour butter sauce over top and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Let cool before taking out of pan.

title: dumplins
directions: Mix, drop by spoonfuls on top of hot vegetables and liquid of beef or chicken stew.
Cook on low for 10 minutes, uncovered, and 10 minutes, covered.

title: copper coins
directions: Mix together the carrots, onions and green pepper; set aside. Mix soup, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salad oil and mustard. Pour over carrot mixture.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Mix corn with eggs and set aside.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, pepper and milk.
Add milk gradually to flour mixture.
Beat until smooth, then add melted butter.
Combine this batter with corn and egg mixture, then pour mixture in a greased casserole.
Set in a pan of hot water.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 45 to 60 minutes until custard is firm.

title: seashell dandy salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Mix mayonnaise with lemon juice, salt and sugar. Combine with macaroni, celery seed, tomato, celery, pimiento and green pepper.
Serve on salad greens; garnish with radish roses. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick casserole dinner
directions: Press beef in a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Spread mushroom soup over meat.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over all.
Top with potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch cake pan or baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over top of rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: plump pork patties with spinach
directions: Remove stems from spinach and plunge into boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain and squeeze dry.
Chop fine, or very coarse in blender.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef and garlic in a small amount of oil.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Alternate layers of meat sauce, noodles and cheese in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish, beginning and ending with meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: orange velvet
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir until completely dissolved.
Chill in mixing bowl until syrupy, like egg whites. Whip with beater until gelatin is foamy and light and no clear gelatin showing.
Add sherbet and whipped topping; fold together until smoothly blended.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours, until set.
Easy and fast.
Can be poured into an elegant bowl before chilling for best presentation.

title: mom's barbecue sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, stir together sugar, flour and salt. Drain pineapple, reserving juice to equal 1 cup.
With whisk, gradually stir juice and egg into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in lemon juice.
Cool to room temperature.

title: one skillet spicy chicken 'n rice
directions: In plastic bag, combine flour and seasoned salt.
Add chicken; shake to coat well.
In large skillet over medium-high heat, brown chicken in hot oil; reduce heat to low.
Cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except parsley; blend well. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and chicken is tender.
Garnish with parsley. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: k f c cole slaw
directions: In large bowl, place cabbage and carrots.
Separately combine sugar, salt, pepper, milk, mayonnaise, buttermilk, vinegar and lemon juice, beating until smooth.
Mix well with cabbage and carrots.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: stuffed calamari
directions: Wash and drain squid.
Chop tentacles.
In medium bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, eggs, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.
Stir in tentacles.
Fill each squid with stuffing.
Pinch ends closed and seal with toothpick. Preheat oven to 350°.
Place squid in shallow baking dish.
Pour sauce over squid.
Bake 45 minutes or until squid are tender.

title: frozen hash browns
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Season to taste. Add croutons or fried onions on top.

title: snickerdoodles(cookies)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill dough at least one hour.
Roll into walnut-sized balls.
Roll balls into mixture of 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until bottoms are brown and top cracks.
Cool on paper bag.

title: apple or cherry dump cake
directions: Spread crushed pineapple in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch cake pan. Spread pie filling mix on top.
Spread cake mix on top of the fruit, then nuts.
Cut up the margarine and put all over the top. Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: heaven by the sea crab ball
directions: Blend all ingredients well. Chill in a ball. Before serving, make a well in the middle of the ball and fill with cocktail sauce.
Serve with butter crackers.

title: curried cabbage and carrots
directions: In a medium skillet, combine all ingredients.
Cover; cook until crisp-tender (about 6 to 8 minutes), stirring occasionally. Makes 3 (1 1/2-cup) servings.

title: saucepan scotchies
directions: Grease bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with oleo.
Melt oleo in a saucepan. Remove from heat. Add sugar and blend. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Stir in flour, vanilla and baking powder. Mix thoroughly. Add nuts and stir lightly to combine.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for approximately 30 minutes. Do not overbake. Cool in pan. Cut into bars. Frost, if desired.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; mix well after each addition.
Add flour, cocoa and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Top with chocolate frosting if desired.

title: sweet and sour beans
directions: Cook sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar for about 15 minutes to make a sauce.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar and vinegar well.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour over beans and marinate a few hours or overnight.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar. Add eggs and pumpkin and mix well. Sift together dry ingredients. Add to pumpkin mixture alternately with water. Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 5 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach-spaghetti casserole
directions: Chop, thaw and drain spinach.
Break, cook and drain spaghetti.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake, covered, in casserole at 350° for 40 minutes.
This recipe may be cut in half and can be made the day before.
Good with all meats, fish or fowl.

title: squash relish
directions: Step 1:
Chop squash, onions, bell peppers and hot pepper; add salt.
Stir and let stand 1 hour.
Keep cold with ice cubes. Cover with ice cubes in pan.
Drain off liquid.

title: kiffle
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.
Roll out very thin on powdered sugar board into 2-inch squares.
Add
1 teaspoon filling and roll to form logs.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken a la romano
directions: Place chicken pieces in shallow baking pan.
Place pan in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour off liquid. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and red pepper.
Mix garlic, parsley and oregano and sprinkle over this.
Cover with canned tomatoes, then grated cheese.
Top with olive oil.
Return to oven and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours more until tender.
Serve with pasta.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in a medium size saucepan; combine with flour.
Add basil and thyme; combine.
Heat milk and stir in gradually.
Stir in wine; cook, stirring until smooth and thick.
Combine wild and brown rice with almonds and 1/4 cup parsley; add to sauce and toss lightly to combine.
Slice each fillet down side seam to form a pocket; spoon in rice mixture. Secure with toothpicks if necessary.
Place on oiled baking pan.

title: antipasto platter
directions: In a large bowl combine mushrooms, artichoke hearts, olive oil, vinegar, red wine (if desired), basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Toss ingredients well, then set aside and let marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Crush crackers and 1/4 cup butter, 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Mix together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs and add remaining 1/2 cup of sugar.
Beat in cream cheese and vanilla. Pour mixture over graham cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until firm.
Let cool.
Spread with blueberry filling. Top with Cool Whip.
Serve.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add rice and put in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour over rice the beef broth and water.
Stir in mushrooms.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, stirring often.

title: butterscotch nibbles
directions: In large saucepan over low heat, melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter, stirring frequently.
Stir in cereal until pieces are coated.
Stir in chocolate morsels just until combined but not melted.
Spread on waxed paper lined tray.
Chill 30 minutes or until coating is set.

title: zesty crackers
directions: In a large bowl, blend the dressing mix, garlic powder, dill seed and lemon pepper with oil.
Add oyster crackers and toss until completely coated.
May be served as is or may be baked at 350° for a few minutes if desired.

title: baked chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Mix above ingredients in a large bowl. Coat chicken breasts. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in cornflake crumbs.
Chill.
Place in greased pan and bake in a 325° oven for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mrs. fields' cookies(best chocolate chip cookies you ever ate!)
directions: *After measuring, put into blender and blend until powder.

title: brown bag burritos
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Add next eight ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Heat 3 to 4 tortillas in a microwave until warm, about 45 seconds.
Spoon 3 to 4 tablespoons of beef mixture down side of each tortilla.
Top with 2 to 3 tablespoons of cheese.
Roll up. Wrap each burrito in paper towel, then in foil.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Eat burritos cold, or remove foil and heat paper towel-wrapped burrito in a microwave on High for about 1 minute.
Yields 15 to 20 burritos.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender.
Chop coarsely. Place in buttered 1-quart casserole.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with cooked macaroni.
Spread pizza sauce and mushrooms over macaroni.
Top with cheeses.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add anything you like on pizza.

title: fanny may fudge
directions: Put the marshmallows or Marshmallow Creme and the water in a 2-quart saucepan over low flame to melt.
Put the sugar and evaporated milk in another 2-quart saucepan.
When it comes to a boil, boil for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour second mixture over the first and stir.
Add the chocolate chips and butter.
(First some chips, then part of the butter, until all is added and melted.)
Add desired amount of nuts.
Put in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan to cool.

title: bahamian stew fish
directions: Heat oil in skillet; blend in flour and brown well, stirring constantly to avoid burning.
Add onion, thyme, tomato paste and sauce; mix well.
Heat 6 cups water to boiling; add flour mixture and simmer for about 15 minutes stirring occasionally.
Add fish, salt and pepper; cook for 20-30 minutes or until fish is tender.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in whipped topping and well drained crushed pineapple.
Spoon into crust.
Top with pineapple chunks.
Chill two hours or overnight.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and oil together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes in 2 loaf pans.

title: rolled enchiladas
directions: Cook ground beef lightly.
Drain.
Add onion, bell pepper, chili powder, garlic powder and 1/2 cup taco sauce.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Combine fish, celery, onion and lemon juice and season to taste. Chill. Drain before serving and toss with just enough mayonnaise to hold the mixture together.

title: hearty meatball and vegetable soup
directions: Combine onion flakes and minced garlic with 2 tablespoons water; let stand 10 minutes to soften.
Set aside.
Mix beef with 1/2 teaspoon marjoram.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Heat oil in saucepan.
Add meatballs, a few at a time.
Brown on all sides. Remove meatballs and set aside.
Add reserved onion and garlic to oil.
Saute 2 minutes.
Add 2 1/2 cups water, vinegar, cloves, thyme, black pepper and remaining marjoram.
Bring to a boil, stirring to scrape drippings from bottom of pan.
Return meatballs to pan.
Add potato; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 10 minutes. Add cabbage and tomato.
Return to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley flakes and serve.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together.
Butter square casserole dish (8 x 8).

In layers, put 5 slices of bread (crust), fresh spinach (cut small). Add oil, garlic powder and Cheddar. Continue for second layer. Pour wet ingredients over all. Let sit 3 hours in refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown, uncovered.

title: new caesar salad
directions: Prepare penne as label directs; rinse under running cold water and drain.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken in small pieces and place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread chicken soup on top, then spread celery soup on top. Combine stuffing mix with just enough broth to make it moist. Put on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: bohemian cake
directions: Cream sugars and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix dry ingredients and nuts.
Add alternately with milk and creamed mixture.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Spoon into greased Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Ice with favorite icing, if desired.

title: glazed nuts
directions: Microwave 1/2 cup butter one minute.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Microwave 2 minutes.
Add nuts.
Stir until coated. Microwave 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir.
Spread on waxed paper to cool.

title: cheese soup with broccoli
directions: Combine broth, potatoes, celery and onions and cook about 20 minutes or until tender.
Add frozen broccoli and cook for about 10 minutes.
Add cream of chicken soup and cheese.
Stir until cheese is completely melted.
Serve hot.

title: seven minute icing
directions: Place in a double boiler and cook, beating until stiff.

title: aunt betty's oriental salad
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the vegetables.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: mcdonald's biscuits
directions: Pour half of the melted margarine in pan; reserve the other half to pour over tops of biscuits before baking.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: okra and cheese casserole
directions: Cut tips and ends from okra and slice crosswise.
Arrange ingredients in alternate layers, beginning with tomatoes and ending with cheese.
Add seasoning to each layer.
Bake for 40 minutes in covered casserole dish at 350°.

title: aunt eilleen's soft pretzels
directions: Mix water and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add yeast and let stand approximately 20 minutes.
Add flour and knead for approximately 5 minutes.
Let rise until double in size.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt butter, Pet milk and caramels.
Pour over cake while hot, then sprinkle chips and nuts over that.
Pour the remaining cake batter on top.
Bake 20 minutes more at 350°.

title: slush margaritas
directions: Mix well in plastic container and freeze overnight.
Take out an hour before serving.
Will keep for months and is wonderful especially with Mexican appetizers!

title: strawberry angel
directions: Add water to jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add berries and stir to defrost.
Refrigerate until syrupy.
Stir in whipped cream.

title: jackie's breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add rest of ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch casserole.	Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to	45
minutes.
This
is	great to make ahead of time for overnight guests.
Feeds 6 to 8.

title: seasoned rice
directions: Heat broth to boiling; stir in rice.
Reduce heat to low. Cover. Cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: vermont maple walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat eggs; add in salt, sugar, butter and maple syrup.
Beat well.
Mix in walnuts.
Bake until knife comes out clean, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Cream butter, sugar and egg until smooth.
Add the vanilla and pumpkin.
Blend in.
Add the raisins and nuts.
Sift together baking powder, soda, salt and flour.
Stir into butter mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto buttered cookie sheet. Bake 10-13 minutes.
Remove from sheet, cool slightly then frost.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and oil until light.
Add sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Sift together and add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in small pan; add sugar.
Cook until sugar melts. Add boiling water, stir until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Mix in small bowl cornstarch, flour and salt.
Add milk gradually.
Add to sugar mixture.
Cook and stir constantly, bring to boil until thick.
Add egg yolks, slightly beaten.
Add a little mixture to keep eggs from cooking.
Mix together.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pastry shell.

title: the best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend oatmeal in a blender until it becomes a fine powder. Cream the butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: witch's brew
directions: Combine first two ingredients.
Stir in the orange juice.
May serve hot or cold.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and form into 2 loaves.

title: chasen's famous chili, updated
directions: In large pot, wash beans; add water 2-inches above beans and soak overnight.
Simmer in same water until tender.
Add tomatoes and simmer 5 minutes.
Saute green peppers slowly in oil in large pan for 5 minutes.
Add onions and cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Add garlic and parsley; stir well and add to tomato mixture.

title: pasties
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Divide into 6 equal parts.

title: party nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour pecans and salt in pan.
Mix well.
Cook for 1 hour, stirring once or twice during the cooking time.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together with hands until crumbly.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over mixture.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let cool and cut in squares.
Real good, but rich.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Spoon over coconut and nuts.
Melt margarine; add cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Turn upside down.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Dust chicken pieces with garlic powder to taste; then brown in butter or oil.
Remove chicken.
In drippings, saute green onions until tender; stir frequently.
Remove chicken to skillet.
Mix catsup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, bouillon, crushed red pepper and 1/8 to 1/4 cup water; pour on top of chicken.
Heat until boiling.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place tortillas that have been cut into triangles on cookie sheet.
Dust with salt, if desired, and bake 15 minutes or until crisp.
Place chicken on meat platter and encircle with tortilla chips.

title: sweet-sour salad
directions: Drain vegetables and combine in container.
Boil together for 5 minutes the sugar, salt, water, vinegar and oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: spaghetti dinner
directions: Boil until tender the spaghetti in six cups boiling water with salt.
Drain and rinse the spaghetti with hot water.
Mix vegetable soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper.
Cook over boiling water until the cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Fold in spaghetti and place in greased baking dish that holds about 6 cups.
Arrange desired number of wieners on top.
Bake 20 minutes or until the mixture is bubbly.

title: sausage-vegetable casserole
directions: In a 3-quart microwave-safe casserole, stir together water, milk and sauce packet from potato mix.
Add potato slices, sausage, vegetables and onion.
Microcook, covered, on High for 32 to 34 minutes, or until mixture is heated through and slightly thickened, stirring every 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Start layering in a pan with broccoli on the bottom, then put a layer of chicken on top of the broccoli.
Mix all other ingredients except the cheese and pour over the chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle the cheese on top and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice or noodles. May be cut in half for smaller casserole.

title: juanita's angel food cake
directions: Sift flour twice.
Add salt and cream of tartar in egg whites after they are half beaten.
Blend egg whites until they form a stiff peak.
Add sugar and flour alternately, 1/4 each time.
Fold in with slotted spoon.
Bake at 375°; turn down to 350° if it browns too fast.
Bake until cake springs back when touched.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to directions.
Squeeze out water thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Make into balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen place in plastic bags.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Boil 5 minutes the margarine, sugar and syrup; pour over corn. Stir to cover well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder, sugar and salt. Cut Crisco into dry mixture. Gradually add buttermilk. In separate bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water. Then add to the rest of the ingredients. Flour hands to handle dough. Roll out on floured board. Cut with biscuit cutters. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes. Dough can be covered and kept in refrigerator for a week.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: peggy's cinnamon nut bread
directions: Let bread defrost and rise.
Take a portion of bread and flatten by hand into a circle onto a greased cookie sheet.
Spread with margarine.
Sprinkle with quite a bit of brown sugar, cinnamon and chopped nuts.
Roll from the wide end into a jelly roll and curve into a circle.
Cut slits around the top and let raise approximately 45 minutes.
Then bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins and cool.
Peel and shred coarsely. Cook onion in butter on low heat.
Add cheese and stir until almost melted.
Add sour cream and salt.
Fold in potatoes and put into a greased 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons butter and bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Beat egg well.
Beat in remaining ingredients in order given: milk, vegetable oil or margarine, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Fold in 1/2 cup drained fresh or frozen blueberries.
Bake on a hot griddle.
Makes twelve 4-inch pancakes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In large skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano. Add ground chuck. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Place half of spaghetti in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with half of vegetable mixture. Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese. Repeat layers. Mix soup and water until smooth; pour over casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through. Serves approximately 12.

title: southern baked fish
directions: Place fillets, skin side down, in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Brush with butter.
Arrange limes over fillets. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and add the next 5 ingredients.
Layer 4 noodles, beans, half of meat mixture and sprinkle with chiles. Layer 4 noodles, black olives and remainder of meat mixture.
Top with 2 cups Monterey Jack or a combination of Monterey Jack and Cheddar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with sour cream or spread 2 cups of sour cream on top.

title: tea cake
directions: Sift flour; make a well and add sugar, shortening, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix and knead, making a stiff dough.
Cut with cookie cutter, thin.
Bake in moderate oven until light brown for a crisp cookie.
Use enough flour to form a stiff dough.

title: virgil's special omelet
directions: Stir clam chowder into eggs.
Beat together (do not add milk or water).
Fry as any other omelet.
You may add chopped onion or other ingredients if you wish.
Salt and pepper to taste. Excellent omelet.

title: date apple cookies
directions: Combine dates and water in saucepan.
Heat, mash and stir until smooth.
Add shredded apple, honey and pineapple juice and beat until smooth.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes to absorb moisture.
Beat briskly.
Drop from teaspoon on sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: bachelor buttons
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add egg.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Chill 2 hours or overnight.
Shape into balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: peppermint drum cake
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy. Gradually add sugar.
Beat well. Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Begin and end with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla. Beat egg whites at high speed with an electric mixer until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold into batter.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate whip pie
directions: Melt candy bar and combine with topping.
Mix well and pour into crust.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: jeannie's mexican rice
directions: Fix rice as directed on box.
Mix all ingredients into rice. Season with salt to taste.
Cook until ingredients thicken.

title: pound cake
directions: Add flour a little at a time with 1 cup milk and baking powder last.
Grease large tube pan and flour.
Put wax paper in bottom of pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let rise for 15 to 20 minutes before putting in oven.
Start in cold oven.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer uncovered for 2 hours.
Cool completely.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla
and 2 cups vodka.
Store in sealed bottles.

title: any flavor cookie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes or until brown around the edges.

title: easy banana pound cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes in greased and floured tube pan.

title: peanut butter oatmeal bars
directions: Cream together first four ingredients and the vanilla.
Beat egg and milk well.
Beat flour, soda and salt until well combined. Stir in oats and spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: pedalite drink
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: hot creamy beef dip
directions: Beat cheese
with
sour
cream	until light and fluffy. Stir in beef,
onion
and seasoning.
Turn into shallow baking dish, sprayed with Pam and top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. This makes about 3 cups.
Serve with raw vegetables. It is especially good with zucchini.

title: soft taco shells(tortillas)
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal and salt in a bowl.
Combine beaten eggs with oil and 1 1/2 cups water and pour gradually into dry ingredients to prevent lumping.
Thin to desired consistency, using more water, if necessary.

title: beef company casserole
directions: Early in the day, cook noodles according to package directions and drain. Saute beef, onions and green peppers in 1 tablespoon margarine (or use Pam) until brown. Stir in tomato sauce. Remove from heat. Combine cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream. Spread 1/2 of noodles in bottom of 2 qt. casserole dish. Spread cheese mixture over noodles. Spread rest of noodles over cheese. Pour melted margarine over the noodles. Refrigerate an hour before serving. Heat oven to 350° and bake until heated through, approximately 30-45 minutes.

title: cheese n' wiener crescents
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Slit hot dogs to within 1/2 inch of end. Insert cheese strips.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles. Place hot dogs on shortest side of triangle.
Roll up.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, cheese side up.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: diet snack or dessert
directions: Core and slice apples.
Sprinkle with dry Jell-O.
Eat and enjoy!

title: baked chop suey
directions: Cook onions until yellow; add meat and brown.
Mix with rest of ingredients, except for noodles and almonds.
Put in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle Chinese noodles on top, then the slivered almonds.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: baked pork chops and sauerkraut
directions: Drain sauerkraut.
Peel and dice apple and onion; mix with sauerkraut.
Add celery seed and salt and pepper to taste.
Spread into an 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Season pork chops; place on top of mixture.
Cover with foil; bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: peppermint stick candy layer cake
directions: Pour into baked pie shell and sprinkle with ground cinnamon.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water in an oblong dish.
Set aside 1/4 cup jello mixture to use in topping.
Stir strawberries and pineapple in dish.
Chill.

title: calico beans with pasta
directions: Fry together ground beef, bacon, onion and mushrooms; drain. Then mix tomato sauce, brown sugar, white sugar, salt, pork and beans, kidney beans and lima beans.
Cook spaghetti until tender. Mix together and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
(May sprinkle shredded cheese on top of casserole in the last few minutes of baking.)

title: sausage casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Spread oleo on each slice.
Place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook sausage, crumble and drain. Spread on top of bread.
Top this with cheese.
Combine beaten eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over cheese.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 20 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together the first 5 ingredients. Set aside.
Beat shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add egg and molasses.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to shortening mixture, alternating with boiling water.
Beat after each addition.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 9 servings.
Use 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange potatoes in four layers in 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle the first three layers with 1 tablespoon onion, 1 tablespoon flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Sprinkle last layer with remaining onion, salt and pepper; dot with butter.
Pour hot milk over potatoes and bake, covered, 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, 60 minutes longer.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Drain water.
Add onion, butter and milk.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook about 1 hour.
If needs to be thicker, add 2 tablespoons of flour.

title: centerton salad dressing
directions: Mash garlic cloves and salt together.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Allow several hours for the ingredients to blend.

title: orange french toast
directions: Slice loaf into 1-inch pieces.
In a large bowl, whisk eggs, sugar and extracts until mixed. Add juice and milk; stir to mix. Dip bread and place slices on baking sheets.
Pour remaining liquid over slices; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight until all liquid is absorbed.
Melt butter in skillet on medium heat and fry each side until browned.
Garnish with oranges and/or strawberries.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serves 8.

title: sopa de arros (spanish rice)
directions: Brown rice in 1 tablespoon hot oil making sure not to burn rice; brown rice thoroughly.
Take skillet off flame; let sit until almost cool.
Add 3 cups water or as needed.
Bring to a boil.
Add chopped onion, fresh cilantro and tomato sauce or paste.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Simmer until fully cooked.
Just before serving, add cooked peas.
In serving dish garnish with sprig of fresh cilantro.

title: chocolate cream filled cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin pan.
Sift together the flour, sugar, salt, cocoa and baking soda. Add buttermilk, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes. Add 1/2 cup boiling water.
Beat 1/2 minute more.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey parmigiana
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In shallow dish, beat egg and milk.
Mix bread crumbs, parmesan cheese, salt and pepper to taste.
Dip turkey slices into egg mixture and coat with crumbs.
Arrange on a greased baking pan, 10 x 5 x 1 inch.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over slices and top with mozzarella cheese.
Bake 4 to 5 minutes, until sauce is heated and cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: picante dip
directions: Cube cheese and add sauce.
Microwave for 5 minutes and stir. Serve with nacho chips.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Drain one can pineapple.
Stir together flour and sugar; then stir in the pineapple chunks and grated cheese.
Put mixture into a casserole and crumble Ritz crackers over the top.
Melt the margarine and drizzle it over the crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: roulade
directions: In small skillet, cook bacon, onions and parsley until bacon is cooked.
Drain off all fat.

title: barbecued onions
directions: Parboil onions for 5 minutes and drain well.
Mix honey, catsup and butter.
Pour over onions in a casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Great made with Vidalia onions.

title: tater-tot-casserole
directions: Press uncooked ground beef into bottom of 1/4 to 1/2 sheet cake pan.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Spread green beans over meat.
Spread mushroom soup over beans.
Top with package of Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and butter.
When starts to boil, time for 2 minutes, then remove from
heat.
Add peanut butter and stir.
Then add oats.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter. Mix ingredients together and beat until well mixed. Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake until done at 375° (or a little lower) or (firm).

title: chicken puffs
directions: Mix cream cheese until soft. Add chicken and soup.
Mix well. Separate crescent rolls and put 1/4 cup chicken mixture in each. Roll up and dip in butter.
Roll in crushed bread crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Heat the leftover can of cream of chicken soup (with milk added).
Put on top just before you eat.

title: no egg chocolate cake
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients into large bowl.
Add to this the last 4 ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Very moist and easy to make.

title: teddy bears picnic
directions: Mix in large bowl and serve.

title: microwave rice krispie treats
directions: In 3-quart casserole, place butter.
Microwave at High for 1 minute.
Add marshmallows. Cover.
Microwave 2 1/2 or 3 minutes. Remove from oven and stir until butter is melted and marshmallows are well blended.
Add cereal.
Stir until well coated.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Mix and shape into a ball.
Roll in nuts.

title: peanut butter chocolate chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine peanut butter, brown sugar and egg in medium bowl until well blended.

Add chocolate chips to the dough. Mix well. Roll heaping tablespoonfuls of dough into 1 1/2-inch balls. Place dough balls about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Dip table fork into granulated sugar. Press sugar-coated tines of fork in crisscross fashion onto each ball, flattening to 1/2-inch thickness.

Repeat dipping fork into granulated sugar to prevent it from sticking to dough. Bake cookies in middle of oven until set, about 12 minutes. Let cookies stand on baking sheets for 2 minutes. Remove cookies with spatula to wire racks. Let cool completely. Store cookies in airtight container for up to one week.

title: brown buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add a teaspoon of sugar. Combine shortening, boiling water, sugar, salt and graham flour. Stir until shortening is melted.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture, molasses and eggs.
Add white flour as needed (about 6 to 7 cups) to make firm elastic dough.
Let rise until double.
Knead down and let rise again.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Flake the salmon and stir in crumbs, eggs, salt and paprika. Form the ingredients into cakes and saute them in butter until browned.
Serve with mushroom or tartar sauce.
Serves 12.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Beat margarine for 30 seconds.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, 1 cup flour and the salt.
Mix well and press into the bottom of the 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, beat eggs.
Add remaining 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons of flour, lemon juice and the baking powder.
Beat 3 minutes or until slightly thick.
Pour over baked layer.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until light golden brown around the edges and the center is set.
Cool.
Sift powdered sugar over the top, if desired.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16.

title: beef cabbage casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Then layer in casserole.
Put cabbage first, then beef and onion mixture.
Mix tomato soup with 1/2 can water.
Pour over cabbage and beef.
Cover with foil to cook.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Put in 1-gallon crock.
Let pickles stand 3 days before using.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Blend in a blender until smooth.

title: good filled white cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix well and roll out thin.
To make filling, boil raisins, water, flour and sugar until clear.
Add nuts.
Spread half of rolled dough with filling.
Then cover with other half of dough.
Use cookie cutter or cut in squares.
Bake at 350° until nice and brown.

title: japanese pie
directions: Cook 45 minutes or until done, in uncooked pie shell, at 300°.

title: dump cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
No mixing.
Spread each ingredient over the last one.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with ice cream.

title: meringue hearts with strawberry ice cream
directions: Place egg whites in small, deep bowl of electric mixer.
Add salt, vinegar and vanilla to whites.
Beat on high speed until peaks form.
Gradually add sugar until whites are very stiff. Make 6 mounds of egg white on a cookie sheet covered with brown paper.
With the back of a teaspoon, form each mound into a heart shell.
Bake in a 300° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from paper immediately.
Cool.
Fill meringue hearts with scoop of ice cream.

title: mustard glazed chicken
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Pour over chicken in shallow dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight; turn occasionally.
Drain; save marinade.
Preheat both sides of gas grill on high 10 minutes.
Place chicken on grill.
Close hood and cook 45 to 50 minutes.
Turn and baste often.
Just before serving, brush with a mixture of honey and mustard.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Split rolls.
Place ham and cheese in middle.
Melt margarine in a small saucepan.
Add dry mustard, poppy seed, dried onion and soy sauce or Worcestershire sauce.
Heat to boiling.
Spoon or brush over tops of rolls.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: funnel cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Heat oil to 375° to 400°. Use 1/2 cup mixture in o size funnel.
Swirl in circles in hot oil. Let brown, then turn.
Remove and place on paper plate.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes about 12 (9-inch) cakes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients. Chill.
Roll into 2 balls and roll in chopped pecans.

title: deer meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Grease baking dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or so.
Check occasionally.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Boil together marshmallows and butter.
When boiled, drop in extracts.
Take popcorn, popped in oil and salted slightly and mix together with first mixture.
Spread in buttered pan.
Let cool in refrigerator.

title: rich banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 1 (9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch) pan or 2 (7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inch) pans.
Melt the butter and cool slightly.
Add eggs with sour cream, bananas and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add to banana mixture.
Be careful not to overmix.
Stir in nuts.
Pour dough into greased bread pan(s). Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool bread in pans for approximately 10 minutes before removing bread to cool on racks.
Store one day before slicing.
Be sure pans are well greased.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: In a saucepan combine chocolate chips and margarine.
Stir over low heat until chips are dissolved.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
In a medium bowl combine flour, nuts and chocolate mixture. Mix well.
Shape 1 teaspoon of mixture around unwrapped candy Kisses, covering the Kiss completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Remove and cool.

title: ole buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs, slowly adding sugar.
Add flour, then buttermilk and then butter, all the while beating.
Add vanilla.
When all is well beaten, pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° to 350° until nicely browned on top and firm in center, approximately 45 minutes.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Grind cranberries and orange in food grinder.
Add sugar. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir jello into cranberry mixture. Chill.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine eggs, muffin mix, cream-style
and whole kernel corn, sour cream and butter or margarine. Spread in 11 x 7 x 1 3/4 baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 10 to 15 minutes more or till knife comes out clean. Makes 8 servings.

title: slaw
directions: Pour sugar over cabbage.
Mix oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and celery seed and pour over cabbage; add onion and pepper slices on top.
Let set 2 to 4 hours before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: good stuff salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Freeze at least 6 hours.
Take out of freezer at least 20 minutes before serving.
This is good used as a salad on a lettuce leaf, or as a dessert with a cookie.

title: baked salmon
directions: Skin one side of the salmon.
Tie a slice of bacon over the skinned side or with a larding needle, run a few fine strips of salt pork into the fish.
Butter a shallow baking dish; add shallots and place the salmon on top of them, skin side down.
Dot the fish with 4 tablespoons butter and bake it, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 15 minutes, basting several times with the pan juices.
Then add the wine vinegar and water to the pan and cook the fish another 15 minutes, still basting.
Remove the salmon to a hot platter; discard the bacon and keep the fish warm.
On top of the stove, dilute the pan juices with the dry white wine and stir in the creamed butter with the 2 teaspoons flour.
Simmer the sauce, stirring often, for 2 to 3 minutes; taste it for seasoning. Strain it and pour it over the salmon.
Serves four.

title: light herb chicken with mushroom sauce
directions: Spray a 2-quart casserole dish with cooking spray.
Sprinkle the poultry seasoning over the chicken; bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
In a nonstick skillet, saute the onion in red wine vinegar (no oil).
Add the soup and 2 cans of water.
Stir in pineapple tidbits and 1/2 of the pineapple juice.
Pour mixture over chicken; bake for 25 to 30 more minutes.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: quick no bake cookies
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.

title: lemonade icebox pie
directions: Combine sweetened, condensed milk with lemonade concentrate; mix in Cool Whip and pour into pie shell; refrigerate at least three hours before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: dole golden layer cake
directions: Combine undrained pineapple, whipped topping and pudding mix. Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut cake lengthwise in thirds.
Mix together 1/3 cup pineapple juice and almond extract and drizzle the cake with this mixture.
Spread 1/3 pudding mixture over bottom layer of cake.
Top with second layer.
Repeat layering, ending with pudding.
Chill 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds and garnish with pineapple slices, if desired.
Makes 12 servings. (Recipe from Dole.)

title: kitra's chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in broth and onion soup mix.
Add cream of chicken soup to broth and add parsley.
Cut tortillas across center, then crosswise to make 1 inch wide strips.
Separate strips, fan into liquid submerging each layer as entered.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour into 3 cake pans and bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spareribs "aloha"
directions: Cut every third rib about halfway through the strip.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Pour off fat.
Mix remaining ingredients and let stand to blend flavor.
Pour over ribs.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes, basting frequently to glaze ribs.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Use only wooden utensils and glass or ceramic containers. Acid in starter will corrode any metal with which it comes in contact.

title: natalie's taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Add taco seasoning per package directions.
Press crescent rolls into 9 inch or 10 inch pie pan.
Spread 1/2 of Fritos on top of crescent rolls.
Add hamburger mixture.
Put sour cream on top, then cheese, and the rest of the Fritos.
Bake 20 - 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes.

title: any occasion cookie
directions: In large bowl, mix cool whip and egg.
At this time a few drops of food coloring may be added.
Add cake mix slowly and dust your hands with powdered sugar and make each a size of unshelled walnut.
Roll each cookie in powdered sugar, and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: rotini stir-fry
directions: Prepare rotini as package directs; drain.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Add chicken, broccoli, carrots and onion.
Cook and stir over medium heat until broccoli is tender and crisp.
Add water, bouillon and tarragon; cook and stir until chicken is cooked through.
Add hot, cooked rotini and Parmesan cheese; toss to coat. Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat in 1/2 x 2-inch pieces and brown.
Cook ingredients over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Then add broth and stir flour into skillet to make gravy.
Stir cream into meat.
Cook for 45 minutes before serving.

title: summer squash
directions: Brown bacon, remove all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Saute onion. Place flour, salt and pepper in a sack.
Add squash and shake well until coated.
Then put squash in a greased casserole.
Add soup to bacon and onions and pour over squash.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: patty cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted butter and one egg.
Pat down in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar in mixer.
Pour into pan, covering cake mix batter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Finely chop dried beef, pepper and onion.
Mix into cream cheese.
Shape into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Roll balls in ground walnuts.
Serve with any kind of crackers.
Great for parties or holiday guests.

title: carolina packers hot dog spaghetti
directions: Melt onions in 4 tablespoons oil until clear.
Add all ingredients except hot dogs and cook for 4 hours on low heat, stirring occasionally.
Cut hot dogs into 1/2-inch circles and add to sauce. Add 3 cups water and continue to cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes or until boiling.
Boil spaghetti in water until done and add to sauce. Serve hot and enjoy.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter
and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add mashed bananas.
Add dry ingredients alternately with
milk.
Pour
into well-greased baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugars until fluffy. Stir in vanilla and add eggs; beat well.
Sift in flour; mix well. Add oatmeal, stirring until all is blended.
Add butterscotch (pecans and coconut, if desired).
Cover cookie sheets with foil and drop cookies.
Bake 9 1/2 to
10 minutes.
When done, cookies will slide off foil.
Makes 100 (2-inch) cookies.

title: alice cann's three-bean salad
directions: Drain beans; mix with pepper and onion.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar together and pour over beans.
Add salt and pepper, then refrigerate in closed container.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender and blend until thoroughly mixed.

Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean when inserted in center of pie. This pie provides its own crust, coconut custard filling and coconut topping.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to box.
Bake in an oblong pan.
Mix the remaining ingredients and put over hot cake.

title: chicken on linguini
directions: Slice chicken breasts into 1/4-inch pieces.
Saute chicken in small amount of olive oil 5 to 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, wine and seasonings, except parsley.
Cover and cook over medium heat until chicken is cooked through (8 to 12 minutes).
Spoon over linguini and sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown hamburger in pan with finely cut onion.
A little cooking oil may be added.
When brown, sprinkle chili powder on top.
Also, add salt; mix.
Add tomato juice, sugar and beans. Heat; serve with crackers or add 1 pint cooked macaroni instead. Navy beans may be used instead of kidney beans.

title: salsa chicken(low-fat)
directions: Lightly brown chicken in frying pan with nonstick spray on medium to medium-high heat.
Turn down to simmer and add 1 jar of salsa (choose degree of spiciness desired).
Simmer in covered pan for 30 minutes.
Serve with plain or Spanish rice and a salad.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Mix Jello and 3 cups water with strained juice.
Heat up and let jell, soft.
Add Cool Whip and drained strawberries.
Spray a large 9 X 13 baking dish with Pam.
Pinch angel cakes into bite size pieces.
Pour Jello mix over it.
Top with whole fresh strawberries.
Let chill.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Stir together 1/2 cup sugar and gelatin in small saucepan. Blend egg yolks, water and lemon juice; stir into sugar mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture boils.
Stir in lemon peel.
Place pan in bowl of ice and water or chill in the refrigerator, stirring occasionally until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until foamy.
Beat in sugar (1/2 cup), 1 tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until stiff and glossy.
DO NOT UNDERBEAT! Fold lemon mixture into meringue.
Pile into baked pie shell. Chill at least 3 hours or until set.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish, place all ingredients in alternate layers starting with chicken and ending with bread crumbs. Dot with butter. Bake 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: a piece of heaven
directions: Mix margarine, flour and chopped nuts.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip and spread on top of crust.
Mix together instant pudding and milk and spread on the cheese.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours.

title: leg of lamb
directions: Cut five slits in meat.
Insert garlic.
Combine salt, pepper, thyme and garlic powder.
Rub over meat.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Broil 5 to 6 inches from heat until browned.
Turn and brown other side.
Set oven at 350°.

title: farmer's spoon bread
directions: Put cornmeal in a large bowl. Stir in boiling water.
Continue to stir until cool to prevent lumping.
Blend in butter and egg yolks.
Stir in buttermilk, salt, sugar, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold into cornmeal mixture.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve at once with butter. Makes 8 servings.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine cooking oil, beef and onion in skillet.
Cook until meat is lightly browned.
Drain and add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cut cheese into thin strips and spread over meat.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 30 minutes until biscuits are golden brown.

title: christmas hum dingers
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Melt over low heat.
Add dates and cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove from stove and add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Shape into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: snackin' s'more bars
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups of cake mix with margarine, milk, honey and eggs, mixing just until moist.
Add remaining cake mix.
In a saucepan, melt chips and shortening.
Pour first batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spoon chocolate over top and marble with knife.
Put marshmallows on top and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool and cut bars.

title: gator chorizo(sausage)
directions: Mix and work all ingredients together, except meats.
Then mix in meats and work it with your hands to mix thoroughly.
The vinegar and sherry "cures" the meat and prevents spoilage.
Cover and refrigerate.
Let season for at least 3 days before using.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease lightly 2 cookie sheets.
Beat egg whites stiff; slowly add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Then fold in chocolate chips.
Place small spoonfuls on cookie sheet 5 across in 8 rows.
Place pan in oven.
Shut off heat and leave overnight.
Makes about 80 cookies.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix flour, cocoa, sugar, soda and salt together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make 3 holes; put oil in one, vanilla in one and vinegar in one.
Then pour cold water over all this.
Mix all up and bake in 350° oven.

title: grilled peaches with raspberry puree
directions: Process berries and lemon juice in blender or food processor until smooth.
Strain puree and discard seeds.
Cover and chill. Cut 1 (18 x 18-inch) sheet of foil.
Place peach halves, cut side up, on foil.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; spoon evenly into center of each peach half.
Sprinkle with flavoring.
Dot with margarine. Fold foil over peaches and loosely seal.
Place on grill rack over medium coals and cook 15 minutes or until peaches are thoroughly heated.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Cut vegetables real fine or shred.
Mix all vegetables together; set aside.

title: chocolate chip-cookie bar
directions: Cream together margarine, sugars, salt and eggs.
Add vanilla and chips; mix well.
Gently stir in flour and baking soda. Spread onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 20 squares.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Blend lemon juice and blueberries with Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans and chill.

title: glorified rice
directions: Cook and drain white rice.
Mix rice and drained pineapple together.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours to blend well.

title: apple crisp
directions: Cover bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with apples.
Mix all remaining ingredients together and cover apples.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pineapple rolls
directions: Trim crusts from bread and flatten bread with rolling pin. Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Add egg yolk, vanilla and pineapple.
Spread mixture thinly on bread.
Roll up and cut rolls in halves or thirds.
Brush with melted butter and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Lift off cookie sheet and cool.
Don't eat hot, they will burn your mouth!!!!

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers, onions and cabbage together. Put in kettle and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and add other ingredients.
Boil about 30 minutes.
Put in jars and seal. Makes about 8 pints.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a skillet, brown the beef and onion.
Place the mixture in the bottom of casserole dish.
Add the vegetables next and cover with mashed potatoes.
Top with grated cheese, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven until warmed through and the top is browned. Serves 4 to 6.

title: deanne's wonderful crabmeat salad
directions: Mix crabmeat, onions, spices, and mayonnaise in bowl. Continue adding ranch salad dressing and mayonnaise until desired consistency and taste.
Let chill overnight for best results. Serve on crackers for great finger food.

title: angel corn muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk. Bake in greased muffin pans, 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: diet salad dressing
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix sugar, mustard, vinegar, salt and butter together.
Stir together with first mixture.
Cook over slow flame, stirring constantly.
When thick, gradually add milk and continue to cook mixture.
When slightly thickened, remove from heat.
If mixture becomes lumpy, you may strain and store in pint jar in refrigerator until needed.

title: no name cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Next, take the peach slices and place on top of the cake mix. Combine peach syrup, cream cheese and sugar. Mix well. Finally, drop the cream cheese mixture by the spoonful all over the cake mix. Bake according to the mix directions. Let cool. Spread whipped topping on top and sprinkle cinnamon. Serve cool. DELICIOUS!

title: meatball vegetable soup
directions: Mix hamburg, onion, salt and pepper.
Make into small balls. Brown in butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Tips:

A combination of one or more of the following can be added to the baked potato pulp to create new interest: minced green onions, chives or fried onion rings, chopped green peppers or avocados, diced ham or bacon bits, curry powder and chopped, cooked shrimp; sauteed mushrooms.

title: zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in slices.
Boil in salted water until soft. Drain well and mash.
Add cheese, olives, eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Put in a baking dish and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Test like custard.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Melt margarine and add to mixture. Pour fruit into pan (glass baking dish can also be used) and pour mixture over fruit.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: mom schroeder's rice pudding
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into ovenproof baking bowl. Bake at 350°.
Skin will form on top.
Turn the skin under, repeating for a total of 4 times.
Leave the fifth skin (this should take about 1 hour).

title: confetti mexican salad
directions: In large bowl, combine spinach, onions, tomatoes, and corn; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine chilli powder, garlic powder, and cumin; blend well.
Add pork; toss to coat.
In medium skillet, heat oil over high heat.
Saute pork until golden brown and thoroughly cooked.
Stir in orange and lime juices.
Spoon mixture over vegetables; toss gently to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: caramelitas
directions: Melt together caramels and evaporated milk; set aside. Combine cake mix and margarine. Press 1/2 cake mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread caramel mixture over this. Spread remaining batter over top of caramel layer, spreading evenly.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool slightly. Refrigerate 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla; beat together.
Add zucchini, nuts and pineapple; mix well.
Spray 2 loaf pans with Pam.
Divide batter evenly between the 2 pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked apple squares
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy.

title: veggie macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni, drain and rinse with cold water to cool. In bowl, combine macaroni, tomato, peas, cheese, celery, egg and onions. Pour dressing over mixture and coat.

title: banana pudding
directions: Reserve 1 banana and 10 to 12 vanilla wafers for garnish.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta until chewy.
Add remaining ingredients including juices from mushrooms and artichokes.
May add anything you wish. Best when chilled overnight.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice to use later with water).
Heat water to boiling; add jello and when dissolved, add 1 cup juice and/or water.
Let set to a jelly like consistency.
Add cottage cheese, salad dressing and pineapple.
Stir well.
Place in mold and set in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: honey in a stew, beef - that is!
directions: Simmer bacon in a little water (about 10 minutes); drain and dry. Cut in 1/2 inch pieces. Place bacon in heavy skillet and fry until crisp. Remove bacon. Coat the beef pieces with flour and after adding a little oil to bacon fat, brown beef fairly well. Transfer the browned beef and bacon pieces to whatever large pot you will cook it in over direct heat. A heavy deep pot with cover is best. Add a little of the wine to the skillet where the meat was browned; swish it around to get it all out and empty in big pot with meat. Add beef bouillon, tomato paste, salt and pepper and garlic. Pour in enough wine to cover meat. Place over direct heat and bring up to a simmer. Cover and cook over low heat 3 to 4 hours. Peel onions and cut in coarse pieces. Peel and cut (coarsely) a few carrots. Drain mushrooms well (retain liquid) and wash thoroughly. Cut up and saute in a little butter. When the stew has cooked at least 1 1/2 hours, add the vegetables and liquid. If a lot of the liquid has cooked out of the stew, you can add more of the canned bouillon and more wine as needed. Simmer until all ingredients are tender.

title: three bean sausage chili
directions: Add water to cover. Cook onions until tender. Add peppers and garlic and cook

5 minutes. Brown pork and sausage in 2 or 3 batches and drain fat. Mix meats and chili mixture in pot and cook 1 minute. Add tomatoes and beans and bring to boil. Simmer 20 minutes. (Add water to cover before simmering.)

title: hand lotion
directions: Add all ingredients into a large mixing bowl and beat until well blended.
Velvacol and glycerin can be purchased from a pharmacist.

title: turtle ice cream pie - easy!
directions: Make brownies according to directions and bake in a 9-inch pie pan.
Cool.
Spread ice cream over brownies.
Slowly melt caramel and milk until creamy.
"Swizzle" over ice cream and sprinkle nuts as soon as possible to stick to the caramel before cooling.
Freeze and serve.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except grated cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex dish (grease pan).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven and cover top with cheese.
Return to oven just until cheese melts.

title: lumpia
directions: Saute garlic and onion in oil.
Add shrimp, pork and seasonings; brown well.
Add vegetables.
Cook until half done. Drain and cool.
Drop 2 tablespoons of mixture in center of lumpia wrapper; fold over, fold in ends and roll.
Seal ends with egg. We like to dip in Sweet Sour Sauce!

title: spinach pecan pesto
directions: In a food processor, place each ingredient one at a time and puree it so that finally a loose paste is formed (if the mixture gets too thick during this process, then add some of the olive oil to loosen it up).
Makes approximately 2 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate chip bundt cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs and buttermilk together. Stir in the chocolate chips. Spray the Bundt pan with Pam liberally. Sprinkle chopped pecans in bottom of pan. Pour cake batter on top of pecans. Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°. Check with toothpick for doneness. Let cool.

title: broccoli chicken bake
directions: Layer broccoli first (if fresh, steam 5 minutes first), then layer chicken, then Velveeta cheese.
Stir together other ingredients, except onion rings; spoon over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour French fried onions on top; bake 10 minutes longer.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Melt butter, milk and chips in a double boiler.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Put marshmallows and nuts in large bowl.
Pour chocolate mixture over nuts and marshmallows.
Stir until well covered.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Chill until set.
Cut in squares.

title: phyllis' caramel popcorn
directions: Mix popcorn and nuts in lightly greased roasting pan.
Add to margarine the brown sugar and honey.
Bring to boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir until coated.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool completely, then store in airtight container.
Great for Christmas gifts or parties!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs; add sugar, oil and vanilla. Beat until creamy; add in dry ingredients.
Makes 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until done.

title: salty pickles
directions: Bring to boil and pour over pickles that are already in the jar.
Do not cook the pickles.

title: herb marinade mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Brush on seafood, beef or poultry. Marinate in the refrigerator for 2 hours prior to grilling.
Herb Marinade may also be brushed on meat during grilling for additional flavor.

title: brownies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add syrup, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Bone and skin chicken breasts. Combine egg with 1 tablespoon lemon juice. Combine flour, garlic powder and paprika. Dip chicken in egg mixture, then into flour mixture. Brown chicken in margarine. Dissolve bouillon in hot water. Add remaining lemon juice. Cover skillet and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos and set aside.
Cream together margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Mix in milk, pudding and Cool Whip. Layer alternately the cookie crumbs and the creamed mixture into a plant pot.
Begin and end with the cookie crumbs.
Place silk flower stems in pot and serve.

title: cream of cheddar soup
directions: Cook bacon; crumble.
Set aside.
In medium saucepan, melt butter over medium-high heat.
Add celery and leeks.
Cook, stirring often, 8 to 10 minutes, or until tender.
Stir in flour, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add chicken stock.
Stir constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Reduce to medium heat.
Continue cooking and stirring for 1 minute.
Alternately stir milk and half and half into mix.
Cover and heat through, about 10 minutes.
Reduce to low heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
To Serve:
Stir in the crumbled bacon and ladle into cups.
Add garnish.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli 1/2 time of directions.
Drain and set aside on paper towel.
Melt oleo in heavy, ovenproof saucepan.
Saute onion and celery until soft.
Add mushrooms and cook 3 to 4 minutes. Add soup and cheese, mixing well after each.
Add broccoli and mix lightly.
Cover and place in 300° oven until cheese melts, about 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Heat butter and milk.
Mix flour (1 cup), yeast, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Add together with milk, butter, yeast, sugar, salt and 1 cup flour along with egg.
Mix by hand 2 minutes.
Mix in flour.
Let rise until double.
Punch down.
Shape and let rise again.
Bake at 350°.

title: hot fudge chocolate sauce
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa.
Add water and cook 3 minutes, stirring all the time.
It will get thick.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Continue to stir until butter is mixed in the sauce.

title: gold sauce
directions: Cream butter and sugar over low heat.
Add milk and cook very carefully for short time.
Remove from heat and add mixture slowly to 1 beaten egg.
Add vanilla.
Excellent on a piece of leftover cake.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, milk and oil together.
Add cheese to flour and stir.
Add egg mixture and mix to a soft consistency.
Pour into small muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Makes 24 small muffins.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix; use 1 teaspoon per hot cup of water.

title: corn bread muffins
directions: Grease muffin pans or an 8-inch skillet.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium mixing bowl, sift together corn meal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add buttermilk and water; stir until smooth.
