Stir in egg and oil, just until all ingredients are blended.
Do not overbeat.

title: arkansas trash
directions: Mix all box mixes together.
Mix seasonings with oil and pour over box mix. Place in large pan; bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except potato chips.
Bake in casserole dish at 375° for 1 hour. Crumble potato chips over baked casserole. Return to oven for 15 minutes or until brown on top.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients. Add eggs and oil.
Stir until moistened.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in centers of cakes comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Make your own frosting or use can of cream cheese frosting.
Frost generously between cooled layers and on sides and top of cake.
Enjoy!

title: pork chops and gravy in crock-pot
directions: Brown pork chops on medium heat on stove.
Mix soups together in a bowl, adding the Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Spoon some of the soup mix into the crock-pot, then add a layer of pork chops, continuing until done.
Let cook for 4 hours or until meat is done.
Serve with mashed potatoes and use the soup mixture as a delicious gravy.

title: super-rich cocoa mix
directions: Mix well. Serve 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Place pork chops in glass casserole dish and top with vegetables.
Pour tomato soup over chops and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown steak in oil, then add onion.
Add tomato sauce, mushrooms, water, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce; simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add small amount of sauce to 1 cup of sour cream; blend well, then add to meat and sauce.
May be thickened with a little Wondra flour.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients and blend in milk.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, Karo, butter and pecans.
Bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Slice bananas, strawberries and pineapple.
Mix together with peach pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix dressings and place chicken in pan.
Marinate overnight. Grill or bake.

title: cherry salad
directions: Bring water to a boil; mix with Jell-O and stir in pie filling, pineapple and nuts.
Firm in refrigerator.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve orange jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add frozen orange juice and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water, mandarin oranges and juice and pineapple tidbits and juice. Pour into dish and mold.

title: banana-oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour with salt, soda, nutmeg and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, beat margarine, sugar and egg until fluffy.
Beat in bananas and vanilla until smooth.
Gradually stir in flour mixture and oats until well combined.
Refrigerate dough for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In casserole dish, layer oleo, asparagus, potato chips and sliced eggs at least 2 times.
Top with cheese and milk.
Pour juice over top of casserole.
Bake at 300° until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Grease casserole.
Cook the onion in the oleo.
Combine the soup and Cheez Whiz.
Blend all ingredients carefully.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: leek and potato soup
directions: Melt butter in a large boiler.
Trim roots and about 1/2 greens off leeks.
Slice leeks in very thin slices and saute in butter at medium heat for about 5 minutes.
Cube potatoes.
Add broth, milk and potatoes to leeks.
Add other ingredients.
Use additional milk and broth by halves if more liquid level is desired.
Cover and cook over medium heat until potatoes are done (usually about 20 minutes).
Serves 4.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray a pizza pan with Pam and spread the cookie dough out on the pan. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until done. COOL in the refrigerator. Mix marshmallow cream and the cream cheese in a bowl; spread over the cooled cookie. Then top it with the fruit of your choice and then sprinkle shredded coconut over the fruit. Enjoy!!!

title: chicken with a twist
directions: Cook the macaroni according to package directions; drain and cool.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Put rhubarb in a big pan.
Pour sugar on top and stir, making sure all pieces are covered.
Let stand for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Cook on top of stove for 12 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Stir well.
Put in small canning jars.

title: lentil soup
directions: Combine lentils, water, salt, and sausage in a Dutch oven or soup pot.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to medium.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add broth and continue cooking for another 15 minutes.
Add potato soup, butter, and tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, for about 30 minutes or until lentils are tender. Add water or more chicken broth, if soup gets too thick.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix margarine and cream cheese together.
Fold in Cool Whip. Mix pudding and milk.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Line the bottom of a new 8-inch or 10-inch flowerpot with foil.
Start with layer of crushed Oreo cookies, then layer of pudding mixture. Continue layering being sure to end up with Oreos on top.
Add silk flowers to pot.
Use flower garden spade for spoon to serve. Attach note to plant:

title: ranger dans
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and brown sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well then add rolled oats and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: florida panhandle oyster stew
directions: Carefully remove flecks of shells from oysters, if any.
Place oysters in their own juice in large saucepan, bring to a boil until oysters curl around their edges.
Add evaporated milk and water.
Bring to a boil again.
Do not scald.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan and let simmer for 30 minutes.
Add chicken and heat until warm.
Layer spaghetti sauce and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well. Blend in potatoes and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Add alternately with milk.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: apple crisp
directions: *Raisin and spice or cinnamon and spice flavored.

title: one dish meal
directions: You also need a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: bean curd and kim chee soup
directions: Rinse pork and cut into thin slices. Marinate with the soy sauce, cornstarch and pepper powder.
Rinse and dry bean curd, then cut into cubes.
Heat 1 teaspoon oil to saute ginger. Pour in water (4 to 6 bowl fulls) and bring to a boil.
Add Kim chee, pork slices and bean curd.
Bring all to boil, then let simmer until soup is rich. Add salt to taste and serve.

title: opossum and chestnuts
directions: Skin opossum, remove gland and entrails.
Scrape clean and scald in boiling water.
Rub inside and out with salt and pepper; set in cool place.
Stuff with chestnuts, applesauce and bread crumbs in equal proportions.
Cover with slice of sweet potato, 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup lemon juice.
Bake in butter and baste often until tender.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Put the 2 cups of salt in 1 gallon of water and boil.
Pour over cucumbers while hot.
Let stand 5 days.
Wash off.
Add the alum to 1 gallon water and boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Take out; wash in boiling water.
Drain good.
Add sugar and vinegar; boil this.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours. Second day, drain vinegar off and reheat.
Put cucumbers in jars and seal in water bath 5 minutes.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: The night before serving, layer lettuce, onion, bacon pieces and cauliflower into a large bowl that has a tight fitting lid (or use plastic wrap).
Sprinkle sugar over top layer.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle cheese all over.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Select 6 smooth round tomatoes.
Scoop out the pulp and pass through sieve.
Put in frying pan with chopped onion, bread crumbs and egg.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
Remove from heat and add grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Fill the tomatoes.
Sprinkle with extra bread crumbs and cheese. Bake until tender.

title: fat ladies
directions: Cut cookie dough and press into 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until brown.
Cool slightly.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Melt caramels and cream over low heat.
Spread on top of cookie bar.
Top with pecans and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast packet from hot roll mix package in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine pumpkin, egg and 2 tablespoons sugar; mix well.
Add yeast; stir in flour packet from hot roll mix package to make a stiff dough.
Place dough in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 45 minutes, or until doubled in bulk.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash and soak red kidney beans overnight.
Drain and put them into an iron pot.
Cover with water.
Bring to a full boil over high heat.
Stir well and let beans settle.
Add ham hock, onion, garlic cloves, celery and green pepper.
Season with salt and pepper.
Reduce heat to medium and cook about 3 hours until tender.
Adjust seasoning.
Slice meat and serve with beans over freshly cooked rice.

title: broccoli and cauliflower melt
directions: Steam broccoli and cauliflower until done (slightly firm). Drain and place in a single layer in a baking dish.
Top with cottage cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until melted and bubbly.

title: rice primavera
directions: In large skillet, cook mushrooms, onion, celery, bouillon and seasoning in margarine.
Add rice, cheese, peas and carrots; cook 5 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the margarine and chocolate in the
small	saucepan
over	low heat, stirring constantly. Beat the eggs with a fork in a small bowl.
Stir in the syrup, sugar and vanilla extract.
Pour this mixture into the saucepan
and mix well with the chocolate.
Pour the filling into a pie
crust. Bake
to
minutes
until set.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Then add other ingredients.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cook broccoli, put broccoli in the bottom of a buttered casserole, then layer chicken pieces on top of broccoli. Then pour soups, curry powder and milk (which has been heated together).
Can put bread crumbs on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: jerky
directions: Slice meat into thin strips.
Marinate meat overnight.
Hang meat on toothpicks across oven rack.
Dry 6 hours at 150° to 160° with oven door cracked open.
Let hang 6 more hours without heat.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Marinate tenderloin in equal parts olive oil, Worcestershire and soy sauce.
Before placing in marinade, sprinkle with lemon pepper and marinate for 24 hours.
Remove from marinade and dry off with paper towel; sprinkle again with lemon pepper.
Place on broiler pan.
Bake 45 minutes or longer at 375° in preheated oven.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Put half the butter in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save rest of butter for top.
Mix other ingredients together; put in pan. Cover with 2 cups cornflakes; drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour with cover on.

title: turkey-fruit salad
directions: In salad bowl, combine spinach and celery.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Core apples; cut into wedges.
Dip apples in reserved pineapple juice.
Arrange pineapple chunks, apple wedges, orange sections and turkey atop spinach.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash red beans and soak in water overnight.
This will make your beans more tender.
If you don't have the time to soak overnight, that's okay.
Cook sausage, drain fat and set aside. In heavy pot, put beans and fill pot with water about 1 1/2 inches below top.
Put all your spices in and sausage and bring to a boil.
Turn to about medium (needs to be continuous boil).
As it needs water, add.
Cook several hours, until beans are tender and juice is thick like a gravy.
Cook amount of rice you need. Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbecue for a crowd
directions: Brown ground beef.
Pour off excess drippings.
Add onions and saute with beef.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer over low heat. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: here's what cooking 49er's
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread into 13 x 9-inch baking dish greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares and dust with powdered sugar.

title: easy dinner biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased muffin pans and bake at 350° until done and light brown on top.
Similar to rolls.

title: lemon lush
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and nuts. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mixture in pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix Eagle brand milk and lemon juice, pour over graham cracker crust. Slice bananas over milk mixture. Drain pineapple and pour over bananas. Top with Cool Whip and garnish with pecans and cherries. Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter, milk and salt to soft ball stage (234° to 238°).
Add peanut butter just before removing from fire.
Do not stir.
Cool to room temperature.
Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture is creamy, thick and will hold its shape when dropped from a teaspoon.
Pour into well buttered shallow pan.
Cut into squares.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch casserole. Add cheese, milk and butter.
Break up Ritz crackers and mix them in casserole.
Cook uncovered in 375° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw loaf of bread (on a cookie sheet or overnight in the refrigerator).
When thawed, roll it out onto a greased cookie sheet.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve
strawberry
gelatin in 3/4 cup boiling water; add strawberries.
Stir
until	thawed; add pineapple, cut up bananas and 1/4 cup pecans.
Chill to thicken. Spread softened Cool Whip on top and	sprinkle
with	rest
of
nuts. I double this; it's so good.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Leave on cookie sheet until cool, then remove.

title: stuffed jalapenos
directions: Cut off tip of pepper (leave stem in place).
Using a narrow knife or very narrow potato peeler, remove the inside of pepper. Stuff pepper with cream cheese.
Wrap pepper and cream cheese with sausage and roll in finely ground Stove Top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Combine chicken, sour cream, chilies, 1 can soup and 1 c. grated cheese.
Spoon generous amount of this filling down the center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in a greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Take the remaining 2 cans of soup and stir together to soften. Spread over tortillas.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: avocado party mix
directions: To the sour cream, add soup mix and mayonnaise.
Mash the avocado separately until smooth.
Mix with sour cream mixture and chill for several hours.

title: gail's hushpuppies
directions: Mix well
with spoon, onion, bell pepper and corn.
Add cornmeal, flour, egg and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls in hot oil.
Cook until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: jambalaya
directions: Fix chicken.
Fry sausage; save drippings in the pan.
Brown rice in drippings, then add chicken and broth.
Brown vegetables in oil.
Add to other mixture.
Add Worcestershire, Tabasco and liquid smoke.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: oreo cream pie
directions: Coarsely chop 10 cookies; set aside.
Finely roll 26 cookies. Combine the cookie crumbs (from 26) and the margarine.
Press evenly on top, bottom and sides of 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Chill while preparing filling.

title: banana brazil nut cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder. In a larger bowl, cream together butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition. Beat in bananas.
Add flour mixture, buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Stir in nuts.
Turn batter into 2 greased and lightly floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until tester inserted near the center comes out clean. Let stand in pans on wire rack for 5 minutes.
Turn out.
Turn top side up.
Cool.
Spread whipped cream on top and sides with remaining cream.
Slice.
Serve.

title: rice pudding from the riviera hotel
directions: Pour rice slowly into rapidly boiling, slightly salted water in a large pot.
Do not stir.
Cover tightly and cook exactly 7 minutes at which time all the water will be absorbed and the rice will be slightly undone.
Add the milk and butter.
Stir a little. Bring to a boil, cover and cook slowly over a low flame for 1 hour.

title: sugar cookies (old fashioned)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add butter.
Mix until this is fine, like corn meal.
Then add egg, cream and vanilla which have been well beaten.
Knead dough until it is all in a firm ball.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mash fruit up. Mix all together and freeze. Makes 6 quarts.

title: lemon dressing
directions: Prepare a couple of days ahead.
Keep refrigerated and shake up once in a while and before applying to salad.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Stir in flour.
Mix in 3/4 cup finely chopped nuts.
Mix with fingers and squeeze together.
Chill dough.

title: rhubarb jell
directions: Cook rhubarb and sugar over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O and Kool-Aid.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Cook squash and onion together; drain well.
Add all ingredients, except for corn meal.
If not dry enough, add more bread crumbs.
Roll into long shapes, then roll in cornmeal. Deep fat fry in oil or use a deep skillet with oil.
Drain on paper towels and serve.

title: raspberry filled almond muffins
directions: Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners.
Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add the milk, butter or margarine, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Mix until just moistened.
Half fill the muffin cups with batter. Spoon 1 teaspoon raspberry preserves into the center. Top with remaining batter.
Place blanched whole almonds on top of batter.
Press in lightly.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 400° for 12 to 20 minutes until golden. Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan.

title: english caramel icing
directions: Melt butter (margarine) in saucepan. Add brown sugar and milk. Heat to a boiling point, stirring constantly. Boil gently 5 minutes, while stirring. Cool 10 minutes.
Blend in powdered sugar and vanilla. Beat until it is ready to spread.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve with shrimp or oysters.

title: carrot and green bean scallop
directions: Melt butter.
Cook onion in it slightly.
Add flour and seasonings, blending well.
Gradually add milk and vegetable juice, stirring while cooking.
When slightly thickened, add beaten eggs; cook 1/2 minute, stirring constantly.
Do not let sauce boil after adding eggs.
Add cheese, then vegetables.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix juice with cornstarch; heat to thicken.
Add butter and spices; mix lightly with apples.
Fill pastry lined pan.
Cover with top crust (vented or slit).
Bake at 450° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: In a medium saucepan over medium heat, combine condensed milk, butterscotch chips and white chocolate chips.
Stir constantly until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and rum flavorings.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, 30 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Whisk cream cheese and mayonnaise until well blended.
Add pecans, green olives, olive juice and pepper.
Mix well; let set in the refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.

title: turkey loaves with stuffing
directions: In a medium bowl combine turkey, oats, water, Italian seasoning and soup mix.
In small bowl, combine stuffing and water; cover and set aside.
Coat 4 (6 ounce) custard cups with nonstick vegetable spray.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Place chicken, bouillon cubes, water and vegetables in a large Dutch oven or stew pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add frozen noodles and stir to separate.
Return to a boil and cook 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer gently 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: green fried tomatoes
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Pour milk into another bowl. Put frying pan on medium heat.
Let pan get hot, then pour in oil to depth of 2-inches.
Dip tomatoes in milk, then into flour mixture.
Repeat.
Fry in oil until golden brown.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until moist.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and walnuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and place in 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: country potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Put potatoes into a large bowl.
In a small bowl, mix soup and butter; add cheese, sour cream and onion.
Stir into potatoes and add salt and pepper.
Put into the baking dish.
Crush cornflakes, stir butter into them and sprinkle them onto casserole.
Bake for about 45 minutes.

title: spinach deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except eggs.
Fold in eggs and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until top is bubbly and slightly browned.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cornmeal rolls(harriet's)
directions: Cook cornmeal and 2 cup water like mush (5 to 10 minutes). While still hot add butter or margarine, sugar and salt.
When cool add eggs, yeast mixture and enough flour, as you knead, until stiff and does not stick to board.
Let rise until double.
Punch down; let rise.
Form into rolls.
Let rise again (3 rises).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Clean broccoli and cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Steam in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Do not drain.
Set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour to make a roux.
Cook 2 to 4 minutes.
Add chicken stock, stirring with wire whip and bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low.
Add broccoli, half and half, salt and pepper.
Heat, but do not boil.
Makes 8 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, butter and flour.
Add buttermilk and juice.
Bake in a 9-inch pie shell at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: frozen pea salad
directions: I serve this in a small crystal punch bowl.

title: michigan mix
directions: A great snack.
Mix desired amount of each.

title: peachy smoked pork roast
directions: In blender, combine the ingredients; blend until smooth. Marinate pork in half of this mixture overnight in refrigerator. Prepare grill until medium hot and place a drip pan over coals. Place pork on grill over drip pan; baste often with marinade until internal temperature reaches 155°, about 60 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes to reach 160°.
Slice thinly and serve with reserved peach sauce.

title: baconed snack
directions: Cut bacon slices into thirds and fry over medium heat, turning, until crisp.
Spread the cut sides of each muffin with approximately two tablespoons of sauce.
Top each muffin with three pieces bacon and Mozzarella cheese.
Dust with oregano and drizzle each pizza with about 3 or 4 drops of salad oil.
Broil until the sandwiches are heated and cheese is melted.
Makes 12 small pizzas.

title: tropical blizzard
directions: In pitcher, combine pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.
Stir in club soda and ice cubes.
Top each serving with rainbow or orange sherbet.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, cheese, crumbs, and butter.
Place broccoli/chicken in the bottom of pan, pour soup mixture over the top.
Brown cracker crumbs in butter.
Put cheese on top of soup mixture; put cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: tuna or salmon rice pie
directions: Bring rice to boil in salted water, cover and simmer 14 minutes.
Mix with fork and stir in margarine and 1 egg.
Place in 9 inch pie pan sprayed with vegetable spray.
Press against sides and bottom of pan to make crust.
Spread tuna or salmon evenly over rice.
Heat milk and peas to a simmer, add seasonings.
Beat remaining egg.
Gradually stir into milk mixture.
Pour over tuna. Layer slices of
cheese over top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: bubble buns
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a small bowl, combine cinnamon and sugar.
In another bowl, melt the margarine.
Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Roll each piece of biscuit into a small ball.
Dip into the margarine and roll in the cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Place 4 pieces into a muffin pan (I use paper muffin cups).
Four pieces will be in each cup.
Do not worry about how the pieces are setting in the muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 17 minutes (I baked mine 15 minutes).
Enjoy!
These are very rich and should be eaten while they are warm.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar, milk, salt and vanilla and stir.
Pour into a single pan or individual custard cups. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cook for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves eight.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, onion, rice, salt and pepper.
Roll into balls about the size of walnuts.
Cook in tomato soup mixture with water 15 minutes in pressure cooker.
If you cook this in a saucepan, add more water and cook longer until done.

title: ele salad
directions: Mix and press first 3 ingredients into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool before adding next layer, about 30 minutes.
Mix and spread next 4 ingredients over first layer. Chill until set.
Mix last 3 ingredients together and put on top of other layers.
Chill again.
Makes a lot!

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and rinse them.
Cut them widthwise into thin slices, but not all the way through (like you would slice bread, but not all the way through). Put potatoes in a baking dish and fan them slightly.
Sprinkle them with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle on herbs. Bake at 425° for about 50 minutes. Remove from oven. Sprinkle with cheeses. Bake another 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and potatoes are soft inside.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Beat egg whites very stiffly.
(Should look like white icing.)
Add sugar gradually while beating.
Add vanilla and fold in pecans.
Drop onto cookie sheet by teaspoon. Turn oven to 275° and cook for 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Shred onions and smash finely.
Take the pulp from the onions, add tomato sauce and A.1. and stir together.
Recommend on chicken, lamb or beef ribs.

title: cherry fluff salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Set overnight in refrigerator.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Place scoops of ice cream into punch bowl.
Add mixture of punch and juices.
Stir in ginger ale gently.
Yields 25 servings.

title: meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine bread crumbs, sage, pepper, egg whites, onion, garlic and milk.
Add meat and mix lightly.
Place in a shallow baking pan or loaf pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and carefully drain fat from pan.

title: german chocolate cream pie
directions: Melt chocolate and two teaspoons of milk over low heat. Beat sugar
with
cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate.
Beat until
smooth.
Fold
in
Cool
Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about four hours.

title: salami wedges(appetizer)
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Spread on the salami slices; stack. Spread slices and top with a plain slice of salami.
Cover and chill.

title: green beans with mushrooms
directions: Wash beans; trim ends and remove strings.
Arrange beans in a steaming rack placed over boiling water; cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Plunge beans into cold water.
Drain and set aside.
Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Melt margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and garlic; cook, stirring constantly 3 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.
Add green beans, remaining ingredients.
Cook 3 minutes or until heated. Yields 4 servings.
Contains 93 calories.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine, then add brown sugar and mix.
Let it cool. Add eggs and blend well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts, chips and coconut.
Spread in greased pan and bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Take out when light brown and cut, when cool, into squares.

title: buttermilk cakespringfield, missouri
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in moderate oven at 350°.

title: old-fashion drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add vanilla.
Beat until fluffy. Sift into dry ingredients until creamy.
Mix together with milk, enough for soft dough.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or lightly browned.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters. Roll biscuit pieces in sugar and cinnamon.
Put in lightly greased Bundt pan.
Spread brown sugar on top.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: deep, dark, delicious cookies
directions: Preheat
oven to 350°.
Mix cocoa, flour, soda and salt in large mixing bowl;
set aside.
Blend butter and eggs until smooth; add vanilla and both sugars while continuing to blend. Gradually
add
dry
mixture.
Stir
in chips.
Drop by tablespoonfuls
onto
ungreased
cookie
sheets.
Bake
for 8 to 10 minutes.
Place on wire racks to cool.

title: frosty pitcher margaritas
directions: In saucer, dip rims of cocktail glasses in 1 tablespoon lime juice.
Dip in salt.
In blender container, combine remaining lime juice with sugar; blend well.
Add ice; blend until slushy.
Pour into 2-quart pitcher.
Stir in tequila and triple sec.
Serve in prepared glasses.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add okra and fry 5 minutes to take away the slime.
Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Remove cover and let simmer 5 minutes longer.

title: cottage cheese dill bread
directions: In a large bowl, soften yeast in water with pinch of sugar. When ready, add 1 1/2 cups flour and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Let rest 15 to 20 minutes. Work in remaining 1 1/2 cups flour. Add more if necessary to make a medium stiff dough.
On greased or floured board, knead until smooth. Shape into loaf. Place in greased or sprayed baking pan. Let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with flour.
Brown in oil in a Dutch oven. Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Pour mixture over chops.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: texas-style chili
directions: In large skillet, brown steak cubes and garlic in hot oil; drain off excess fat.
Stir in water, beef broth, sugar, oregano, cumin, salt and bay leaves.
Reduce heat, simmer, covered, until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in chili peppers and corn meal.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaves.
Serve over squares of corn bread, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Mix flour and soda.
Add to mixture.
Add M&M's.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until light brown around edges.
Yield:
about 4 dozen.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Butter bread and cut into cubes.
Line bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with bread; top with sausage, then cheese.
In a bowl, mix eggs, half and half, mustard and salt. Beat well and pour over sausage and cheese.
Leave in refrigerator at least 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crisp zucchini pancakes
directions: Put shredded zucchini in colander.
Sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon salt; set aside for 30 minutes.
Squeeze as much liquid as possible from zucchini with your hands; reserve.
Saute onions in hot butter in a skillet over medium-high heat until soft. Transfer reserved zucchini and onion to large bowl.
Stir in eggs, flour and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.

title: potato and broccoli supper
directions: Whip together the first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Season to taste.
Fold in 1/2 can of onions.
Spread potatoes in baking dish and form a shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Arrange broccoli in shell and sprinkle with remaining onions and cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer.
Yields 8 servings.

title: marinated baked fish
directions: In 12 x 7-inch baking dish, combine all ingredients except fish.
Add fish; marinate 1 hour.
Bake fish in marinade in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.
Yields 2 to 4 servings.

title: confetti bites
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet to form a crust.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, basil leaves and garlic powder.
Spread thinly over cooled crust.
Top with chopped vegetables.
Refrigerate until time to serve.
Cut in squares.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Gradually add sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and chocolate; mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, soda and salt together 3 times.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, a small amount at a time.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in 3 paper-lined 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans at 350° for about 3 minutes.
Frost with desired frosting.

title: bishop louis e. gelineau english tea cake
directions: Mix raisins, milk and enough water to barely cover in a saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Drain and allow to cool.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Lightly brown meat.
Add pepper and onions.
Cook until soft. Add chili sauce, catsup and relish.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: low-fat taco soup
directions: Mix all together except chips and cheese.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes or longer.
Serve with chips and shredded cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: danish puff
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Cut first 1/2 cup butter into first cup of flour.
Sprinkle with water and mix with fork.
Round into ball and divide in half.
Pat into 2 long strips 12x3 inches, 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Mix second 1/2 cup butter and water; bring to rolling boil; add almond and remove from heat. Stir in second cup of flour and keep from lumping.
wWen smooth and thick, add 1 egg at a time, beating until smooth.
Spread evenly over each pastry.
Bake 60 minutes or until topping is crisp and nicely browned.
Frost with powdered sugar icing and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix cream cheese with lemon juice and a little sugar.

title: escalopes de veau a la moutarde
directions: Place the scaloppine on a flat surface and pound with a flat metal meat pounder or the bottom of a clean skillet.
Blend the flour with salt and pepper and dredge the scaloppine on all sides. Heat the butter in a large heavy skillet until it is quite hot but not brown.
Add the scaloppine (note that they shrink as they cook).
Cook quickly until golden, for about 2 minutes, on one side and turn.
Cook until golden on the other side.
Remove the scaloppine to a warm dish and keep warm and covered with foil.
Add the shallots to the skillet and cook briefly, stirring.
Add the wine and cook, stirring, until it is almost evaporated.
Add the cream and let it boil up, stirring.
Cook about 30 seconds and turn off the heat.
Stir in the mustard.
Do not cook further.
Pour sauce over veal and serve.
Yield:
2 or 3 servings.

title: lemon biscuit wreaths
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix butter, sugar, eggs and lemon juice.
Add flour mixture until soft dough.
Make about 1 to 2-inch balls with dough.
Then roll into ropes.
Twist ends to make wreaths.
Roll wreaths in powdered sugar and use lemon zest as a garnish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Put in blender or mixer, liquid ingredients first.
Add sugar and cocoa, blend, pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350 for 35-40 mins., will be shakey in middle.
Great with ice cream or cool whip.

title: mock lasagne
directions: Mix macaroni, salt, pepper, yogurt and 1 egg together; place in a buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Spread beaten egg and 2 tablespoons grated cheese over mixture in pie pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, or until knife comes out clean.
Serve with spaghetti sauce and remaining cheese.

title: crustless brownie pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Beat for 4 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Stir in nuts.
Spread batter evenly in buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean (pie will puff, then fall slightly).
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put in layers:
broken lettuce; hard-boiled eggs (sliced); salt and pepper; raw peas, drained; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon of sugar; lettuce; shredded Swiss cheese; bacon or bacon bits and mayonnaise.
Let set at least 6 hours or overnight.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Put pineapple juice, catsup, vinegar, sugar and soy sauce into pan.
Stir in cornstarch mixed with cold water.
Cook until thickened.
Do not boil.
Add all the rest of ingredients and heat to serve.

title: viennese fish casserole(if you like fish and potatoes, you'll love this dish!)
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish generously.
Arrange boiled, sliced potatoes on all sides of baking dish, as if lining the sides of the dish with potatoes.
Place fish fillets in bottom of pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: mumma's shortcake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Add milk and rest of dry ingredients.
Bake in long greased pan (8 x 12-inch or a little larger).
Bake at 350° until light brown (about 30 minutes).
Cool; cut in squares and top with strawberries that have been mixed with sugar.

title: butter coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, vanilla pudding, oil, water, eggs and vanilla together for batter.
Mix together cinnamon, chopped walnuts or pecans and sugar.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 of batter in pan; sprinkle 1/4 of cinnamon/sugar mixture on top. Repeat.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mediterranean fish bake
directions: Put onion, celery and tops and parsley in an ungreased baking dish, then the fish, then salt and pepper.
Add cooking oil and paprika by sprinkling on top of fish.
Bake 10 minutes, then pour tomato sauce on and bake 30 to 35 minutes more.
(Try it served over white rice with broccoli on the side.)

title: hot pear relish(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Grind pears alternately with onions and peppers in food grinder or processor.
Mix thoroughly and set aside.
Combine sugar, mustard, salt and turmeric in kettle.
Add prepared fruit and vegetables and return to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes, stirring frequently.
Ladle into hot, sterilized quart canning jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace and seal with canning lids according to manufacturer's directions.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Put in layers in a jar or container.
Mix liquid and seasonings.
Pour over slices.
Store for 5 days before using.

title: duck ala orange
directions: Wash duck.
Poke holes in skin all over duck.
Bake in oven without lid at 450° for 25 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Add 3 cups orange juice.
Cover with lid.
Put back in oven at 350° for 2 1/4 hours.
Pour the juice from the duck over a bed of cooked rice.

title: chicken fajita pitas
directions: In large skillet, heat corn oil and garlic over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and saute 4 minutes or until tender.
Add peppers and onion; saute 4 minutes.
Spoon chicken mixture on pitas.
Top with salsa and sour cream, if desired.
Fold pitas and enjoy.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Bake at 375° for 6 to 10 minutes.
This can be used as a drop cookie if you wish.
Use a little more flour and you can roll it out thin and cut into shapes.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Boil noodles until al dente; drain well.
Slice cabbage coarsely.
Fry cabbage and onion in butter until golden in color. Stir while frying, adding more butter if needed.
Stir drained noodles into cabbage.
Cover and heat through.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Sift corn meal, baking powder and salt together.
Mix soda with buttermilk and add to dry ingredients.
Add egg and beat well.
Add water to make a medium thick batter.
Grease skillet with oil, pour batter in and bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Beat all ingredients, except nuts, with rotary mixer.
Mix in nuts.
Pour in crust and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: blackberry-buttermilk cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well. Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Combine buttermilk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk mixture alternately to creamed mixture.
Fold in blackberries. Spread batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Invert on
wire rack.
Cool completely.
Combine powdered sugar and enough milk to make drizzling consistency.
Drizzle over cake.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in buttered 8-inch square baking dish.
Add a small amount of water with apples.
Mix together butter, sugar, flour and cinnamon until crumbly.
Place mixture on top of apples. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces with seasoned salt.
Blend spaghetti sauce mix and crumbs.
Roll chicken in crumb mixture.
Fry in hot oil in skillet.
Add wine, tomatoes, mushrooms and remaining crumb mixture.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve with spinach salad and garlic bread.
Serves 4.

title: sausage pepper pot
directions: Cook and stir sausage and peppers in a large skillet on medium heat until sausage is browned.
Stir in broth water and beans. Bring to boil; stir in rice and paprika.
Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir.
Serves 4.

title: cheese crescents
directions: Prepare biscuit mix according to package directions for biscuits.
(Note:
The 2/3 cup of milk is the amount specified in most biscuit mixes to go with 2 1/4 cups of mix.
Read your own box directions for the exact amount of milk to be used.)
Knead 8 to 10 times.
Roll out on floured surface to 14-inch circle.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cut into pie shape wedges. Roll to form.
Place point side down on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Dredge blueberries in flour and set aside.
Cream margarine with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold into cake batter; blend well.
Gently stir in berries.
Spoon mixture into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: homemade cornbread stuffing
directions: Blend together	all ingredients.
Stuff large turkey or chicken or may be pan baked.

title: holiday shortbread drops
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in egg yolk, vanilla and salt. Mix well.
Stir in flour.
Mix in raisins and walnuts.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until delicately brown on bottom.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chicken rice almondine
directions: Mix together like chicken salad and spread into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: orzo fruit salad
directions: Cook orzo until well done.
Rinse with cold water and drain well.
Drain pineapple and oranges, saving juice from oranges. Mix juice from oranges with sugar, flour, salt and eggs.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool and add fruit and drained pasta, mixing well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine
ingredients
and
pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake for 50 minutes very slow.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and shape into a log.
Roll in chili powder and slice.

title: barbecued chicken in the oven(wings, legs or breasts)
directions: Season the wings with the ingredients, and in a greased baking pan, place
the
wings.
Let
cook for 30 minutes, covered,
After
minutes,
uncover,
empty
excess grease, and cover with
Hunt's barbecue sauce.
Cook for 20 to 30 more minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Combine butter and bread in blender to make crumbs.
Set aside.
Mash turnips in blender.
Put all other ingredients in blender and mix.
Pour into a casserole dish and stir in 1/2 of bread crumbs.
Put rest of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: patio hamburger pie
directions: Cook onions.
Add meat, salt and pepper.
Brown and pour off fat.
Add green beans and soup to mixture.
Pour into greased deep dish pie plate.
Prepare potatoes and spoon in mounds onto meat mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until heated or potatoes turn golden brown on top. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice and use instead of water).
Mix cake according to directions.
Cut up 4 slices of pineapple in cake mix.
Grease and lightly flour bottom of cake pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon (enough to cover the floured bottom).
Place pineapple circles on bottom of pan.
Pour cake mix over circles, covering well.
Bake according to directions.
Let cool 20 minutes.
Turn upside down on board or tray.
Cut into squares and top with Cool Whip.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup in a heavy pan. Cook mixture, without stirring, to 240°. Add peanuts and salt and continue cooking to 290°. Stir continuously after adding peanuts. Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and soda. Stir rapidly until soda stops foaming. Working quickly, spread onto buttered cookie sheet. Crack into pieces when completely cool.

title: beef in wine sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until meat is done.
Serve over noodles.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk.
Stir in 2 cups Cool Whip.
Add the blueberries.
Save some for on top.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Rinse shrimp well; drain on paper towels.
Melt butter in oblong baking dish.
Add garlic and tablespoon of parsley; mix well.
Add single layer of shrimp. Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp; sprinkle with lemon juice and remaining parsley.
Bake 5 minutes more, or until shrimp are pink.
Shrimp will become tough if overcooked.

title: green chili dip(hilton head island)
directions: Mix all together after draining peppers.
Pour into a pie pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in slow oven.

title: sugar-free spiced tea
directions: Mix all together.
Store in closed jar.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and margarine.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Combine other ingredients and spread over crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients well and spoon 1/2 of batter in stem pan and sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon mix. Add rest of water and bake at 350°.

title: salad dressing francais
directions: Blend with mixer or blender at least two full minutes.
Put into clean jar and refrigerate prior to use.
Use in place of bottled French dressing.
Use within two weeks.
